title: ritz bits snack mix
directions: In a small bowl, mix oil, salad dressing and dill weed.
Stir and set aside.
Place the Ritz Bits, oyster crackers and pretzels in a large bowl or container.
Be sure to take the pretzels by hand from the bag.
Do not pour directly from the bag!
A large amount of salt settles at the bottom of the bag and can give the mixture a very salty flavor.
Stir the oil-dressing mixture again, then pour over the cracker-pretzel mixture.
Mix with a large spoon and coat well (3 to 5 minutes).
Let stand for 30 minutes (or eat immediately if you wish).

title: chocolate eclair cookies
directions: Line a bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with a layer of graham crackers (whole).
Prepare pudding according to directions and combine with Cool Whip.
Pour pudding over graham crackers.
Top with chocolate frosting.
Chill 1 hour.

title: old fashion chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: veggie casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed; drain.
Mix together vegetables, mayo, onion, celery and cheese.
Top with crackers.
Pour melted butter on top. Bake at 350° until top is browned.

title: chocolate pie #1
directions: In heavy saucepan combine sugar, flour, salt and cocoa. Make certain there are no lumps. Add milk and eggs. Cook at medium temperature, stirring often. When mixture becomes hot, add margarine. Continue to cook until mixture begins to boil, and thickens. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla. Pour into pie shell.

title: pasta with carbonara sauce
directions: Cook noodles in salted boiling water for 10 to 12 minutes until tender but firm.
Drain well.
Let eggs, margarine and cream stand at room temperature for 2 to 3 hours.
Beat together eggs and cream just until blended.
Toss pasta with butter and pepperoni.
Pour egg mixture over this and toss until pasta is well coated.
Add cheese and parsley.
Serve immediately.
Cook with French bread.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook onions and peppers in shortening until onions are clear. Add hamburger and salt.
Cook until mixture falls apart.
Add tomatoes, rice, and other seasonings.
Arrange in large casserole. Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: ricotta spinach quiche
directions: Cook spinach; drain well.
Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Stir in spinach, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
In large bowl, combine Ricotta and Parmesan cheese, cream and eggs; mix thoroughly.
Stir into spinach mixture.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and bake 40 minutes.

title: aggie maroon punch
directions: Add ginger ale to juice in a large punch bowl. Float strawberries on top. Serve over ice or can make an ice ring using strawberries. Makes 1 1/2 gallons. Serves 50.

title: judy's sausage and chicken stew
directions: Cut kielbasa diagonally into 1/2-inch slices.
Chop onion. Cut celery stalk diagonally into 1/4-inch slices.
In a 5-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat, cook kielbasa until lightly browned.
With slotted spoon, remove kielbasa to bowl.
In drippings in Dutch oven, cook onion and celery until tender-crisp, stirring frequently.
Add beans with their liquid, carrots, tomatoes, thyme leaves, chicken pieces and kielbasa; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 5 minutes or until heated through.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice.
Add cream cheese, onion, salt, garlic salt and pepper sauce.
Blend.
Stir in tomatoes. Serve with chips.
Makes 4 cups.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, onion
and garlic salt; add diced ham chips. Roll into a ball.
Cover with nuts; chill.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix and put in graham cracker crust.

title: hawaiian sunset cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat 3 minutes on medium speed.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool layers before adding filling and topping.

title: oriental carrot souffle
directions: Saute
peas
and bean sprouts slightly, just to soften. Season with marjoram, parsley flakes, salt, pepper, butter and soy sauce. Set
aside.
Season carrots with cloves, honey and salt.
Butter a
souffle
dish
or Bundt pan.
Melt remaining butter, add
flour and
cook
minutes.
Add cream and cook until
thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add egg yolks and
carrots.
Cool. Fold
in egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 35
minutes.
Unmold
on platter.
Place
peas
and
bean sprout mixture
in
center and surround with a row of mushroom caps that have been lightly sauteed in butter and lemon juice. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine egg, milk and salt.
Add flour.
Dough should be stiff.
If not, add a little more flour.
Roll very thin on floured surface.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Roll up like jelly roll and slice 1/8-inch thick.
Spread noodles out on wax paper to dry, about 2 hours.
Drop into boiling broth.
Boil 15 to 20 minutes until tender.
Delicious.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut potatoes into thin slices but not all the way through.
Put potatoes in a baking dish.
Fan them slightly. Add butter.
Sprinkle with salt, onions and cilantro.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake for another 10 minutes or until cheese melts and potatoes are soft inside.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice; add fruit and coconut. Mix with spoon and fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into prepared graham cracker crusts.
Garnish with fine chopped nuts (pecans or English walnuts).
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Will keep a week in refrigerator.

title: douglas egg pie
directions: Mix flour with sugar. Beat eggs, sugar and margarine together. Add milk, mixing well. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Put in unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: corny dogs
directions: Delete dry mustard and replace with finely diced onion and you have hush puppies.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla; beat in eggs.
Blend in chocolate.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Bake in 8 x 8-inch greased pan at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Lasts six days in refrigerator.

title: salsa
directions: Cook all ingredients, except tomato paste, until tender.
Then add the tomato paste.
Seal in pint jars.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat together sugar, oil and eggs. Stir together flour, cinnamon and soda.
Blend flour into first mixture.
Add canned pumpkin and beat well.
Pour batter into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Place in cold oven and turn to 325°.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Remove from oven, cool 5 minutes and remove from pan.
Glaze while warm.

title: golden coffee cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together for 8 minutes.
Pour half of batter into a Bundt pan which has been greased and floured. Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon over batter reserving some for top.
Pour remaining batter in pan and sprinkle with remaining sugar/cinnamon mix.
Cut through with a knife or spatula.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: reuben chicken
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place layer of boneless chicken breasts. Next layer drained sauerkraut over chicken.
Then layer Swiss cheese over sauerkraut and top cheese with 8 ounce bottle of Thousand Island dressing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar and oil.
Sift flour , soda and salt.
Add a little at a time.
Fold in nuts, apples and vanilla. Bake in a Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.
It may take more than an hour, just keep checking.

title: chicken continental
directions: Saute chicken, mushrooms and garlic in oil for 2 to 3 minutes. Add all remaining ingredients, except rice; bring to a full boil. Stir in rice.
Remove from heat, cover and let stand 5 minutes (or until liquid is absorbed).
Serves 4.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk with electric mixer. Add Eagle Brand milk and cheese. Fold in Cool Whip.
Line a large glass serving bowl with vanilla wafers, then sliced bananas, then add pudding. Chill and serve.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and bring to a boil (stirring constantly).
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and peanut butter.
Then add oats. . Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto buttered plate or on wax paper.
Cool and enjoy.

title: french fried onions
directions: Slice onions 1/2 inch thick and cover with cold water.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Wipe dry and separate rings.
Mix flour, salt and sugar.
Combine egg and milk and add dry ingredients. Add oil.
Mix thoroughly.
Dip onion rings into batter and fry in deep fat until brown.
Drain.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix 3/4 cup Pepperidge Farm herb dressing with ingredients. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with 1 cup grated cheese, 1/2 cup dressing crumbs and 2 tablespoons margarine mixed together.
Bake at 400° until bubbles and turns brown.

title: old fashion kidney bean salad
directions: Peel eggs and cut in small pieces.
Mix all ingredients. Chill and serve on lettuce.

title: magic peach cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in a 9 x 15-inch pan.
Mix ingredients in a bowl and pour on top of butter; do not stir.
Add peaches on top of batter.
Add the cup of sugar by sprinkling over the top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix.
Cook
in	greased and floured Bundt pan.	Bake 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: rumaki
directions: Cut chicken livers into halves; cut water chestnuts crosswise into halves.
Mix soy sauce, brown sugar, ginger root and garlic in glass or plastic bowl; stir in chicken livers and water chestnuts. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours; drain.
Cut bacon slices into halves.
Wrap piece of liver and piece of chestnut in each bacon piece.
Secure with wooden pick.
Arrange on rack in broiler pan.
Cook in 400° oven, turning once, until bacon is crisp, 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 20.

title: joyce's strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix
and
flour well.	Add oil and water; then add eggs, one at
a time, beating well after each.
Add strawberries to mixture and
beat well.	Pour batter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Cream butter, flour and pecans (save some pecans for topping). Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes; let cool.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup Cool Whip and 1 cup 10x sugar. Spread over crust.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Make 2 packages chocolate pudding using 3 cups of milk.
Spread over cream cheese. Spread with remaining Cool Whip.
Top with pecans and coconut.
Refrigerate 1 day before serving.

title: betty ann colombo's pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Line pie shell with pecans in a circular pattern.
Beat eggs in a bowl until well mixed (not whipped).
Set aside.
Put sugar and syrup into a heavy saucepan (small pot).
Cook over low heat, stirring until sugar is dissolved and mixture is smooth.
Pour hot syrup mixture gradually into eggs, constantly stirring.
Add the butter and keep stirring until butter is melted.
Stir in vanilla extract.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a small bowl, combine onion and bread crumbs; sprinkle evenly over a baking sheet lightly coated with Pam. Bake for about 12 minutes or until golden brown. Remove from oven and set aside. In a large bowl, combine soup,yogurt and liquid smoke; stir in green beans and bacon. Transfer mixture to a 7x11 Baking dish, sprayed with Pam. Top with onion mixture. Bake 25-30 minutes.

title: warm green bean salad
directions: Steam beans until tender.
Blend the vinegar, oil, seed and chopped dill.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Toss with beans.
Serves 8.

title: ladyfinger supreme
directions: Split the ladyfingers and making sure the rounded side is facing out and the cut side in, line the sides and bottom of a 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan.
Keep the balance of the ladyfingers.
Set aside.
Cream the cream cheese; add vanilla and sugar.
Cream well. Whip heavy cream until very stiff.
Fold heavy cream and cream cheese mixture together.
Pour half the cream cheese mixture over the ladyfingers.
Cover this with ladyfingers that were set aside. Cover with all the balance of cream cheese mixture over the ladyfingers.
Top with pie filling.
Chill in refrigerator for at least 3 hours or overnight.

title: christmas fruit cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add fruits, nuts, vanilla and soda water.
Add eggs and molasses and mix well.
Add flour and spices sifted together.
Mix well; drop by spoonful on well-greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.
Flavor improves with age.

title: "vrasta fasoulakia freska" - stewed fresh green beans
directions: Saute onion in butter until golden.
Meanwhile, wash beans and cut in 2-inch lengths.
Add to onion and saute, stirring constantly until beans have turned a bright green.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer gently 30 minutes or until beans are tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet potato angel biscuits
directions: Wash sweet potatoes; bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done. Let potatoes cool to touch; peel and mash.
Set aside 3 cups and keep warm.
Combine yeast and warm water in a 2-cup liquid measuring cup; let stand 5 minutes.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients in a large bowl; cut in shortening until mixture is crumbly.
Add yeast mixture and warm sweet potatoes, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; knead 5 minutes.
Place dough in a lightly greased bowl, turning to grease top.

title: feta mushrooms
directions: Brush the mushrooms clean.
Remove stems and reserve.
Brush caps with melted butter; arrange, hollow side up, in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mince reserved mushroom stems.
Heat small frying pan; add butter.
Add stems and onions; saute until liquid has been absorbed.
Add flour to frying pan; mix well.
Add milk, stirring until thickened a bit.
Add parsley, garlic, salt and pepper to taste; mix well.
Add Feta cheese to mixture; fill mushroom caps.
Top with Kasseri and a few dots of butter.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, until stuffing has browned lightly and cheese is melted.
Makes 15 appetizers.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Let jell slightly.
Mix other ingredients and refrigerate.

title: deviled crab
directions: Place fillets on aluminum foil lined pan.
Spread lightly with no fat mayonnaise.
Cover top with corn flake crumbs.
Sprinkle with paprika or dill weed.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 20 minutes, depending on thickness of fillets.
Done when fish flakes with a fork (fish skin will stick to the foil if fish is lifted gently with spatula).

title: berna's holiday oatmeal cookies(yields 7 to 8 dozen)
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda; work butter in bowl.
Add sugars, eggs and vanilla gradually; add dry ingredients to butter mixture.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in 3 cups oats and other ingredients, except 1/2 cup oats.
Shape into a roll and roll it in 1/2 cup oats.
Wrap and chill overnight.
Slice roll into cookies and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Add tomato products using a little water to rinse cans.
Add seasonings to taste; simmer 30 minutes at least.

title: cheesy, vegetable chowder
directions: Saute the first 3 ingredients in the butter. Add the remaining ingredients. Simmer 25 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Stir in envelope of taco seasoning; set aside to cool.
Dice other ingredients.
(I put ground beef mixture on the bottom of serving container.)
Dice tomatoes, green pepper and onion; put on top of ground beef. Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on top.
(Layering ingredients makes it look really colorful.) Grated lettuce goes on top.

title: empanada gallegra (chicken pie)
directions: Boil chicken in water with the quartered onion for 30 minutes. When cool, tear off the bone and tear into bite size chucks. In frying pan heat oil; add diced onions and green pepper and cook for 8 minutes. Add tomatoes and chicken. Pour in pie shell and cover with second pie shell. Bake in 375 degree oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: down home cabbage
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon and drain on paper towels.
Discard all but 1 tablespoon drippings from skillet.
Add onion and saute until golden.
Sprinkle in flour and sugar; stir until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cabbage.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Return bacon to skillet; keep warm.

title: sausage roll
directions: Let bread thaw completely. Brown sausage and crumble it. Drain off fat. Put cheese through food processor until finely ground. Beat eggs and mix all ingredients together (sausage, eggs, parsley and cheeses). Roll out bread. Put sausage mixture in middle of bread. Roll bread into a tube. Let rise 1 hour. Bake at 350° until brown. Butter top of bread after done.

title: nachos
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for about 15 minutes.
Pour over chips.

title: butterscotch fudge
directions: Mix pie mix, sugar and milk until smooth.
Place over medium-low heat.
Stir frequently for 10 minutes.
Lower heat and cook 10 more minutes.
Stir constantly until mixture forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and add 2 tablespoons butter. Beat with electric mixer for 10 minutes, starting on low and gradually increasing to high speed. Stir in chopped pecans.
Pour at once into buttered 8-inch square pan and cut into squares. Yields 2 dozen squares.

title: carrot surprise
directions: Cut carrots
like French fries and about 3-inches long. Add all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer until carrots are tender.
Cook, uncovered, a while to thicken sauce.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: In a large bowl, with electric mixer, beat together cream cheese and peppermint extract.
Add powdered sugar gradually and beat until smooth, kneading the last of the powdered sugar in with hands.
Form mixture into balls the size of a cherry.
Place on wax paper and flatten with fork.
Let stand overnight.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: light 'n crisp waffles
directions: Prepare waffle iron.
Put all ingredients in blender container and process at medium speed until smooth.
Pour 1/2 cup batter over center of grids and bake until golden (about 2 minutes). Yield: 18 servings.

title: dang good pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add melted butter and well beaten eggs. Add
pineapple,
coconut and vanilla.
Put in raw crust and bake until
knife stuck in center of pie comes out clean. Start at 400° for 10 minutes.
Then turn to 325° for remainder of baking time.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Make small meat balls with beef, crumbs, garlic, eggs, salt and pepper.
Fry until brown.
Mix chili sauce and jelly.
Simmer browned meat balls in sauce for 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Sprinkle 1 teaspoon salt over cabbage. Let stand 1 hour. Squeeze out excess water. Mix with other vegetables.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into saucepan.
Set pineapple, marshmallows and nuts aside in large bowl.

title: pecan pie or walnut
directions: Mix and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice green tomatoes 1/2 inch thick (do not peel).
Dip in milk, then in plain flour mixed with salt and pepper, then in the beaten eggs, then in the bread crumbs or corn meal.
Fry over medium-low heat for 8 to 10 minutes on each side, or until brown. Use a heavy pan and 1/2 cup shortening.
Add more shortening as needed.

title: potato sour cream casserole
directions: Boil potatoes whole.
Peel and slice thin when cool.
Blend next 4 ingredients until smooth and add potatoes to mixture.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese or bread crumbs last 5 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package; drain.
Combine all ingredients, except part of cheese.
Place in casserole; top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: tapioca salad
directions: Drain fruit and reserve liquid.
Add water to fruit liquid to make 3 cups.
Use this liquid to cook puddings until thick.
Cool thoroughly.
Add pineapple, orange and marshmallows. Fold in Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: apple fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients; blend in egg and milk.
Stir in apples. Drop by spoonfuls into hot fat; fry on each side until golden brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and nutmeg.
Serve with syrup and butter.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: aunt mary's sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Beat in eggs. Fold in sour cream and vanilla. Mix in flour, baking powder and salt.

title: beef cups
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain off grease.
Add brown sugar and barbecue sauce; simmer 10 minutes.
Mold biscuits to form cups in greased muffin pans.
Fill with hamburger mixture; top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 20 beef cups.

title: prism salad(or broken glass)
directions: Mix jello and water in separate pans making as thin a layer as possible.
It is necessary to prepare this ahead of time so it will be well set.
Heat pineapple juice.
Add the gelatin which has been softened in a little cold water.
Let cool, but it shouldn't start to set.
Whip the cream; add sugar and pineapple juice.
Cut jello into small squares and add to whipped cream mixture until well mixed.
Spread over a graham cracker crust. Refrigerate.
Serves 12.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in microwave in a casserole dish according to package directions.
Cut up cheese and add to broccoli.
Cook in microwave until cheese melts.
Add cooked rice and soup.
Stir well.
Cook in microwave until hot.

title: almond bark(microwave)
directions: Using microwave-safe dish, melt chocolate in microwave 2 1/2 minutes at 70% (Roast), stirring 2 to 3 times.
Add almonds; stir. Pour onto foil-lined cookie sheet.
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: shake sweet pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and pack in gallon jar.
Add canning salt; fill with apple cider.
Soak for 6 weeks (date the jar).
After 6 weeks, rinse and cut cucumbers fine into gallon jar.
Add the 5 pounds sugar (1 cup at a time).
Add spices.
Shake after each layer of sugar until you have used all the sugar.
Shake every week for 2 or 3 weeks.
Open and eat.

title: party punch(for diabetics)
directions: Mix juices and let stand overnight.
Pour ginger ale in just before serving.

title: chinese chocolate cake for naughty children(kinesisk sjokoladekake for slemme barn)
directions: Beat the eggs until stiff.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat some more.
Mix flour and baking powder and add alternately with the milk.
Bake in spring-form pan at 375°; cool on rack.
When ready to fill, split in two layers.

title: cindy's punch
directions: Mix sugar and water; boil 5 minutes.
Then add pineapple juice, orange juice and lemon concentrate.
Just before serving, add four quarts chilled ginger ale.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream shortening (lard), sugar and eggs; then add sour cream and vanilla until well mixed.
Sift together dry ingredients blend into creamed mixture.

title: copper carrots
directions: Slice carrots. Cook until crisp-tender. Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to drained carrots. Refrigerate overnight.

title: citrus wings
directions: Place chicken wings in aluminum foil lined pan. Sprinkle with seasoning salt. Cover wings with green pepper and onion. Sprinkle on lemon juice. Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes until done.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine water and eggs, then add meat ball mix. Combine hamburger with mixture.

Add green pepper and onion to mixture. Roll into balls and bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cook barbecue sauce, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce on top of stove for 10 minutes. Let stand until meat balls are done, then pour over meat balls.
Cook on simmer or in crock-pot on low for 1 hour.

title: chocolate dream squares
directions: Melt chocolate and cool.
Line a buttered pan with crushed graham crackers.
Save a portion of the crackers to sprinkle on top.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add cooled chocolate, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into pan and sprinkle with reserved graham crackers.

title: chicken salad
directions: For sauce, combine thoroughly the mayonnaise, soy sauce and curry; set aside.

title: meat loaf cooked in crock pot
directions: Reserve 2 tablespoons ketchup.
Combine ground chuck, eggs, oats, soup mix and remaining ketchup.
Shape into a loaf.
Place in crock pot with remaining ketchup.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours or cook 4 to 6 hours on high.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan over medium-high heat. Stir in onion, green pepper, celery and garlic; cook until vegetables are tender crisp, stirring occasionally. Add remaining ingredients, except avocado and cheese. Bring to boil; reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Garnish with avocado slices and cheese. Yields 7 to 8 cups.

title: chocolate chip cereal cookies
directions: This makes a double recipe, it makes a bunch. Cream together shortening and sugars, add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients then drop by spoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until light brown, about 10-12 min. Cookies will still be a little soft, cool 2 min. before removing from cookie sheet.
If cookies flatten out to much add a little bit of flour.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in a 7 x 11 x 2-inch pan.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Heat first four ingredients together.
Put chicken in rolls. Place side by side.
Pour sauce over rolls.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans.
Chill mixture until firm.
Roll in 1 large ball or 2 small balls.
Roll in pecans. Good with Triscuits.

title: cranberry-nut bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda into large bowl.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Add eggs, orange peel and orange juice all at once; stir until evenly moist.
Fold in cranberries and walnuts.
Spray pans with nonstick cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Mini loaf pans take about 25 to 30 minutes (bake 4, then 3).
Two pans take 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: spoon bread
directions: Scald milk (do not boil).
Stir in butter, cornmeal and salt. Cook, stirring constantly, until cornmeal comes away from sides of pan and thickens.
Set aside and cool to lukewarm, add beaten egg yolks and mix well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a greased and floured 2-quart baking dish at 375° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: mac tomato cheese bake
directions: Mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes; cut potatoes 4 ways leaving peelings on. Arrange in shallow pan.
Mix remaining ingredients; brush on potatoes.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.
Brush occasionally during baking; last 5 minutes broil to make crispy.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Chop potatoes in bite size pieces.
Put potatoes in well buttered casserole.
Dab with rest of butter.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream butter

and sugar. Blend in eggs, vanilla and pumpkin. Add slowly to dry ingredients. Add nuts. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake 350 degrees for 60-70 minutes. Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: raisin cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour and milk, then vanilla flavoring.
Mix well.
Flour raisins to prevent sinking to bottom of cake and add to mixture with preserves.
Use four loaf pans and line bottoms with wax paper.
Grease and flour generously.
Put in cold oven.
Set oven at 250° for 1 hour.
Turn heat to 325° and cook until done, about 30 to 40 minutes longer.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Bake pie crust.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and pineapple. Stir in Cool Whip.
Put into pie shell, then let chill 1 hour.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs, sour cream, pistachio pudding and oil; beat for 10 minutes.
Fold in nuts and chocolate bits.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick tests dry.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Beat brown sugar and butter until fluffy.
Stir in Bisquick and walnuts until mixture is crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup remaining mixture in pan. Bake 12 minutes.

title: tomato wedges with basil dressing
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; cover and chill. Place lettuce leaves on each serving plate, if desired. Place 3 tomato wedges on lettuce on each plate; top with dressing.
Yields 12 servings. Contains 39 calories and 12% fat per serving.

title: pirohy
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add egg and water to make a soft dough.
Turn on lightly floured board and knead gently about 5 minutes.
Allow to stand about 10 minutes before you roll. Roll dough quite thin, cut in 2 inch squares, place a tsp. of filling in center and fold corners, making triangles.
Seal edge well by pinching.
Cook in boiling salt water.
Allow to simmer until they float to the top, about seven minutes.
Drain. Fry chopped onions in butter and pour over Pirohy.

title: stir-fried clams
directions: Put cooking oil in pan and heat.
When the oil is hot, put garlic, ginger root and green onion in and stir for 10 seconds. Add clams and keep stirring for 5 minutes or until done.
Add soy sauce and sugar and stir 10 seconds.
Serve while hot.
Great with spaghetti.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar, salt and soda together. Pour oil into the buttermilk and add the liquids to the dry ingredients.
Mix to make a soft dough.
Turn out on a floured board.
Gently roll out to 3/4 inch thick; cut with small biscuit cutter.
Place on a slightly greased pan close together.
Bake at 425° for about 12 minutes.
Makes 12 to 16 biscuits.

title: fried fresh okra
directions: Mix eggs with okra.
Add cornmeal and mix together.
Place in a cast iron skillet of oil, the grease must be hot.
Fry on each side! Enjoy!
Now you must wash the dishes-HA.

title: italian three-cheese macaroni
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 2-quart round casserole with nonstick cooking spray. Cook macaroni according to package directions until al dente. Drain and set aside. Meanwhile, melt margarine in medium saucepan over medium heat. Add flour, Italian seasoning, pepper and salt, stirring until smooth. Gradually add milk, stirring constantly until slightly thickened. Add Cheddar and Parmesan; stir until cheeses melt. Layer pasta, tomatoes and cheese sauce in prepared dish. Repeat layers. Combine Mozzarella and bread crumbs in small bowl. Sprinkle evenly over casserole. Spray bread crumb mixture with cooking spray. Bake, covered, about 30 minutes, until hot and bubbly. Uncover and bake 5 minutes until top is golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles; spread over bottom of 9 x 13 baking dish.
Drain water off chicken and spread over noodles.
Add 2 tablespoons of water to chicken soup; spread over chicken.
Slice Velveeta; place over soup.
Slice boiled eggs; put over cheese.
Melt butter. Crumble crackers.
Mix butter and crackers together; spread over eggs.
Put in oven at 350° until cheese is bubbling or crackers are golden brown.

title: chicken and broccoli alfredo
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions.
Add broccoli for last 4 minutes of cooking time.
Drain.
Heat butter in skillet.
Add chicken and cook until browned, stirring often.
Add soup, milk, cheese, pepper and linguine mixture and heat through. Serve with additional Parmesan cheese.
Prep/Cook Time:
20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry brownie torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease two 9 inch round cake pans.
Line with wax paper, extending up sides of pans; grease wax paper.
Prepare brownie mix as directed for cake like brownies; pour into prepared pans.
Bake 20 minutes or until springs back when touched.
Cool.
In large bowl, mix sweetened condensed milk and water, beat in pudding; chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Place one brownie layer on serving plate.
Top with half of pudding mixture and strawberries.
Repeat.
Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: quick cranberry conserve
directions: About 10 minutes before serving:
In a medium bowl, stir all ingredients until mixed.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
Makes 3 cups.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar, Crisco and egg.
Add milk and bananas.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Bake for 70 minutes.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all together.
Top with crumbled potato chips or Ritz crackers.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: just plain fudge
directions: Place 2 quart saucepan on stove over medium heat, with all ingredients, except butter and vanilla, stirring all only until sugar is dissolved.
Cover until it begins to boil.
Remove cover and reduce heat to low.
Insert
candy thermometer, cook until thermometer reads 240 degrees.
Remove from heat and add butter - DO NOT STIR.
Allow to cool undisturbed until temp is 120 degrees. Add vanilla and whip until fudge begins to dull.
Pour onto buttered marble candy board, aluminum pan or similar surface.
Cut into bite sized pieces when ready to serve.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine; let cool.
Cream with sugar.
Add eggs and remaining ingredients.
Bake in unbaked pie shell 40 minutes at 300°.
Cool before serving.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cover potatoes with water and boil until tender; drain well. Mash potatoes and stir in salad dressing, softened cream cheese and onion flakes.
Mix well and add salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon into casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle paprika over potatoes and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May be prepared and frozen for future use.

title: healthy stuffing
directions: Saute everything except millet and tahini for 5 minutes or until tender.
Add to grain and add tahini.
To cook millet, toast in a pan and dry.
Add 3 3/4 cups boiling water and simmer.
Lower to low heat, cover and cook for 35 to 40 minutes.
Millet is a grain found in health food stores.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Soak 2 packages of yeast and 1 tablespoon of sugar in 3 tablespoons of lukewarm water until thoroughly wet and working.

title: marilyn's crazy meatballs
directions: Combine meat, bread crumbs, eggs and onion soup mix.
Mix well.
Shape into golf size meatballs and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 2 hours.

title: basic yeast rolls
directions: Scald milk, sugar, margarine and salt.
Add egg and yeast.
Mix in flour until dough is stiff and can be turned out on floured board to knead.
Knead well.
Place in greased bowl and let rise until doubled.
Let rise again.
Place rolls in greased pan.
Let rise about 1 hour or until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients with 1/4 cup of the condensed tomato soup.
Mix well, then shape into about 20 small balls. Place in skillet.
Mix remaining soup, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over the meat balls and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 40 minutes, stirring often.
Serves 5.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon mixture over melted butter (do not mix together).
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 375° until brown.
Do not overbake.

title: autumn apple dip
directions: For a healthier alternative to chips and dip, mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate and serve with cut up pieces of apples, oranges, peaches, grapes, pineapple, etc.

title: barbecue pork chop casserole
directions: Line oblong dish with large butter beans.
Then mix together catsup, mustard, brown sugar and honey (or molasses) making a homemade barbecue sauce.
Pour this sauce over lima beans, spreading evenly.
Place pork chops on top of barbecue sauce.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour, turning after the first 30 minutes.
May be eaten alone or any leftover sauce may be served over rice.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat oil.
Scramble eggs (always scramble eggs separately). Remove and fry bacon.
Stir in scallions.
Add rice, soy sauce and salt.
Heat until rice is heated through.
Add shrimp, beef or pork, peas and eggs.
Cook until heated through.

title: fresh mushroom pate
directions: In a wide frying pan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add mushrooms and onion and cook, stirring often, until mushrooms are browned (about 15 minutes).
Mix in sherry.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat.
Drain excess fat.
Add sausage, garlic, basil, salt, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles, drain; rinse.
Beat eggs.
Add Ricotta, Romano cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
Layer half the noodles in baking dish.
Spread with 1/2 the Ricotta filling.
Add 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 the meat sauce.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes.

title: helpful health drink
directions: Use juice from bottles.
Mix and store in refrigerator.
Drink 1/4 cup daily to reduce cholesterol and arthritis.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix and bake in floured tube pan 45 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven and punch 100 holes all the way to the bottom.
Ice while hot.

title: spicy pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 250°. Beat egg white with 1 tablespoon water until frothy. Melt butter in a baking pan in the oven; stir frequently.
In a small bowl, combine sugar, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Put pecans in egg white and coat well, then put them into sugar and spices; coat well.
Place on melted butter in baking pan and bake at 250° 15-20 minutes or until done.

title: chicken or beef fajitas
directions: Cut the meat in strips.
Mix the soya sauce, oil, and lemon juice.
Pour over meat.
For chicken, let it soak for 3 hrs. or overnight. For beef soak 8 - 24 hrs.

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Add cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Spread evenly in a buttered 9 x 13 inch pan. Cut into squares when cool.

title: southfork chili
directions: Saute onions and peppers.
Add ground beef; brown.
Add remaining seasonings, then canned goods.
Simmer for about 45 minutes or until slightly thickened and flavors are well mixed. Serve in hot taco shells.

title: lighten-up cereal cookies
directions: Mash bananas, then add rest of ingredients; mixing well. Drop cookie mix by spoonfuls onto a sprayed (or greased) cookie sheet.

title: pineapple honey cake
directions: Drain pineapple and set aside.
Combine rest of the ingredients and stir well until blended.
Add all except 1/2 cup of pineapple to the mixture, blend together.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Cover batter with rest of pineapple mixed with 1/4 cup oleo, and 1/3 cup of honey.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: easy no-roll pastry
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in 9-inch pie pan.
Mix with fork.
Beat oil and milk together with fork.
Mix into flour mixture until evenly dampened.
Press with fingers in even layer over bottom and up sides to partially cover rim; flute edges. This is a rich crust.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: wonderful egg bread
directions: Beat eggs well; add butter, milk and oil.
Stir meal, soda and salt.
Add to liquid and whisk really well.
Pour in greased pan and cook at 450° until done.

title: rice casserole
directions: Put together in a casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: creamy caramel-peach parfaits
directions: Fold ice cream topping into whipped topping in small bowl. Layer cookies, whipped topping mixture and peaches in 6 parfait or other tall glasses. Sprinkle with cookie crumbs, if desired. Serve immediately or refrigerate until serving time.

title: beef tortilla casserole
directions: Crumble beef into a large microwave-safe dish. Stir in onion. Microwave, uncovered, on High for 8 to 9 minutes or until meat is no longer pink, stirring and draining every 2 minutes. Stir in taco sauce and tortillas. In a greased 2 1/2-quart microwave-safe dish, layer half of the beef mixture, sour cream and cheeses. Repeat layers. Cover and cook at 70% power for 10 to 11 minutes. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: congo squares
directions: Cream the brown sugar and margarine.
Stir in eggs.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: caramel cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar together; beat until fluffy.
Add
eggs	and
beat
1 minute.
Add flour mixed with baking powder
and	salt
to creamed mixture, alternately with milk.
Beat
until smooth.	Add flavorings and mix well.
Bake in 3 layer
cake
pans
that have been greased and floured, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: seafood chowder
directions: In 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, in hot oil, cook onion, garlic and dill until onion is tender, stirring occasionally. Stir in soups and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring often. Cook 8 minutes. Reduce heat to low. Add shrimp and fish. Cook 5 minutes more or until shrimp turn pink and opaque and fish flakes easily when tested with fork.

title: onion and bacon quiche
directions: In a large frying pan cook onions in butter over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until onions soften and begin to brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
While onions cook, saute bacon until lightly browned; drain well.
Beat eggs, cream and salt.
Spread onions in pie crust.
Sprinkle evenly with bacon.
Pour in egg mixture. Bake on lowest rack at 450° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and continue baking until top browns lightly, about 15 minutes longer.

title: never fail cranberry sauce
directions: Cook
cranberries in water until tender.
Press through a sieve;
add
sugar.
Cook until it starts to boil; continue boiling
for another ten minutes, stirring frequently.
Put in a mold or pan and let cool.
Easy!

title: raisin pie
directions: Separate the eggs.
Mix the egg yolks and all other ingredients together to make the pie filling.
Fill the pie crust and bake until nearly done.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Note:
Recipe is for half the amount of rice and dal.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Place beef in crock-pot.
Mix beefy onion soup mix with 2 cups of
water	(just
enough
to cover meat).	Cook on low about
10 hours.
Add
cans
of
sliced
carrots and potatoes during last 3 hours.
Cook setting on high about 4 to 6 hours.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour in greased jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pan de elote
directions: Mix corn, bisquick, sugar, milk and butter.
Stir to remove lumps.
Pour 1/2 batter into a greased 8 x 8 pan.
Top with green chiles and lay cheese slices on top.
Pour rest of batter over all.
Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes or until top is brown.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, brown sugar and eggs.
Add oil, vanilla, nuts and strawberries.
Blend all ingredients together thoroughly.
Pour into two greased (Pam sprayed) loaf pans.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until feels done to touch.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Tear bread into bite size pieces and place in bottom of pan.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; add cheese, sugar, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Serve in individual salad bowls.
Top with crumbled bacon.

title: quick chocolate frosting
directions: Combine butter, milk and salt in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until butter is melted.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate morsels and beat until smooth.
Cool. Gradually add sugar, beating until thick enough to spread.
If necessary, add additional sugar to obtain spreading consistency. Yields enough for 1 (8-inch) 2-layer cake.

title: messed-up potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes; make a layer of pork chops, potatoes and sliced onions.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Dilute can of mushroom soup with milk.
Pour over pork chops/potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours (until tender).

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix flour and cake mix together.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour alternately with milk and lemon juice.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemon-grape frostie (non-alcoholic drink)
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and mix well.
Pour into 4 ice-filled glasses and garnish with lemon slices.

title: old fashioned spicy donuts
directions: Scald milk.
Add shortening and salt. Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and 2 1/2 cups flour. Beat until smooth.
Cover and let rise until bubbly.
Mix spices with sugar and beaten eggs.
Mix well with bubbly mixture. Add remaining flour to make dough that can be kneaded. Knead until smooth. Cover and let rise until double in bulk. Roll out 1/2-inch thick. Cut.
Let rise on board until double in bulk.
Fry in deep fat at 375° until brown (about 8 minutes).
Makes 3 dozen.

title: skyline nacho dip
directions: Fix Skyline according to directions.
In a glass baking dish, spread cream cheese.
Spread onion over cream cheese, then add Skyline chili.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
Serve with nachos.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together and drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, heat together soup, sour cream, onion and chilies for 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, soften tortillas in hot oil and drain on paper towels.
Top each tortilla with chicken pieces and 2 tablespoons soup mixture.
Roll up. Arrange in oiled 9-inch pan.
Pour remaining soup mixture over enchiladas.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: strawberry truffle
directions: Tear cake in small pieces.
Mix pudding mix and milk.
Beat well in a medium-size bowl.
Mix strawberry glaze and Eagle Brand milk together.
In a tall glass container, assemble, starting with a layer of cake, then a layer of glaze and then a layer of pudding mix.
Continue until all is used.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with nut topping or fresh strawberries.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: great broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Go to Charlotte, NC on I-77.
Take the Nations Ford exit to Sam's Wholesale Club; show your ID card.
Go to frozen food section; buy Campbell's broccoli and cheese soup.
Take home; follow directions and enjoy!

title: preacher's casserole
directions: Brown hamburger (round is less fatty).	Add onions and celery. Add tomato soup and mushroom soup, water, chili powder and salt and pepper. Mix in rice noodles. Put in 9 x 12 Pyrex casserole and add remaining noodles on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 8.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Break angel food cake into bite-size pieces and place into a punch bowl.
Mix sour cream, Cool Whip, powdered sugar and evaporated milk.
Pour over angel food cake.
Top with strawberries and strawberry glaze.
Refrigerate.

title: crispy baked fish fillets
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Wash and dry fillets and cut into serving pieces.
Season, dip in oil and coat with cornflake crumbs.
Arrange in a single layer in a lightly oiled shallow baking dish.
Bake 10 minutes without turning or basting.
Yield: 4 servings, 260 calories/serving.
This is a low cholesterol, reduced fat recipe.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; add chopped onion, both cans of soup and green beans (drained).
Mix well and put into a large casserole dish.
Arrange Tater Tots on top.
Bake for 40 minutes at 375°. Do not cover while baking.

title: chicken cheese dinner
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan. Coat chicken with flour, place skin side down in margarine.
Bake uncovered, 30 minutes.
Turn and bake 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.
Remove from oven, reduce heat to 325°.
Add onions and mushrooms.
In bowl, mix milk, soup, cheese and pepper.
Pour on chicken.
Cover with foil, bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve on rice.

title: mounds candy bars
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar, coconut and vanilla.
Shape into small bars or balls, as desired.

title: barbecued frankfurters
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Add all ingredients, except franks. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Arrange franks in shallow pan.
Pour sauce over franks.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes in moderate oven, about 350°.

title: mexican style chili bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green peppers, crumbling ground beef with a fork.
Combine with chili beans and soup; bring to a boil and pour into an ovenproof dish.
Top with corn chips and cheese.
Bake at 400° for approximately 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chicken glop
directions: Put olive oil in frying pan.
Saute onion, pepper and garlic. Add balance of ingredients and cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, for a couple of hours.
Add pineapple chunks 5 minutes before serving over rice or pasta.

title: empanditas
directions: Put flour, sugar and salt into bowl. Cut in butter and shortening. Mix in egg yolk and sprinkle in water, one tablespoon at a time, mixing until dough forms a ball.
Flour board and knead dough until springy for 2 to 3 minutes.
Divide dough in half and roll each half 1/8 to 1/16-inch thick.
Cut into 2 1/2-inch rounds.

title: spinach
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs, in baking dish. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: harvest cake
directions: Mix together apples and sugar.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat eggs and blend in oil and vanilla. Mix apples and sugar and dry ingredients with egg mixture.
Blend in walnuts, mixing well.
Pour into greased and floured tube cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Frost with plain white icing and top with nuts if desired.

title: pefoff
directions: Brown noodles in margarine.
Add rice, brown with the onion, mushrooms and green pepper.
Season with garlic, salt and pepper. Add chicken broth (small amounts) at a time and steam for one half hour or until done.

title: moo burgers
directions: Mix all together.
Shape into 3/4-inch thick patties and barbecue.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook onion and celery in oleo until tender.
Combine with other ingredients, except 1 cup crumbs.
Put in large baking dish. Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine dry pudding mix, dry milk and water.
Mix well using a wire whisk.
Blend in peanut butter and 1/2 cup Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Refrigerate for at least 15 minutes.
Spread remaining 1/2 Cool Whip over set filling.
Just before serving, drizzle chocolate syrup and caramel over top.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pineapple together.
Add pudding and mix well (just the dry pudding).
Add marshmallows; mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: tomato bake
directions: Heat
oven to 350°.
Place tomatoes in ungreased baking pan, 13
x
9 x 2-inches.
Mix butter, onion and basil.
Spoon about
1 teaspoon butter mixture into each tomato.
Bake until tomatoes are hot,
20 to 25 minutes.
Serve tomatoes on parsley.
Makes 9 servings.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Stir together the rice, soups and water in casserole dish. Dip chicken in melted butter and place on top of rice mixture; add any remaining butter.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until rice is tender.
Add more water if necessary.
Good with fruit salad.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix the cream cheese, sugar, pecans, sour cream and vanilla. Reserve fruit liquid and add enough water to make 1 3/4 cups. Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mix with juice and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set slightly.
Add blueberries and let set until firm.
Spread cream cheese mixture on top and chill.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in a greased pan about 45 minutes at 450°.

title: quick taco bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown ground meat and onion; drain.
Spoon into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish.
Stir in seasoning mix (dry), tomato sauce and corn.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Stir remaining ingredients until blended.
Pour over meat mixture.

title: potato broccoli cheese soup
directions: Coat a large saucepan with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat until hot.
Add onion; saute 5 minutes.
Add potato, milk and broth; bring to a boil.
Partially cover, reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes.
Remove 1 cup potato mixture and set aside.
Place remaining potato mixture in container of an electric blender. Cover and process until smooth.
Return potato puree to pan.
Stir in broccoli, salt and pepper.
Partially cover and cook over medium heat 8 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add reserved potato mixture; cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
Yields 6 cups.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients with only 1/2 cup butter.
Sprinkle cornflakes on top of mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour remaining butter over casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Can be assembled day before.

title: brenda's brownies
directions: Melt over low heat butter and cocoa.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar, then eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add cake flour, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Combine all dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture alternately with coffee and milk (batter will be very thin).
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar at high speed until well mixed. Add beaten egg yolks and mix well.
Sift together the flour, baking soda and cream of tartar; add alternately with the milk to the mixture.
Add vanilla and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Fold into batter.

title: pennsylvania dutch cabbage rolls
directions: Combine meat, salt, pepper, rice and egg; mix well.

title: cheese dreams
directions: Cut muffins.
Spread cut sides with soft butter; cut 6 slices of bacon in half.
Set oven to broil.
Place muffin halves and bacon slices on rack in broiler pan.
Broil with tops of muffins 3 inches from heat until bacon is light brown, about 2 minutes. Remove muffins and turn bacon over.
Broil bacon 1 minute longer. Top each muffin half with 1 thick tomato slice, 2 pieces bacon, 2 thin slices process American cheese.
Return muffins to broiler. Broil about 1 minute or until cheese is melted.
Serve at once.

title: taco sauce
directions: Boil until onions are tender.
Brown hamburger (much as desired).
Season with garlic, chili powder and pepper to taste. Top with shredded sharp cheese, lettuce, tomatoes and sour cream. Serves 10.

title: moist meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Place in pan and cover with can of tomato soup. Cook 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pepparhokor(spice cookies)
directions: Sift together these dry ingredients.
Stir both mixtures together.
Cover and chill for several hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 350° to 375°.
Roll out dough on a floured board, about 1/8-inch thick.
(Roll out a small amount at a time, keeping remaining dough in refrigerator.)
Cut out with floured cutters. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool and decorate.

title: layered salad
directions: Tear lettuce and spinach in bite size chunks.

title: swiss potato soup
directions: Melt margarine or butter in a saucepan.
Add the onion and carrot.
Cook until tender.
Stir in milk, broth, salt, nutmeg and black pepper; bring to a boil.
Stir in potato flakes; cook until slightly thickened, about 1 minute.
Add Swiss cheese and stir until melted.
Makes 4 servings.

title: butternut ball cookies
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cream butter and sugar well. Blend in the vanilla and dry ingredients.
Form balls with hands by enclosing a pecan half in 1 tablespoon dough.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies (no-bake) 2
directions: First, melt butter in a large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Take saucepan off burner and add sugar, cocoa and milk; blend thoroughly.
Put pan back on stove and cook mixture 2 minutes, no longer.
Take pan off heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oats (1 cup at a time).
Stir thoroughly.
Drop mixture by spoonful onto wax paper and let cool.
Makes 1 to 3 dozen, depending on size of drops.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown meat with seasoning and onion; drain and add chillies. In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish spread refried beans; top with the meat mixture.
Cover with cheese, then pour the picante sauce over the top.
Bake for 35 minutes in a 375° oven.
Serve over tortilla chips or just dip chips in individually.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 3 pies.

title: cup "o" dirt
directions: Crush cookies in food processor or in zipper-style plastic bag with rolling pin.
Pour milk into a large bowl; add pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in whipped topping and half of the crushed cookies.
Place 1 tablespoon crushed cookies into each of 8 to 10 (7 ounce) paper or plastic cups.
Fill cups about 3/4 full with pudding mixture.
Top with remaining crushed cookies.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or until ready to serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugar, beaten eggs, oil, vanilla and zucchini.
Combine dry ingredients separately, then mix together with wet ingredients.
Pour into 2 ungreased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, and water.
Bring to a soft boil over medium heat.
Beat egg whites.
Add 12 tablespoons of syrup mixture to beaten eggs.
Bring rest of mixture to a hard boil.
While beating, add rest of syrup mixture.
Beat to desired consistency, adding vanilla while beating.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: frosty fruit loaf(refreshing frozen yogurt and fruit salad)
directions: Drain fruit cocktail, reserving 1/2 cup syrup.
In saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over syrup.
Stir over low heat until dissolved. Beat in real mayonnaise.
Stir in strawberries and corn syrup. Chill until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.
Fold in fruit cocktail and yogurt.
Spoon into 9-inch loaf pan.
Cover; freeze until firm.
Serves 8.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger (drain grease).
Add tomato sauce and tomatoes.
Cook macaroni and drain.
Put in dish.
Start with a layer of hamburger, then macaroni, then cheese.
Continue until all is used up, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: pig pickin cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Beat well 3 minutes in mixer. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° until tests done.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt butter, sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a boil; boil 1 minute.
Take off stove.
Add remaining ingredients; lay out wax paper and drop cookies onto the paper.

title: jello buttermilk salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Stir slowly. Remove pan from heat.
Add Jell-O; stir until dissolved.
Cool until thick.
Add buttermilk.
Stir.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts. Pour into 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into serving pieces.

title: holiday stuffing(heart healthy)
directions: Baking Temperature: 325°.
Baking Time: 30 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; do not overcook.
Cook Minute rice per package directions.
Mix all ingredients together except bread crumbs.
Place in one large or 2 small casserole dishes.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bread crumbs are browned.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all together and pour
into unbaked pie shell.
Cook 350° until firm (approximately 25 to 30 minutes).

title: mahogany cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Mix well.
Mix flour, soda, salt and cocoa.
Add half of buttermilk with flour mix.
Add other buttermilk and flour with cold coffee.
Beat well.
Bake 3 layers in 9-inch pans at 350°.

title: ice cream salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in ice cream until dissolved.
Add nuts, pineapple and cheese and stir until mixed well.
Refrigerate to jell.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Mix together.
Grease casserole (makes 13 x 9 x 1 1/2-inch size pan).
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Freezes very nicely.

title: gnocchi with fontina sauce
directions: Place Fontina cheese, cream, butter and Parmesan in a saucepan over another saucepan of simmering water.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until cheeses melt and sauce is smooth and hot. Meantime, boil gnocchi until cooked.
Drain and coat with a little vegetable or salad oil.
Serve with sauce poured over gnocchi.

title: irish cream
directions: Blend all ingredients on high for 1 minute.
Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place fryer in electric skillet.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and cook at 250° for 2 hours.

title: mother's hot slaw
directions: Put cabbage and onion in a large bowl.
Fry bacon.
Remove bacon to plate.
Use grease from bacon to mix with water, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage and onion.
Mix and add crumbled bacon.
Serve hot.

title: fruit pie(strawberry crumb cake)
directions: Thaw fruit.
Sprinkle cake mix over top of fruit.
Pour cake mix in on top of fruit.
Spread melted margarine over top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: beef 'n mushroom pie
directions: Line deep dish pie pan with pastry; flute edges. Place beef, onion and green pepper in large skillet.
Cook until meat is browned.
Pour off fat.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into a ball.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: clam chowder
directions: Melt margarine in a heavy saucepan.
Add rest of ingredients. Heat slowly until just hot enough to eat (use no salt).

title: chinese chicken soup *
directions: Simmer chicken in water with salt and pepper until tender. Remove from bone.
When cooled, shred chicken with fingers.
Boil onion and ginger root in broth.
Remove ginger root from broth. Add shredded chicken and corn.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: shrimp cornbread dressing
directions: Saute onions, celery and bell pepper in margarine.
Add chopped shrimp.
Cook until shrimp is pink.
Add salt, pepper, parsley and garlic, if desired.
Add cornbread stuffing and prepared cornbread.
Add well beaten eggs in 1 cup water.
Add enough water to mixture until soft.
Mix well; bake at 350° until brown, about 45 minutes.

title: beef tomato casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Brown beef with onion and drain fat. To beef, add soup, pepper, sugar, salt and water and mix.
Stir in noodles.
Stir in cheese.
Put in lightly greased casserole.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a 3-quart casserole.
Cover and microwave at High for 10 to 12 minutes or until boiling.
Add pepper, stirring well.
Pour eggs in a thin stream into soup, stirring constantly.
Cover and let stand 3 minutes.
Remove garlic; sprinkle soup with green onion.
Yields 6 cups.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add other ingredients, except cheese. Simmer until done.
Add cheese and melt.
(I wait and add kidney beans just before cheese.)

title: imogene evans' chicken surprise
directions: Boil chicken and bone; cut up.
Save broth.
Line bottom of oblong dish with the package of bread crumbs from Stove Top stuffing mix.
Cover the crumbs with the chicken.
Take 2 cups of broth and herbs from the package of stuffing mix and cook according to directions.

title: peanut butter corn flake cookies
directions: Bring to a boil sugar and Karo syrup.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir until melted and mix in:
corn flakes, coconut, vanilla and salt.
Mix quickly and drop onto waxed paper while still very warm.
Allow to set until firm.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix. Spread in shallow dish. Spread chili sauce on top. Chill.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix together lemon cake mix, eggs, lemon extract and oil.
Mix together package of lemon Jell-O and 1 cup hot water and add to above mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Mix together powdered sugar and juice of lemons (or ReaLemon).
Put toothpick holes in cake as soon as it comes out of oven.
Put icing on while cake is still warm.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease bottom only of pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches, with shortening. Make cake mix as directed on package, using water, oil and eggs. Pour into pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool completely, about 1 hour. Poke cake every 1/2-inch with handle of wooden spoon. Beat pudding mix and milk in medium bowl with wire whisk about 2 minutes. Pour pudding evenly over cake. Run knife around side of pan to loosen cake. Refrigerate about 2 hours, until chilled. Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: hilda taylor's old fashioned beans
directions: Clean and separate beans carefully.
Soak overnight or at least 5 to 6 hours.
Drain off water.
Cover with clean water and cook slowly for 3 to 4 hours in covered 3-quart pot.
Add bacon or salt pork in last hour.
May add any other spices as you desire or onions, carrots, etc., to change flavor.
Serve with cornbread or cheese biscuits.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and then add olives.
Then chill until firm.
Scrape out of bowl.
Then roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: chinese noodles
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels over hot (not boiling) water.
Stir in noodles and nuts.
(The secret is in melting of butterscotch. They should melt and not cook.
Use hot water and do not let bottom of pan touch water.
As soon as melted, stir in noodles.) Drop by tablespoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: simple salmon bagel
directions: Drain salmon and mash.
Add next 4 ingredients and mix lightly.
Split and toast bagels.
Spread each bagel half with soft cream cheese and top with salmon mixture.
Garnish with dill and thin tomato slices.
Serve open-faced.

title: mini-cheesecakes
directions: Line muffin tin with foil liner.
Place one vanilla wafer in each liner.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Pour over wafers, filling 3/4 full.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: "I mix this with my hands in a big pan."
Roll on a floured board.
Separate and roll out pieces one at a time and sprinkle with sugar, colored with cinnamon and roll on top.
Cut with a big cutter and bake at about 400° on greased cookie sheet.

title: coleslaw 1
directions: Preferably cut cabbage with a knife so that it is not too fine, or grate on a large-hole grater.
Grate carrots fine.
Chop onion very fine.
Fry bacon crisp and crumble.
Save part of bacon grease and mix it with mayonnaise, mustard, lemon juice, salt, pepper and horseradish.
Then mix this with cabbage, carrots, onion and crumbled bacon.
Best if left in refrigerator for at least 4 hours. Remix before serving.

title: lime 'n "v-8"
directions: For garnish, prepare ice cubes by placing twisted lime slices in each cube compartment.
Fill with water and freeze.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Pour over ice cubes in glasses. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: beet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cool slightly and add remainder of ingredients.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning together. Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan and top with cheese, lettuce and tomato.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar.
Mix flour and walnuts in another bowl.
Add margarine and brown sugar mixture.
Mix with a fork to make a crumb mixture, reserving 1 cup for topping.
Press remainder of crumbs into bottom of ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: salmon ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except parsley.
Mix well.
Chill 4 hours.
Shape into balls or logs and roll in parsley.
For an extra special event, shape mixture into fish and stick with slices of cucumber for scale effect.
Yields a five-inch ball.

title: lemon-buttered potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes; drain carefully.
Combine butter and all other ingredients in small pan.
Cook over medium heat until
butter melts.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Serve immediately.

title: clam dip
directions: Melt margarine.
Add onion and cook until soft.
Add spices, clams, lemon and garlic.
Simmer 8 to 10 minutes; don't let all juice evaporate.
Add bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese; mix well. Layer clam mixture in a casserole, alternating layers with Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or 5 minutes on High in a microwave.

title: tuna layered salad
directions: Layer lettuce, shells, cucumbers, tomatoes, tuna, peas and cheese in 3-quart serving bowl.
Spread Miracle Whip over salad. Cover and refrigerate.
Toss to serve.
Serves 8.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Simmer chicken in 2 quarts of water until tender.
Remove from broth and remove bones.
Add vegetables and paste to broth and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Put chicken, diced ham and ham broth into pot.
Add salt, pepper, hot sauce and a little sugar to taste.
Tastes better if it is made a day ahead of time.

title: pecan chewies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, 1/2 cup oleo (melted), salt, pepper, minced onion, chicken soup, sour cream and cheese together.
Spoon into a 2-quart casserole.
In skillet, melt 1/4 cup oleo.
Stir in corn flakes.
Spread on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Enjoy!

title: kraut
directions: Fill a quart fruit jar 1 inch from the top with cabbage.
Add salt and sugar.
Fill jar to half with real hot water.
Put lid on jar but not on tight.
Set jar in pan so when it ferments, it will run into the pan.
Let set for 3 days.
Put enough water in to cover the kraut, ready to eat in 4 days.

title: brown rice
directions: Stir all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon basil grilled chicken
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients in shallow baking dish.
Add chicken, turning once to coat both sides.
Refrigerate for 30 to 45 minutes, turning once.
You may grill or broil.
If broiling, heat broiler and broil chicken 4 inches from heat, turning once, 3 to 5 minutes per side or until cooked through.
If grilling, place chicken 4 inches from heat source, turning once, 3 to 5 minutes per side or until just cooked through.
Serves 4.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Saute onion with oleo.
Mix all ingredients, except tortillas.
Dip tortillas in chicken broth until soft.
Spoon chicken mixture on soft tortillas.
Roll and place close together in a 9 x 13-inch casserole pan.
Pour remaining sauce over the top.
Top with grated Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Boil potatoes, uncovered, in jackets until tender.
Chill thoroughly, 12 hours or more.
Peel and grate.
Add eggs, salt and flour.
Beat with flour until light.

title: easy chocolate torte
directions: Bake a 2 layer chocolate cake.
Split each layer horizontally when completely cool.
Melt 1 1/2 packages of the chocolate in saucepan over very low heat.
Cool.
Then beat in soft butter. Add almonds to chocolate mixture.
Make curls from remaining 1/2 chocolate bar.
Spread one layer of cake with half of chocolate. Top with 2nd layer of cake.
Spread that layer with whipped topping; top with 3rd layer of cake.
Top with chocolate.
Then 4th cake, top with whipped topping.
Top with chocolate curls. Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Cook meat and onion in oil until browned.
Add rest of ingredients, except milk, eggs and corn meal.
Cook 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add milk, beaten eggs and corn meal.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 400° or until looks dry on top.

title: pineapple pork chops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Trim fat from pork chops.
Lightly sprinkle both sides of pork with salt.
Place pork in ungreased square pan or baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Mix 2 tablespoons of the reserved pineapple juice with the brown sugar and nutmeg; spoon remaining mixture over pineapple.
Cover and bake 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake, spooning sauce over pork occasionally, until done, 15 to 20 minutes longer.
Garnish with snipped chives if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant.
Mash eggplant, pepper, onion and egg.
Add stale bread crumbs.
Add bacon fat or margarine.
Add mushroom soup.
Save few crumbs for top.
Mix and bake in buttered dish at 450° until done.

title: civil war fruit cake
directions: Cook together apples, raisins, butter and sugars with vinegar and water.
Cool, add 4 eggs.
In another bowl, mix flour, soda, salt and spices.
Mix well and bake at 375° until toothpick punched in center of cake comes out clean.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together with 1/3 cup tomato sauce. Shape meat loaf like a jelly roll and top with cheese.
Pinch ends and edges together.
Roll it up, using wax paper.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Drain off grease.
Pour rest of tomato sauce over meat loaf and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Mix eggs and milk.
Then add to other ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350°.

title: tex mex bake
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions; set aside. Preheat oven to 350°. Spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with cooking spray. In a medium bowl, combine Success rice, diced tomatoes and ground beef; set aside. Cover baking dish bottom with chips. Layer half of the cheese over the chips. Top with beans and rice-tomato-beef mixture. Top with remaining cheese. Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted. Garnish with sour cream and green onions, if desired. Makes 8 servings. It is also good meatless or with chicken instead of beef.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Combine with remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in buttermilk; quickly stir it into flour mixture.
Knead on board until smooth.
Roll to 1/8-inch thickness; cut with biscuit cutter.
Brush with melted butter; place one on top of another on a greased cookie sheet.
Cover; let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Smooth into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour melted chocolate on top or top with 10x sugar and nuts. Freeze and serve frozen.

title: corn pone
directions: Saute onion in shortening.
Combine the remaining ingredients. Place in a large casserole.
Top with 1/2-inch layer of cornbread batter.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: green salad dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Wonderful as salad dressing or dip.

title: nibble mix
directions: Place butter in a baking dish.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce. Add dry cereals, pretzel sticks and nuts.
Sprinkle with the garlic and onion salts.
Mix well.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat and add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer uncovered until thick (about 1 hour), stirring occasionally.

Cook noodles in boiling salt water until tender, drain, rinse in cold water. Meanwhile combine cottage cheese with the next 5 ingredients. Place half of the noodles in a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish. Spread half of the cheese and half the meat mixture.
Repeat layers.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and let stand about 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: date oatmeal loaf
directions: Add rolled
oats
and
dates to milk.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Add
egg,
beaten slightly, and corn syrup.
Mix and sift
dry ingredients.
Add milk mixture, stirring only enough to blend
well.
Bake	in moderate oven, 350°, in greased loaf pan for 1 hour.

title: carrots and celery
directions: Cut celery and carrots into 1/2-inch pieces.
Simmer until tender-crisp with water, horseradish and salt.
Drain and toss with butter.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Put ingredients into saucepan with 1/2 cup water.
Let it get hot, stirring occasionally to break up ground beef.
When mixture cooks little while, turn to low and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain and set aside. Butter bottom of casserole dish. Lay bread on bottom of dish; crumble sausage over bread. Sprinkle cheese over bread and sausage. Mix eggs and pour over cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: pretzels "atlantic city"
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and pour over pretzels.
Bake in low oven for three hours, stirring every half hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together and put in large casserole (2 1/2 pints).
Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar, salt and vanilla until fluffy.
Beat in flour and stir in chips and nuts.
Refrigerate one hour and roll into walnut size balls.
Cook at 325° until brown.
Let cool for 10 minutes and roll in 10x sugar.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Slice potatoes and wash.
Place in an 8 x 12-inch square dish, layered.
Pour sugar over potatoes.

title: chocolate chip nut cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugars and salt together; beat until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat in vanilla.
Gradually stir in flour and baking soda.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: sangria for fifty
directions: Combine juices and water.
Stir well.
Refrigerate until time of service.
Just before serving, combine juice mixture, club soda and sliced fruit.
Makes 80 (6 ounce) portions.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mash potatoes by hand or in food processor with pineapple juice.
Add egg whites and spices.
Add milk gradually while mixing or blending in food processor.
Pour into 9-inch pie plate or 2-quart casserole coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle with nuts and bake in preheated 350°
