oven for 25 to 35 minutes, depending on the size of the baking dish used.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Mix melons together in large bowl.
Mix Italian dressing and Dijon mustard in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add chicken.
Marinate overnight, turning every so often.
Heat grill to medium and grill chicken, turning as needed until done, approximately 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with fresh melon salad.
Great, quick summer meal.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and shortening.
Add egg yolks.
Beat well.
Sift together flour and soda.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in coconut, vanilla and nuts. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake in three 8-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Use Cream Cheese Icing.

title: chili cheesecake(servings:  about 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine chips and butter; press into bottom of greased spring-form pan (9-inch).
Bake 10 minutes and cool.
In processor, combine cream cheese and Monterey Jack.
With motor running, add eggs one at a time.
Add sour cream.
Turn off processor and add chilies and picante sauce.
Pulse to mix well. Pour into crust.
Place pan on a baking sheet and bake 40 minutes. Garnish with fresh herbs, diced red and yellow peppers or whatever you prefer.
Ground nuts work well, also.
Serve with a good cracker or pita chips.

title: ice cream freezer recipe(hand cranked)
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and flavoring in condensed milk.
Add 2 quarts plus of milk.
Pour	into freezer container.
Add sufficient milk to fill container.	Use salt on ice around ice cream container to freeze it while cranking ice cream.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and Kosher salt in large bowl.
Knead in additional flour until dough is no longer sticky. Roll out dough until 1/4-inch thick.
Then cut into 1/4-inch strips about 10-inches long.
Twist into desired shapes and lay on greased cookie sheet.
Melt butter and spread on pretzels using small brush.
Sprinkle salt on pretzels and place in oven at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fried chicken coating
directions: Combine pancake mix with 1 pack Italian dressing mix.
Combine the other package of salad dressing with the egg and club soda. Dip pieces of chicken into club soda mixture first, then into the pancake mixture.
Brown pieces in oil, then arrange on baking sheet and bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pistachio surprise
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes; let cool. Blend cream cheese and sugar. Add 1 cup Cool Whip and spread on crust. Beat milk and pudding for 2 minutes. Pour over cream cheese layer. Top with rest of Cool Whip and garnish with chopped nuts. (Any pudding can be substituted including sugar-free as well as fat-free cream cheese.) Use fresh strawberries with strawberry pudding.

title: play dough
directions: Mix together in saucepan until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring and scraping pan constantly, until it sticks together in a ball.
The dough will be very stiff and difficult to stir.
Turn out on table and let cool enough to handle.
Knead for 5 minutes. Store in airtight container.
Do not refrigerate.

title: 3 week pancakes(makes 2 quarts)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine the beaten eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Add yeast, then sifted flour and dry ingredients. Beat on low until smooth.
Pour into a pitcher with a lid.
Keeps 3 weeks in the refrigerator.
Stir batter well before using.
Best made into small pancakes.
These are a thin pancake.

title: low-fat zucchini bread
directions: Spray and flour 2 loaf pans.
Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
In another pan, beat eggs; add vanilla, applesauce and sugar.
Add the dry ingredients gradually. Stir in the zucchini, raisins and nuts.
Divide into loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Check with toothpick.

title: mexican dish
directions: Brown together the ground beef and onion; drain fat.
Add soups, water and enchilada sauce.
Layer casserole dish: tortillas, cheese and meat mixture.
Heat in oven until cheese melts.

title: cornflake chews
directions: In a saucepan, bring to boil Karo and sugar.
Take off heat and add peanut butter.
Blend until evenly mixed.
Add cornflakes and stir gently until all coated.
Do not mash flakes.
Spoon out on wax paper by tablespoons.
Let cool.

title: swedish coffee loaves
directions: In a food processor with a metal blade, add the yeast, butter, sugar, cardamom, salt and egg.
Add 3 1/2 cups flour and pulse to crumble the butter and blend the egg.
Add the raisins and water. With the food processor still running, add the cooled milk through the feed tube.
Process to form a ball.
Add more flour, if necessary, and process to form a smooth and elastic dough, approximately 50 seconds.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, dry Jell-O and sour cream together. Add drained oranges and pineapple. Chill overnight and serve.

title: taco soup
directions: In large Dutch oven, brown meat and onion.
Add all remaining ingredients, except for the last two.
Bring to a boil, reduce and simmer for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and serve with chips. Freezes well.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Pour in oil and mix at medium speed until there is no visible trace of oil; mix at least 3 minutes.
Add flour and spices, then add pumpkin.
Mix at slower speed until batter is well blended.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meringue kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff with electric mixer.
Add sugar and mix well.
Egg whites should hold peaks. Fold in nuts with spatula or spoon.
Drop mix by teaspoon on foil lined cookie sheets.
Bake at 275 degrees for 40 mins.
Let cool and peel off foil.
Cookies will keep indefinitely in a tin container.

title: apple delight
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; cook over low heat until thick. Cool.
Dice apples; add to sauce.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts over the top.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion; salt and pepper to taste. Add cream of mushroom soup and sour cream. Serve over cooked egg noodles.

title: chicken salad wraps
directions: Combine chicken, dressing and vegetables in a bowl; cover and chill 1 to 2 hours. Divide chicken among tortillas and sprinkle with cheese. Fold and serve. Makes 8 wraps.

title: fresh peach pie with pecans
directions: Combine peaches, sugar, 3 tablespoons flour and lemon juice in a bowl and mix well.
Combine brown sugar and 1/4 cup flour in another bowl.
Cut in margarine using pastry blender; add pecans and toss to mix.
Sprinkle 1/2 pecan mixture in unbaked pie shell and arrange peach mixture.
Top with remaining pecan mixture. Bake at 400° for about 40 minutes or until peaches are tender. Cool on rack.
Serves 8; 383 calories per serving.

title: hot crab special
directions: In a bowl, mix the first 6 ingredients, then fold in the crabmeat.
Transfer to a 6 x 4 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle the top with the almonds, then bake at 350° until the mixture bubbles. Serve with crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Cook noodles.
Mix together with the ingredients.
Save some cheese and catsup for top.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Combine with vermicelli and add enough salad dressing or mayonnaise to moisten and suit your taste.

title: sweet potato (yam) bake
directions: Drain yams.
Mash well.
Drain pineapple, saving juice.
Add juice, brown sugar and melted butter to yams and beat well.
Stir in pineapple and nuts.

title: mexican surprise
directions: Spread cream cheese in a pizza pan.
Spread taco sauce over cheese and layer with remaining ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: gooey pecan monkey bread
directions: Melt butter in 9-inch round cake pan.
Pinch each biscuit into 4 parts and coat in butter.
In medium saucepan, combine brown sugar, Karo syrup and cinnamon, bring to a boil; remove from heat, add pecans, pour over biscuit/butter mixture.
Bake at 425° for approximately 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn upside down on serving plate.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix the sour cream, lemon juice, salt, paprika, celery salt, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and garlic salt together. Marinate the chicken breast for several hours or overnight. Take out of mixture and roll in the Ritz and regular crackers. Pour the margarine over crackers. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: coffee muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add the walnuts.
In a small saucepan, melt butter with the coffee and brown sugar.
Cool slightly, then add to the flour mixture.
Beat well and stir in the egg.

title: lime pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers
and
soak
in
lime for 24 hours.
Add cold water to cover cucumbers and cover for 2 days.
Rinse and drain. On 3rd day, add remaining ingredients and simmer until hot.
Pour into quart jars and seal.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate before rolling out about 1/4-inch thick. Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sugar-free pineapple carrot cake
directions: Beat oil, sugar substitute and eggs until very light yellow. Add pineapple juice; stir in.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and spices; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: iced honey and brandy mousse
directions: Beat egg yolks, honey, lemon juice, brandy and water together with an electric beater until the mixture is thick and light and has doubled or tripled in volume.
Beat the egg whites until stiff, then fold into egg yolk mixture with the cream.
Pour into a 2 1/2 pint freezer-proof souffle dish.

title: rapidrise yeast rolls
directions: Make like biscuits.
Let rise 45 minutes or longer.
Bake at 375° to 450° until brown.

title: microwave shrimp
directions: Peel shrimp and place in a glass pan (microwave bowl). Squeeze one whole lemon over shrimp.
Shake on garlic salt.
Set 1 stick of butter on top of shrimp.
Heat on High for 2 1/2 minutes. Turn pan or bowl around.
Stir shrimp.
Cook for 2 1/2 more minutes.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine Karo, sugars and vanilla in large (3-quart) saucepan. Bring to rolling boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, cornflakes and peanuts.
Spread mixture evenly and firmly in a buttered 10 1/2 x 15 1/2 pan.
If desired, spread few chocolate chips evenly over candy.
Place in 300° oven until chips soften, about 1 minute.
Spread chips evenly.
Cut into desired sizes.

title: ginger cream(4 to 5 persons)
directions: Dissolve the jelly in sufficient water and a little ginger syrup to make up to 3/4 pint.
Add the evaporated milk and the preserved or crystallized ginger chopped into small pieces when almost set.
Stir slightly in order to distribute the ginger evenly.
Turn into a wetted mould.
Stand in a cool place to set. (WCB)

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix well.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: wyoming whoppers
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter or margarine over low heat. Blend in sugars, beaten egg and peanut butter; mix until smooth. Add oats, baking soda, raisins and chocolate chips.
Dough should be sticky.
If not, add several tablespoons water.
Drop by ice cream scoopfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Split wings at each joint and discard tips; pat dry.
Deep fry at 400° (high) for 12 minutes or until completely cooked and crispy; drain.
Combine red hot cayenne pepper sauce, oleo and Worcestershire sauce.
Toss wings in sauce to coat completely or for equally crispy wings, bake on a rack in a roasting pan at 425° for 1 hour; turn halfway through cooking time.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Wash, hull and chop strawberries.
(You may use 2 cans of frozen strawberries instead; omit sugar if you do.)
If not, combine sugar with fresh strawberries in medium size bowl.
Cover and chill for 3 hours.
Combine freezing mix and milk; stir until freezing mix is dissolved.
Stir in strawberries.
Pour mixture into freezing container of home ice cream maker.
Stir in cream. Follow procedure recommended by manufacturer of ice cream maker for preparing ice cream.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: homemade ice cream(uncooked)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and salt.
Stir in evaporated milk, homogenized milk and vanilla.
Pour into gallon size freezer canister.
Turn.
Your favorite crushed fruit may be added.

title: chicken tacos
directions: Heat chicken, 3/4 teaspoon salt, chilies and onion in oil over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until chicken is hot.
Heat shells as directed on package.
Cut avocado lengthwise into slices; sprinkle with lemon juice and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Spoon about 1/4 cup chicken mixture into each shell.
Top with cheese, lettuce, olives and avocado.
Serve with taco sauce and sour cream.
Yields 10 tacos.

title: corn and black bean salsa
directions: In a small bowl, whisk together lime juice, honey, oil and cumin.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Great with crackers or chips as a dip or over lettuce as a meatless taco salad.

title: cheese squares
directions: Blend cheese, egg and butter until mixed enough to spread. Spread mixture on bread, crust removed.
Cut into 4 sections and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge candy
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight, then cut into squares.

title: creole zucchini
directions: In skillet cook onion, garlic and green pepper in oil until soft.
Add tomatoes, zucchini, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook about 20 minutes.
Serve topped with cheese and parsley.
Serves 8.

title: zucchini italian style
directions: In skillet, cook vegetables and spices in olive oil for 8 minutes over medium heat.
Stir frequently until zucchini is tender.
Remove from heat.
Remove 1 1/2 cups of mixture from skillet and set aside.
Stir cottage cheese into remaining zucchini in skillet.
Spread half of tomato puree in bottom of 2-quart baking dish.
Heap zucchini-cheese mixture in center.
Top with remaining tomato puree and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Sprinkle reserved zucchini mixture around edge of dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: no-fat mashed potatoes(servings:  8)
directions: Cook potatoes just until done.
Remove from heat; drain well and place back on low heat to dry out potatoes before whipping them.
Mash potatoes until smooth.
Mix all ingredients into whipped potatoes.
Place in ovenproof, slightly buttered casserole dish and heat.

title: spread your own snack
directions: Cook franks for 10 minutes, then drain.
Grind and blend with remaining ingredients.
Spread on crackers or bread.

title: mother goose popcorn
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients to soft ball stage.
Mix with the popped popcorn.
Stir until coated.

title: sausage bean soup
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Put in 5 quart pan and add all other ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together the oil, sugar and eggs.
Add zucchini, vanilla, cloves, ginger and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Pour into 2 loaf pans, greased and floured. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: hot creamy crab dip
directions: In a medium-size saucepan, combine the cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise, wine (or cream), onion, mustard, garlic, and hot pepper sauce.
Fold in the crab meat (or salmon) and 1/4 c. parsley.
Warm over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until hot; do not boil.
Spoon into a warm chafing dish (or other serving dish) and sprinkle with the remaining parsley, the almonds, and paprika.
Makes about 4 c.
Serve with crackers.

title: hot wings
directions: Separate wings and bake in 400° oven for 35 minutes.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Mix well and cook over low heat 4 hours.
Put baked wings into a sealable container; pour liquid in and shake until well coated.
Serve.

title: creamed eggs on toast
directions: Hard boil eggs;
peel
and
set aside.	Make toast; set aside. Use a
medium
saucepan;
melt
butter.
Combine flour with a whisk
and	cook
5 minutes until lightly browned.	Add milk and heat
until thickened.
Add salt and pepper to taste. After I feed the
kids,	I
add curry to the sauce for myself. Have each person tear their toast into bite-sized pieces into a pasta bowl or large low soup bowl.
Slice egg(s) and arrange over toast.	Serve piping hot sauce over toast and egg.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Mix dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture with milk.
Rinse blueberries and remove any stems.
Mash 1/2 cup blueberries and stir into batter.
Fold in remaining blueberries.
Divide batter into 18 muffin cups (with paper liners) and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen muffins.

title: baked indian pudding
directions: Scald 1 quart milk; add corn meal and pinch of salt.
Cook over medium heat to boil.
Pour into baking dish.
After 1 hour in oven, stir in 1 cup cold milk, stirring occasionally during baking.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: creamy chicken casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; spoon into a lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Combine crushed crackers and butter and sprinkle over chicken mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: corned beef salad(serves 10 people)
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to directions.
Refrigerate until thick.
Beat until light.
Fold in mayonnaise.
Add corned beef which has been cut in small pieces and all fibers removed.
Add salt, onion, green pepper, chopped celery and eggs.
Let congeal and serve on lettuce (or make sandwiches, if desired).

title: date nut roll
directions: Cook sugar, salt, syrup, margarine and milk until it comes to a boil.
Add cut-up dates.
Stir all time.
Cook to soft ball stage. Remove from heat; cool.
Beat until very stiff and add pecans. Shape 6 to 8 inches long, 1/2-inch in diameter.
Place on wax paper.
Cut in slices when firm.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Make a roux by stirring flour and vegetable oil until a well browned peanut butter color, not burned!
When roux is made, add onions, bell pepper, celery and garlic.
Cook, stirring until vegetables are limp, being careful not to burn.
Add hand squeezed tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir until well blended.
Add water and cook 50 minutes.
Turn fire off.
Let sit until ready to serve.
Just before serving, bring to a light bubble.
If too thick, add more water.
Add shrimp.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add parsley, green onions, oysters and crabmeat.
Cook 5 minutes more.
It is important not to overcook the seafood.
Serve immediately over rice or noodles.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: chocolate angel pie
directions: Combine egg whites, salt and cream of tartar in mixing bowl. Beat until foamy throughout.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating after each addition, until sugar is blended. Continue beating until mixture will stand in very stiff peaks. Fold in nuts and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.

Spoon mixture into lightly greased pie pan and make a nest-like shell, building up sides 1/2-inch above edge of pan. Bake in slow oven at 300° for 50 to 55 minutes. Cool. Place chocolate and water in saucepan over low heat. Stir until chocolate is melted. Cool until thickened.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Whip the cream. Fold chocolate mixture into whipped cream.
Pile into meringue shell. Chill about 2 hours before serving.

title: easy no-bake chocolate cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in large kettle. Bring to a rolling boil and then boil for 1 minute afterwards. Remove from stove; add vanilla and peanut butter and stir until completely blended together. Mix the mixture with rolled oats well together. Dip onto waxed paper with tablespoon; let dry or refrigerate to cool down faster while still on waxed paper. As it cools down, mixture will harden together.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat eggs one at a time. Stir in applesauce and milk; sift dry ingredients.
Add to applesauce mixture.
Mix well; stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into 2 greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch loaf pans; bake at 350° for 1 hour until bread tests done.
Cool on rack.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat egg; add beef, onion, salt, pepper, celery and bell pepper.
Toss it with a fork until blended.
Lightly stir in tomato juice.
Add cracker crumbs.
Place in pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: blackberry rolls
directions: Mix together oleo, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix with a pastry blender until Bisquick-like flour forms.
Add milk and mix for handling.
Roll out on a floured 12 x 15-inch board.

title: brown rice
directions: Lightly brown rice and onions in margarine over medium-high heat.
Add broth and mushrooms. Pour into 1 1/2-quart covered casserole and bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: dolly's salad dressing
directions: Mix Miracle Whip, minced onion, garlic powder, and Tony's seasoning. Add enough Worcestershire sauce to turn in slightly brown; add enough catsup to turn it pink; add enough milk to thin; add enough sugar to take out the whang. Stir well and refrigerate. It will thicken as it sets. Add more milk as necessary.

title: elie's best french muffins
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually until fluffy.
Blend in egg yolk; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture, alternately with milk.
Fold in beaten egg white.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
While hot, dip tops in melted butter, then in mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix butter, sugar and eggs.
Blend flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Stir into bottom mixture.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Mix 2 tablespoons of sugar and 2 tablespoons of cinnamon.
Roll balls in sugar and cinnamon mixture. Place balls on cookie sheet, 2-inches apart.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mrs. winslow's apple pie filling
directions: In large saucepan, blend in first four ingredients with 1 teaspoon
salt.
Stir this into 8 to 10 cups of water.
Cook while stirring
until
thickened and bubbly.
Add lemon juice and coloring.
Pack
apples
in
hot
jars;
leave
inch headspace.	Fill
with syrup to within 1/2-inch space.
Adjust lids.
Process
in	boiling water for 15 minutes (pints) or 20 minutes (quarts).
Yields approximately 7 quarts.

title: raisin bars
directions: Boil the first 7 ingredients 5 minutes.
Cool well (important).
Add flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix and spread on greased and floured 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.
Cool.
Drizzle with 4x sugar and water mixture.

title: chicken hawaiian
directions: Coat chicken with mixture of flour, nutmeg and ginger.
Brown well in oil on top of stove.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, covered with sauce made with pineapple juice, soy sauce, sugar and garlic.
Add sliced pineapple the last 15 minutes in oven.
Yields 8 servings.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Separate broccoli and cauliflower into small flowerets (can use all of one or the other).
Put in large bowl with Provolone. Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, sugar and Parmesan.
Pour over salad and mix.

title: 5 minute blueberry pie
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and water. Cook on high 2 minutes or until mixture boils.
Boil one minute. Mixture should be thick.
Stir, add blueberries, cook on high for three minutes, stirring often.
Pour into crust; top with whipped cream and a dash of cinnamon.

title: ossobuco
directions: Chop the celery, carrot, onion and anchovy fillets.
Melt butter in heavy pan.
Flour veal shanks and brown both sides.
Add wine and reduce.
Add chopped celery, onion, carrot and anchovy. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until golden and add tomatoes. Cover, lower heat and cook for about 1 1/2 hours or until tender (add stock when necessary).
A few minutes before cooked, add the chopped garlic, parsley and lemon to taste.
Transfer to serving platter.
Serve with rice, mashed potatoes or polenta.

title: gary's potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets in water with a bay leaf.
Cool, peel and shred in bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add to potatoes.
Bake in greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and 1/2 cup crushed corn flakes.
Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: caramel chess pie
directions: Cream sugars with eggs.
Add meal and flour.
Stir in butter, milk, vinegar and vanilla.
Pour into uncooked pie crust and bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: poor man's pecan pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; beat until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in pie shell in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Pie will have golden brown top when done.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine all ingredients with enough dressing to make moist. Chill overnight and add more dressing if needed before serving.

title: mandel bread
directions: Mix liquids with electric mixer:
eggs, sugar, oil and extracts.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Add flour and baking powder.
Mix well.
Put in refrigerator for a few hours.

title: mincemeat pie
directions: Double the apples, improves the pies.
Some folks prefer other wines.

title: italian egg soup(zuppa pavese)
directions: Generously butter one side of the 4 slices French bread; place, buttered side up, on a cookie sheet.
Toast in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden and crusty.
Sprinkle each slice with 1 tablespoon freshly grated Parmesan cheese and broil until cheese is bubbly.

title: sugar cream squares
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and eggs.
Spread in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan (tin).
Mix to a smooth batter in a mixer. Cream cheese, powdered sugar and eggs.
Spread over the first layer.
Sprinkle generously with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Center will remain soft.
Cut into squares when cool.
Outside edges will seem crusty, so trim 1/4 inch all around pan and then cut into squares.
Crusty part makes yummy samples and my children always knew when to be there.

title: springtime pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain and rinse with cold water.
Place in a large bowl.
Add zucchini, olives, red pepper and onion.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over salad and toss to coat.
Cover and chill 2 hours before serving. Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: grandma beach's sweet pickled peaches
directions: Tie spices in cloth bag.
Blanch peaches one minute in boiling water.
Plunge into cold water to cool, then peel.
Freestone peaches can be pickled whole or split to remove seed.
Make syrup by boiling 2 cups sugar, water and vinegar for 3 minutes.
If peaches are halved, boil 1 minute.
Add remainder; cook until tender, not mushy.
Cover and let stand for a day.
Drain off syrup and reheat.
Pack in hot, sterile jars.
Cover with syrup. Process pints 15 minutes below boiling.

title: carol's cheesecake
directions: In mixing bowl cream butter and sugar.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, cornstarch, vanilla and lemon juice.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time beating well after each addition. Wrap bottom and sides of a 10 inch spring form pan. (I use a disposable aluminum-roasting pan.)
Bake 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Turn off oven and let stand in closed oven for 1 hour.
Cool in pan at least 3 hours. Chill for 4 - 6 hours or overnight before serving.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain these ingredients and mix with:

title: chicken breasts and wild rice
directions: Prepare rice according to package.
Season breasts with salt and pepper; brown chicken slowly in butter.
Arrange breasts on cooked rice.
Saute celery in drippings.
Add soup to drippings. Slowly add wine, stirring until smooth.
Heat to a boil.
Pour over chicken.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350° with cover on and vent open.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Follow directions on can to make 2 pies, except use only 1/2 milk called for. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with yellow cake mix (may not need all of it) and chopped nuts. Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: mother-in-law's good pierogi
directions: Mix flour, Crisco, salt and eggs well.
Add small amount of water, less than 1/2 cup, to make a stiff dough.
Knead 5 to 10 minutes on unfloured surface.
Cover with a bowl.

title: baked broccoli and cheese
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Spread in baking dish; sprinkle with cheese.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over all and bake in preheated oven at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: squash pickles
directions: Slice thinly the squash and onions.
Mix salt with enough water to cover squash.
Let set for 1 hour; drain.
Mix vinegar, sugar, celery seed, turmeric and pepper; bring to a boil.
Pour over squash and place lids on jars.
Process 5 minutes in hot water bath.
Makes approximately 6 pints.

title: peach praline pie
directions: Combine sugar and 3 tablespoons flour.
Add peaches and lemon juice.
Combine brown sugar, 1/4 cup flour and pecans in a small bowl.
Mix in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle 1/3 of pecan mixture over bottom of pie shell.
Cover with peach mixture and sprinkle rest of pecan mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift together first 8 ingredients.
Cream together shortening, sugar and molasses.
Add egg yolk and mix well.
Stir in flour mixture; mix well.
Roll out dough 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with gingerbread man cookie cutter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 350° oven, 8 to 10 minutes.

title: spicy barbecue chicken
directions: Combine seasonings; mix well.
Rub seasoning mixture onto both sides of chicken.
Place chicken, skin side down, on greased grill (low coals).
Grill uncovered 45 minutes or until tender; brushing frequently with barbecue sauce during last 30 minutes, turning occasionally.

title: beef brisket(fresh)
directions: Night before, pour liquid smoke over meat.
Sprinkle salts. Cover with foil; refrigerate.
Don't let foil touch meat.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix oleo,
flour and walnuts;
pat into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake	in
a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Let cool. Mix softened cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip; place on top of crust.
Mix pudding with milk.
Put on top of cream cheese mixture.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Mix the water, yeast and sugar in a large mixing bowl and let stand for 1 hour.
Then mix in flour.
Knead mixture for about 10 minutes.
Preheat oven for 5 minutes to warm it, then turn off heat.
Place mixture in a greased bowl.
Cover it and place in the warmed oven for about 1 hour until the mixture doubles.
When it has doubled, make twists.
Place twists on a greased baking sheet not too close together.
Dilute 1 egg yolk with 1 to 2 teaspoons water or milk.
Run a thin coat of liquid around outside of each pretzel.
Sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake in a preheated oven at 475° for 12 to 15 minutes until they are golden brown.
Yields about 2 dozen.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Stew chicken.
Cook spaghetti in broth.
Drain but save the broth.
Mix chicken, spaghetti, soup and remaining ingredients together.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Top with grated cheese. Bake 20 minutes at 400° in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add some of the broth to make real moist.

title: candied pecans
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans.
Simmer in skillet for 4-5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add pecans, stirring until all nuts are covered with syrup.
Pour onto a platter and separate quickly.

title: tuna patties
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pinch
mixture
into
1/2-inch balls; pat them flat.
Fry in skillet in 1 tablespoon shortening or oil. Brown on both sides.

title: hillbilly casserole
directions: Boil macaroni.
Drain.
Brown ground beef in a skillet.
Drain corn, then mix in other ingredients.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Add butter on top.
Bake in large baking dish at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: low calorie snack dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Will keep until expiration date on cottage cheese.
Dip is especially good with cucumbers, celery, cauliflower and carrots.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix together the potatoes, butter, soup, cheese, sour cream, seasoned salt and onion.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine melted butter with cornflakes; sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 75 to 90 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: crock-pot franks
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Cook on high for one hour, low for 2 hours.

title: bacon & cheddar dip
directions: Mix a 1 oz. packet of Original Ranch Party Dip with 1 pint sour cream.
Add 1/4 c. bacon bits and 1 c. finely shredded cheddar cheese.
Mix well and serve with chips.

title: coca-cola pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Drain off grease.
Place in oblong baking dish.
Mix together ingredients.
Pour evenly over pork chops. Cook on low heat for about 1 hour.
May also cook on top of stove, simmering for 1 hour.

title: polenta (ground beef)
directions: Mix 1 cup cold water, the cornmeal and 1 teaspoon salt in a bowl.
Bring 2 1/2 cups water to a boil in heavy saucepan.
Stir in cornmeal mixture and bring again to a boil, stirring until thickened.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes.
Pour into lightly oiled 8-inch square pan and chill several hours, overnight or until firm.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Melt butter in a large roasting pan.
Add seasonings and mix well.
Add the cereal, nuts and pretzels.
Mix gently until well coated with seasoned butter.
Bake in a 250° oven for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: san francisco stir-fry
directions: Brown meat in large skillet; season to taste.
Combine jelly, cornstarch and mustard; add to meat.
Add vegetables.
Cover and simmer for 5 to 7 minutes, stirring frequently.
Makes 4 servings.
tags: Green Giant San Francisco style frozen vegetables

title: black bean and beef barbecue bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown the ground beef and onions.
Drain off fat.
Add beans (undrained), barbecue sauce, salt and cheese. Stir and simmer together 5 minutes.
Pour into casserole or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour cornbread batter on top.
Bake 20 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Blend confectioners sugar, oleo and egg and spread on cooled crust.
Layer with bananas, crushed pineapple and Cool Whip.
Top with chocolate syrup and nuts.

title: candied pecans
directions: Whip egg whites till frothy.
Then mix cold water and pecans until covered.
Mix together cinnamon and sugar, and then add to mixture and coat thoroughly.
Then spread on cookie sheet and bake at 225 degrees for 30-45 minutes.
Cool on wax pepper.

title: scallop appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate scallops for several hours in refrigerator in mixture.
Broil 5 to 6 minutes.
Turn once after 3 minutes.
Watch carefully.

title: reindeer treats
directions: Mix well.
Serve in a bowl for snacking.

title: crab spread
directions: Mix lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and softened cream cheese together.
Spread on round plate. Spread with cocktail sauce. Top with flaked crabmeat. Chill. Serve with crackers.

title: pancakes - low cholesterol
directions: Mix all together.
Cook on hot griddle.
Has 55 calories per pancake.
Makes 10 pancakes.

title: cheese marbles
directions: Mix all ingredients into a soft dough with hands.
Roll dough about the size of a marble and press crisscross with a fork.
Bake at about 400°.
Do not brown.

title: 10 minute oatmeal cookies
directions: Put the milk, butter, cocoa and sugar in pot.
Bring to a boil and let boil 3 minutes (no longer).
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter until creamy.
Add in oatmeal and drop on cookie sheet.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Pull off the bone.
Mix soup and water; put into casserole bowl.
Add chicken on top of that, then fix Stove Top stuffing on top of chicken.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy in a large mixing bowl. Stir in egg yolks, vanilla and salt, beating well. Gradually stir in flour; mix well. Shape dough into 3/4-inch diameter balls. Dip in slightly beaten egg whites and then roll in pecans. Place 12 balls on high temperature plastic baking sheet lined with waxed paper. Make thumbprint in each. Cook a dozen in microwave oven on Full power for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, or until firm but slightly moist. Allow cookies to cool slightly before removing from waxed paper. Fill "thumbprints" with preserves just before serving. Repeat with remaining cookie dough.

title: barbecue pockets
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Add onions and brown sugar and cook about 2 minutes. Add barbecue sauce and heat through. Remove from heat and set aside. Open biscuits and flatten with your hand. Spray muffin pan and place 1 biscuit per cup. Press gently to form cup. Add meat mixture and bake at 350° to 400° until biscuits are done. Remove and add cheese to top of each pocket. Return to oven on broil until cheese is melted. Use a knife to remove from pan.

title: sparerib sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil for 3 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 stick of margarine in a casserole dish.
Drain corn and add to margarine.
Mix sour cream, onion, cheese and soup. Pour mixture over corn.
Crush crackers, add to one stick of melted margarine and place crackers on top of corn mixture.
Bake 25 or 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Cream light brown sugar and butter together.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Mix flour, soda and salt together; add to creamed mixture a little at a time.
Add pecans and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine and pour over baked crust.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cooled.

title: holiday fruit dips
directions: Microwave:
In small bowl, melt chocolate on High for 2 minutes.
Stir after 1 minute.
Stir until chocolate is smooth. Dip fruit half-way in chocolate and then dip in chopped nuts.
Set on wax paper-lined baking sheet.
Let set or chill until firm, about 15 minutes.

title: trifle
directions: Cut cake in 1-inch squares.
Put layer in large serving dish (looks best in see through glass bowl).
Mix pudding with 12 ounces of
Cool Whip and place layer over cake.
Then put layer of chocolate chips.
Then another layer of cake, pudding and chocolate chips.
Place 8 ounces of Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with chocolate chips.

title: japanese cabbage salad
directions: Mix cabbage and onions together in a bowl.
Set aside.
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper well.
Chop up chicken into chunks and add to cabbage mixture. I have found that the salad has better flavor if you barbecue the chicken.
Add crushed noodles, sesame seed and almonds.
Serve.

title: chicken-broccoli-cauliflower casserole
directions: Slightly cook noodles.
Combine all ingredients.
The broccoli and cauliflower (10 ounces each) should be slightly thawed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tart cranberry relish
directions: Combine all ingredients except red wine vinegar in large non-aluminum saucepan.
Bring to a simmer, stirring to mix well. Cover; reduce heat and cook until cranberries burst and mixture thickens slightly, about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vinegar.
Cool.
Cover and refrigerate at least overnight and up to 1 week.
Remove from refrigerator 20 minutes before serving.

title: chris' taco dip
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer refried beans, ground beef, taco seasoning, sour cream, avocado dip, tomato and onion.
Place in 350° oven and bake for 30 minutes, then remove.
Grate desired amount of cheese over top.
Return to oven and heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with your choice of chips!

title: honey-mustard dressing
directions: Combine sour cream, mustard and honey.
Beat well, as much as five minutes, to make it fluffy.
Add orange peel and salt.
Beat in fruit juices slowly.
Chill at least one hour.
Especially good for fruit combination salads.
Makes about 3/4 cup.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In medium bowl, beat cheese until light and fluffy. Add milk; blend thoroughly. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into crust. Chill until firm (about 3 hours). Top with desired amount of pie filling and serve.

title: granny's buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Cream butter with sugar; add eggs and buttermilk.
Beat well. Add vanilla and coconut.
Bake in uncooked pie shell for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: prune cake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except nuts and prunes.
Mix well. Stir in prunes and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes if using a tube pan or for 45 minutes if using sheet cake pan.

title: s'mores
directions: Place one graham cracker on a paper towel.
Top with chocolate squares and small marshmallows.
Microwave, uncovered, at High for 15 seconds.
Top with second graham cracker.
Let it stand one minute before serving.

title: apple strudel
directions: Thaw pastry 20 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°.
On a lightly floured surface, roll pastry to a 12 x 15-inch rectangle.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Arrange apples down the center. Sprinkle with raisins and cinnamon-sugar.
Brush edges of pastry with egg wash.
Roll up pastry, jelly roll style, with seam side down.
Turn ends under and brush with egg wash.
Make diagonal slits across top at 2-inch intervals.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes. Serves 6.

title: vegetable filled pancake
directions: For pancake: Mix flour, milk, salt and eggs. Beat until well blended.
In 450° oven preheat 10-inch casserole or ovenproof skillet for 5 minutes.
Add oil to hot pan and tilt to coat bottom and sides.
Pour batter into pan and bake 10 minutes at 450°. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 10 minutes.

title: angel food cake
directions: Resift flour 3 times.
Add salt to egg whites and whip until foamy.
Add cream of tartar; whip until stiff and will hold peak. Fold in sugar, one tablespoon at a time; add flavoring.
Fold in flour, 2 tablespoons at a time.
Bake in 9-inch tube pan for 3/4 to 1 hour.
Turn cake over, permitting cooling before removing from pan.

title: blackberry pudding
directions: Cream 1 cup sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Mix well and spoon batter into a greased 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle blackberries and 1 cup sugar over batter; add boiling water. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Serve warm; top with ice cream or whipped cream. Serves 6.

title: grandma's irish bread
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Put eggs in middle of flour with a little milk.
Add raisins.
Knead.
Add milk, bit by bit.
Knead 5 minutes.
You may not use all of milk.
To prevent dough from sticking to hands, use oil.
Make a loaf and put in heavy greased pan and bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.
After done, put butter over it.

title: congo squares
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add brown sugar to oil and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add dry ingredients, then add nuts, chocolate chips and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into squares.

title: sherry's hot slaw
directions: In a saucepan, combine the vinegar and sugar. Cook over medium heat until sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat and refrigerate until chilled.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: In crock-pot or fondue pot, melt all ingredients slowly.
Stir often.
When completely melted, serve with chips as a dip.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine sugar, oil and vinegar in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Combine vegetables; pour hot vinegar mixture over them.
Refrigerate overnight.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine the sugars, milk and marshmallow. Bring to a boil over med. heat, stirring until the sugars are dissolved and the marshmallows are melted.

title: weight watcher's spaghetti with savory sauce
directions: Coat a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add turkey and onion; cook over medium heat until turkey is lightly browned, stirring to crumble. Drain and pat dry with paper towels.
Wipe drippings from skillet with a paper towel.
Add turkey mixture, water and next 4 ingredients to skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until thickened, stirring occasionally.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift together cocoa, salt, baking powder and flour.
Add dry mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and blend well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool in pan for 25 minutes before removing.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and oil well.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Fold (don't beat) in nuts and apples.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 40 to 45 minutes in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Put powdered sugar on top after baked.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: If you want to cook a small pudding, one pint of each is all that is needed and 1/2 teaspoon soda instead of 1 teaspoon.

title: chicago chili
directions: Saute onion over moderate heat until soft but not golden. Add meat and brown; break into small pieces. Drain off any fat in a colander. Add remaining ingredients to meat mixture. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 1 1/4 hours, stirring occasionally. Serve hot, using 1 cup per serving.

title: california vegetable quiche
directions: Grate squash coarsely into bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand 10 minutes.
Squeeze out all liquid.
Preheat oven to 350°. In a large mixing bowl, combine squash, eggs, cheese and seasonings.
Pour into 8-inch square baking dish and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until set.
Knife inserted at outer edge comes out clean.

title: fruit ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and juice until softened.
Add remaining ingredients and shape into a ball.
Refrigerate until firm. Serve with vanilla wafers.

title: black forest
directions: Bake cake in two layers.
Mix 1/2 box powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Drain cherries and chop.
Mix in Cool Whip mixture.
This goes between two cake layers.
Use chocolate frosting for outside. Put pie filling on top.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Combine egg, buttermilk and oil; slowly stir into dry ingredients.
Then bake.

title: coca-cola chicken
directions: Place chicken in large frying pan or electric cooker. Add salt and pepper. Mix ketchup, Coca-Cola and Worcestershire sauce together and pour over chicken. Simmer for 1 hour, turning once during cooking time. Serve with rice.

title: coconut pie
directions: Bake ingredients in pie plate, at 350 degrees for one hour.

title: old fashioned gingersnaps
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy, then add molasses and beaten egg.
Add dry ingredients gradually, mixing well.
Form dough into small balls. Roll in additional sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 8 dozen.

title: thick shake
directions: Combine ingredients in blender.
Process until smooth.

title: cheese pate
directions: Mix all together.
Spread on a plate or tray 1/2-inch thick. Refrigerate.
Chop 1/2 cup chutney and spread on top before serving.
Serve with favorite crackers.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix ingredients together very well.
Homogenize in a blender. Use two level teaspoons per cup.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Let oats and water stand for 20 minutes.
Combine oleo, sugars and eggs.
Beat well and add dry ingredients. Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crescent chicken rolls(club member: keisha hudson)
directions: Mix soup, cheese, milk and salt. Pour half into square baking dish. Separate rolls and place cut up chicken in rolls. Roll up, tucking in edges. Place in mixture and pour other half of sauce over rolls. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Cook all of the ingredients on top of stove for approximately 10 minutes.
It will thicken. You can add more apple juice if it gets too thick.
Excellent with baked ham.
Any leftovers can be frozen for future use.

title: curried mushrooms
directions: Saute the mushrooms and onion in the butter or margarine for about 5 minutes.
Add the garlic and curry powder and cook 2 minutes longer or until curry is darkened.
Stir in the beef broth. Simmer over low heat for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: caramel dip for apples
directions: Melt all ingredients together in top of double boiler or on low heat in microwave until chips are melted.
Serve with apple slices.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water slightly.
Add pecans and mix to moisten.
Mix next 5 ingredients.
Pour over nuts and stir.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes on greased cookie sheet.
Stir once.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients as listed.
Chill well before serving.

title: date pecan balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and mix.
Blend in pecans and dates.
Roll teaspoonful of dough into balls.
Refrigerate balls for 1 to 2 hours.
Bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and roll balls in powdered sugar. Sprinkle again with powdered sugar after cookies have cooled.

title: hayes star brand pinto bean pie
directions: Mash beans
well (use juice).
Beat eggs, add all other ingredients; mix
well.
Pour into 3 unbaked pie shells.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 300°.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, remove from fat and drain.
Chop garlic, saute in hot bacon fat, add cabbage and onions.
Cook until about half done (do not overcook), add pimento, chicken broth and white wine, simmer covered until done.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon and caraway seed.
It is better to use a large pot for this.

title: mushroom chicken
directions: Brown chicken breasts in oil.
Remove meat.
Add 1 tablespoon oil to skillet and brown mushrooms until liquid is gone.
Add tomato soup, water and red wine.
Return chicken to skillet and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: sloppy chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bag.
Shake chicken to coat all pieces.
Arrange in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Turn pieces and bake another 20 minutes.
Blend soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons Parmesan and paprika.
Bake another
20 minutes at 400°.
Remove chicken to warm platter.
Stir sauce in pan.
Add some water, if necessary to make gravy consistency.
Pour over chicken or use as gravy over noodles, rice or mashed potatoes.

title: crab meat casserole appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour.
Serve with party rye.

title: kolaches
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
In a medium-size mixing bowl, combine the flour, sugar, salt and lemon rind.
Add margarine and mix with hand until well blended.
In small bowl, beat the egg yolks with a fork; add cream or milk and yeast and stir well.
Add to flour mixture and stir until well blended with fork or spoon. Cover well and store in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to shape rolls, pat the dough out on a floured surface and roll out to 1/4 inch thickness.
Cut with a 2 inch cutter and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Cover with a light cloth and let rise for 1 hour.
Make a depression in the center of each roll and place a bit of filling on each one.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes or until light brown.
Frost while still warm.

title: cobbler sauce
directions: Cook until thick.
Very good to pour over cobbler.

title: cindy's famous oxtail soup
directions: Cook oxtail in crock-pot with 8 cups water; cook for 6 to 8 hours on high or until oxtail falls off bone.
Strain oxtail and debone it carefully, saving broth.
Once deboned, place meat back in broth.
Add tomatoes, garlic salt, black pepper, beef base, salt and catsup; reduce to low.

title: jalapeno rice
directions: Mix and bake in a greased casserole for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken mozzarella
directions: Preheat frypan to medium-high.
Add butter and olive oil. When heated, add chicken, bone side down, turning 2 or 3 times until done, 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove chicken; set aside.
Add tomatoes, onion and bell pepper with salt and pepper to taste, to frypan.
Reduce heat; stir-fry vegetables until done.
Place chicken on top of vegetables.
Cover chicken breasts with mushrooms until cheese is melted.
Serve with French bread.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Brown chops and arrange in baking pan.
Sprinkle them with salt and pepper.
Combine soup, water and thyme.
Heat, then add parsley, sour cream and half of the onions.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour sauce over chops.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until tender.
Remove cover; sprinkle remaining onions over the top and bake 5 minutes more.
Serve with baked potato and tossed salad.

title: foolproof chocolate fudge
directions: Put everything in a saucepan on low heat and stir in nuts. Pour into a 9 x 9-inch lined pan.
Chill about 2 hours.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Whip Dream Whip with 1 cup milk until stiff.
Add confectioners sugar.
Add softened cream cheese and vanilla.
Slice cake in thin layers.
Cover bottom of dish with layers of cake.
Pour part of mixture over cake.
Add second layer of cake and place remaining mixture over that.
Add cherry pie filling in spots over top. Chill before serving.
Delicious.

title: baked vidalia onions
directions: Peel onions and slice in 2 or 3 thick slices (at least 3/4 inch thick).
Place slices in buttered baking dish flat side up. Cover each slice with at least 1 heaping tablespoon of beef bouillon granules.
Top with a pat of butter.
(Be sure you put a heavy coating of granules on the slice.
This gives the wonderful flavor.)
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: open fire dessert
directions: Drain peaches.
Add water, lemon juice and sugar.
Pour into large skillet.
Place biscuits over peaches.
Brush with melted margarine.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon to taste. Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.
Serve with cream.

title: candied yams
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until soft.
Peel and cut in half.
Place in shallow pan.
Bring syrup, sugar and butter/margarine to a boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: herbed baby potatoes(low-fat - low cholesterol)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 2-quart casserole, toss potatoes in oil to coat each piece.
Add remaining ingredients, except parsley.
Toss to coat evenly.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned.
Garnish with parsley.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in large baking dish.
In saucepan, boil onion and water for 3 minutes.
Add milk and sliced or grated cheese; simmer until cheese is melted.
Add Ro-Tel and soups; heat until boiling.
Place Doritos over chicken; pour sauce over top.
Be sure sauce covers all.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: green onion dressing
directions: Beat real good in blender.
Gradually add 1 cup oil and beat real good.
Very good taste!

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars; add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Add flour, salt and soda.
Mix well; add chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: cheese fudge
directions: Mix cheese and oleo then add the remainder of the ingredients. Pour mixture onto buttered cookie sheet.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg and put in 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix 3 eggs, powdered sugar and cream cheese and put on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in pizza sauce, undrained mushrooms, oregano, garlic salt, onion and pepperoni.
Bring to boil; remove from heat.
Combine macaroni with milk.
Place in a 2-quart casserole.
Layer the ground beef, sauce, 1/2 of macaroni and 1/2 of cheese; repeat layers.
Cover; bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Enjoy!!

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Mix thoroughly and make into loaf.
Add dash of Worcestershire sauce.
Spread mustard and catsup on top.
Roll in foil paper tightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Drain and bake open 15 minutes to brown top.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Beat all ingredients except the eggs and chocolate chips and mix 2 minutes.
Add 4 eggs all at one time.
Mix another minute.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs, vanilla, salt and peanut butter. Add flour and baking powder and spread in small greased cookie sheet.
Bake until slightly brown.
Cut into bars.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first five ingredients and pour into a large casserole. Coat the crumbs with margarine and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: amaretto custard pie
directions: Prepare according to instructions and spread over the first layer of filling.
Allow to set.
Top with whipped topping and garnish with slivered almonds before serving.

title: flank steak marinade
directions: Trim fat from flank steak and poke it with a fork on both sides.
Place in container to marinate overnight.
Combine ingredients and pour over meat.
Turn the meat occasionally. Broil flank steak until cooked to desired doneness.
Heat marinade separately and serve as a gravy topping over the meat.

title: date balls
directions: Mix together the first four ingredients in a saucepan and cook over low flame 15 minutes.
Add Rice Krispies, vanilla and chopped walnuts.
Remove from heat; cool 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sticky buns for a crowd
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, milk and pudding together.
Set aside. Slice each loaf of bread into 12 slices.
Break each slice into 2 or 3 pieces and place in a greased 10 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/2 sugar mix over this.
Repeat with other loaf of bread.
Pour remaining sugar mix over all.

title: almond joy pie
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients well.
Fold in coconut; pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until firm. Makes 2 pies.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine egg, milk, ketchup, onion, salt and pepper.
Add dry crumbs and let soak a few minutes.
Add sausage and beef; mix lightly.
Shape into 2 loaves on a shallow baking pan.
Ketchup can be spread on top, if desired.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.
Can be frozen satisfactorily.

title: molded waldorf salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water and lemon juice; chill until thickened.
Stir in apple, celery, raisins and nuts.
Pour into a 2 1/2 or 3-cup mold.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Unmold.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine stuffing and butter.
Put half in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add chicken on top.
In separate bowl combine cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and 2 cups of broth.
Put this mixture over top of chicken and sprinkle remainder of stuffing on top.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lye soap
directions: Mix water and grease; let boil.
Pour lye into mixture; boil. Add 3 gallons water.
Cook until thick.
Pour into mold.

title: autumn spotlights
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine first five ingredients.
Fold in candy.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes until golden.

title: italian biskets
directions: May leave out anise seed or for more anise taste, add anise extract.

title: apples and dip
directions: Cut apples and soak in salt water for 30 minutes.
Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Whip cream cheese and marshmallow cream together until creamy.
Keep cool until ready to serve.

title: filled cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and salt; add beaten egg and vanilla.
Beat together good.
Add your flour sifted with baking powder and soda. Beat together well; then take small amount on floured board and pat it out.
(I do not roll mine.)
Cut with a cookie cutter.
I use a juice glass.
Put a teaspoon of filling on bottom cookie; cover with top cookie.
Make a slit in top and sugar each cookie with a little sugar.
I use raisin filling or Solo brand apricot, raspberry or any other.

title: waffle cookies
directions: Mix altogether and make in a waffle maker.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and sugar.
Stir in cranberry sauce, pineapple, pecans and Cool Whip.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Serve slightly frozen.

title: nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter an 8-inch cake pan and dust with flour.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Mix and pour over spareribs.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours or on medium heat all day in crock-pot.

title: spanish rice(delicious)
directions: Brown ground beef in butter.
Add onions, green pepper and celery and simmer on range top until almost tender.
Pour into ovenproof casserole (4 quarts or larger).
Mix in tomatoes, salt, pepper and rice.
Blend well.
Garnish top with chopped parsley. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add Vernors slowly.
Add rest of ingredients.
Let set a while, then stir.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Cut up wings. Set aside. (Throw tips away.)
Combine red hot sauce, vinegar and margarine.
Dip chicken pieces in sauce and arrange on flat baking tray. Sprinkle with Hidden Valley Ranch (dry).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tuna casserole
directions: In casserole dish, blend soup and milk.
Stir in tuna, eggs and peas.
Bake at 400° or until hot; stir.
Top with cheese; bake until cheese melts.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine brown sugar, corn syrup, eggs, vanilla extract and cinnamon; beat well.
Stir in Nestle Toll House semi-sweet chocolate morsels, nuts, oats, raisins and orange rind.
Pour into prepared pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm.
Garnish as desired. Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: tomato pie
directions: Layer bread crumbs (in bottom of buttered 9-inch pie plate; save 1/2 of bread crumbs for top), tomatoes, onions and cheese. Repeat.
Pour beaten eggs over top and remainder of bread crumbs and top with bacon.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Good summertime recipe.

title: rice o verde
directions: In large saucepan, bring broth and water to boil.
Add rice and salt; when boiling reduce to low.
Cover and cook 10 minutes; add spinach and dill pushing spinach down into rice.
Cover and cook 10 to 15 minutes longer until rice is tender and water absorbed.
Remove from heat and let stand 3 to 5 minutes.
Before serving, stir spinach and cheese into rice.
Makes about 4 1/2 cups.
Good as a starch and vegetable.

title: festive pumpkin pie
directions: Put first 5 ingredients together in double boiler.
Stir in remaining ingredients in boiler and mix well.
Cook over boiling water, stirring, until gelatine dissolves and mixture is heated (10 minutes).
Remove from heat; chill until mixture mounds when dropped from spoon.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat 1/4 cup sugar.
Fold in pumpkin mixture; put in baked shell.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour and seasonings and pound thoroughly in meat.
Heat drippings and brown meat on both sides.
Add onion, green pepper, boiling water and tomatoes.
Cover and cook slowly over very low flame for 2 hours.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Put apples in a large bowl; add beaten eggs to apples (the eggs keep the apples from turning dark).
Add oil and sugar; mix well. Add dry ingredients, nuts and raisins next to last; last add vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Makes 12 servings.

title: breakfast burrito
directions: Brown sausage and onion in a skillet.
Drain.
Add potatoes and eggs; scramble all together.
Place generous amounts of cooked mixture in a steamed tortilla.
Use picante sauce, if desired.

title: western omelette
directions: Drain and mash tofu with a fork.
Saute onions and bell pepper in a little water.
Add tofu and seasonings.
When tofu is done, add
CASHEW
CHEESE and tomato dices.
Stir together well.
Pour into
a Pam-sprayed 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: better than ever cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
When done, punch holes in cake with wooden spoon.
In saucepan, combine pineapple and sugar.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Pour over cake and let set to cool.
Slice bananas and layer over cake; cover with Cool Whip and top with coconut, nuts and cherries.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix and pour in buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Layer 1/3 of crackers into single layer in 9 x 13-inch dish. Combine pudding and milk in large mixing bowl.
Beat at low speed for 2 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon 1/2 of the mixture onto crackers.
Repeat cracker layer.
Put on rest of pudding mixture. End with crackers.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix first three ingredients as for pie crust.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and pat into pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix together next three ingredients.
Add eggs.
Blend in the lemon juice.
As soon as crust comes out of oven, top with lemon mixture. Return to oven for 25 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares.

title: southwestern swiss steak
directions: Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper.
Using a mallet, pound all of the flour into the meat.
In a skillet, heat oil over medium-high.
Brown the meat on both sides.
Arrange onion slices over the meat.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over onions.
Cover and simmer until the meat is tender, about 45 minutes.
Remove meat and keep warm.
Cook the sauce until it is reduced and thickened, about 5 minutes.
Season to taste with additional salt and pepper, if desired.
Pour sauce over meat and serve immediately.

title: french silk pie
directions: In a small mixer bowl, beat together sugar and butter for 4 minutes or until light and fluffy.
Beat in melted chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating on medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes after each addition, scraping sides of bowl constantly.
Turn mixture into baked pie shell.
Chill several hours before serving, making sure it is set before serving. Garnish with whipped cream and chocolate curls as desired.

title: barbecue beef(for sandwiches)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over 3 to 4 pounds boneless stew meat; cover.
Bake 4 to 5 hours at 300°.
If too soupy, remove lid last 1/2 hour.
With fork, shred meat.
Some liquid will absorb into shredded meat.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Easy and delicious.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together.
When well mixed, pour in pecans.
Stir well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Pie is done when crust is brown and edge of filling is set.

title: chicken waikiki beach
directions: Wash and dry chicken; coat with flour.
Heat oil and brown chicken.
Remove to shallow baking pan.

title: wisconsin cranberry-apple pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in large bowl.
With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Whisk water, egg and vinegar in cup.
Sprinkle onto flour mixture 1 tablespoon at a time, tossing with fork and adding more water as needed until pastry holds together.
Divide into 4 balls; flatten into disks.
Wrap and refrigerate 1 hour. (Reserve 2 pastry disks for another use.
Wrap and freeze up to 1 month.)

title: pierogi
directions: Combine flour, eggs and water to form a firm dough.
Break off small portion of dough at a time and roll out onto floured surface until thin.
Cut into circles using the rim of a 16 ounce glass (floured).
Fill center with 1 teaspoon of filling and fold in half.
Seal edge with water and press lightly with fork tip.
Drop into boiling water and butter mixture.
Cook until they float and remove from water.
Brush with butter and freeze.

title: nancy's zucchini casserole
directions: Mix cream of chicken soup, sour cream and carrots together. Boil the sliced zucchini until tender with the onion and water for 5 minutes.
Drain and stir in soup mixture.
Combine the stuffing mix with melted butter.
Toss gently.
Line the bottom of a casserole dish with half of the stuffing mixture, then add the vegetable mixture, then add the remaining stuffing mixture on top. Bake at 350 degrees for 25-35 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix Nestle Quick, flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar and salt together. Add beaten egg yolks.
Add milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour into baked pie shell. Beat 3 egg whites with 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder and vanilla. Pour on pie and bake until brown.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Combine turkey, broth, noodles, beans, rice and seasonings in baking dish and let stand for 10 minutes.
Cover dish with foil. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: creamed chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease the bottom and sides of a 11 x 7
inch baking dish.

title: carrots elegante
directions: Cook carrots, covered, in 1/2-inch boiling water 8 minutes; drain.
Turn carrots into a 1-quart baking dish.
Stir in raisins, I Can't Believe It's Not Butter!, honey, lemon juice and ginger. Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 375° oven 35 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Spoon into serving bowl.
Sprinkle with almonds. Yield:
4 servings.

title: dump bars
directions: Mix all ingredients and stir until moistened. Pour into 9 X 13 greased pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips on top. Do not mix into batter. Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven. Can be sprinkled with powdered sugar if desired and can also add nuts on top.

title: zippy chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken pieces.
Brush with Ranch dressing. Coat with combined crumbs and cheese.
Place in baking dish and cover with foil.
Bake one hour or until tender at

title: seven-up pound cake
directions: Cream well the margarine and Crisco.
Beat in sugar, eggs, flour, lemon and 7-Up.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: sweet onion casserole
directions: Put onions in 12 x 7-inch dish.
Add crackers and sausage. Add layer of onions and top with soup.
Add salt and seasoned salt.
Add cheese and pimentos.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: kids cereal mix
directions: Wash, peel, core and cut a few apples into small pieces. Place apple pieces into a pot and cover with water until 1/4 of the apples are in the water.
Add a little cinnamon to taste. Slowly cook the apples over low heat until mushy.
Stir into sauce.
Eat warm or cold.

title: jellied cranberry-apricot sauce
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over 1/2 cup of the orange juice.
Set aside to soften.	In a medium saucepan, combine cranberries, wine, remaining 1/2 cup orange juice, apricots, and sugars.
Bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugars.	Simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in gelatin mixture and simmer, stirring 5 minutes longer.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into a 4-cup mold sprayed lightly with vegetable oil. Smooth the top.
Refrigerate overnight or until firm.	To serve, dip bottom of the mold in hot water.
Invert onto a serving plate, tapping mold to release jelly.

title: b. j.'s mississippi mud
directions: Melt together margarine, sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs, mixing well.
Add flour and salt to the nuts and then to the sugar mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Remove from oven and cover with miniature marshmallows.
These will start to melt and then cover with Chocolate Sauce.

title: cracked sugar cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a cookie sheet. Cream the sugar and butter until fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Beat in the yolks and vanilla.
Sift the dry ingredients together, then add to the batter in 4 parts, mixing well after each addition.
Form dough into balls the size of a walnut and place balls on cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Do not flatten.
Bake for approximately 11 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.
Repeat with remaining dough until used up.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: banana fritters(caribbean recipe)
directions: Peel bananas and mash with fork.
Stir in sugar.
Stir in flour, baking powder and nutmeg.
Fry by spoonful in hot oil; turn and brown on both sides.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Garnish with a sprinkle of sugar.
Serve hot.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening; add the eggs and beat well. Sift the dry ingredients together and add to the first mixture. Add the nuts.
Drop batter from a teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet, spacing two-inches apart.
Bake in a moderate oven, 350°, for ten to twelve minutes.
Makes six dozen cookies.

title: crisp german meatballs
directions: Combine sausage and onion in a large skillet; cook until sausage is browned, stirring until it crumbles.
Drain well.
Stir in sauerkraut and 2 tablespoons bread crumbs.
Combine cream cheese and next 4 ingredients in a large bowl; add sausage mixture, stirring well.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Combine mayonnaise and mustard; set aside.
Combine eggs and milk in a small bowl; set aside.
Shape sausage mixture into 3/4-inch balls; roll in flour. Dip each ball in reserved egg mixture; roll balls in 1 cup bread crumbs.
Pour oil to a depth of 2 inches into a Dutch oven; heat to 375°.
Fry, a few at a time, 2 minutes or until golden brown. Drain on paper towel.
Serve with mayonnaise mixture.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use a large spoon to cream butter and sugar.
Add yolk of egg and mix well.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Stir in fruit and nuts.
Be sure to have fruit and nuts well coated with dough.
Beat egg white until it holds soft peaks; fold into dough.
Using a teaspoon, drop dough onto an ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart; bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen cookies.

title: diet salad dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients. Refrigerate. Keeps well.

title: chocolate date nut cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and completely cool.
Cream oleo, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, cocoa and salt.
Add vanilla to date mixture and alternate date mixture and flour mixture into sugar.
In last portion of flour, add nuts.
Bake approximately 45 minutes at 350°.

title: riches bread dough(cinnamon rolls)
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top.
Break off small amounts of bread dough and roll into a shape of a hot dog. Dip into melted butter and roll in sugar and cinnamon mix.
Tie the dough in a knot.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let rise about 1 hour until double in size.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Flip onto aluminum foil.

title: rice with pigeon peas and pork(arroz con gandules y cerdo)
directions: Saute pork at medium heat in olive oil until lite brown.
Add pepper, onion and garlic and simmer for a few minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Cook slowly until liquid evaporates.
Stir; cover and cook on low heat until the rice is tender.
Serve warm.
Serves 8.

title: easy pizza party balls
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees. In a large bowl, combine the crust package, 1/3 cup of the pizza sauce and the entire container of cheese from package along with the sausage, bell pepper and onion.
Mix well.
This mixture is thick, so it might be necessary to use your hands for mixing.
Shape into small balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes. The remaining pizza sauce can be used as a dip. Insert a toothpick into each pizza ball and dip into sauce.

title: sweet 'n nutty date spread
directions: Place dates in microwave-safe dish.
Cover with water and microwave on High power for 2 minutes, until dates are soft. Drain, cool and chop.
Mix chopped dates with peanut butter and honey.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together.
Put into 8 x 8-inch pan (instead of loaf pan). Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fast nail drying tip
directions: Place ice cold water in the bowl along with chunks of ice cubes.
After painting fingernails, place hand in bowl of water and ice for 20 seconds.
Remove hand from water and nail color will be dry to slight touch.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: You will need one 8 x 11-inch rectangular pan.

title: kindergarten soup
directions: Mix together everything (with juices) except corn.
Simmer and add corn when almost done.

title: seven-layer tex-mex chip dip
directions: *You may add more or less of these ingredients.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain blueberries and pineapple, saving the juice-should be 1 cup, if not, add water.
Bring juice to boil and add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Then add 2 cups of cold water.
Next add blueberries and pineapple.
Let congeal.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Stir all together; heat thoroughly and serve on toasted buns.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Mix oatmeal and brown sugar.
Add margarine and white sugar. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and chill.
Melt together peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Spread on top of chilled mixture.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt margarine, remove from heat, and blend in sugar and egg. Sift the dry ingredients, and add to the mixture. Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread in greased 8 inch pan and bake for 25 minutes at 350 degrees.
Do not overbake.
Make 16 - 2 inch brownies.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: layer salad
directions: Mix mayo and sugar very well. In a glass 9 x 13 dish, layer veggies starting with lettuce, then peas, celery, onions and green pepper. Spread mayo dressing over veggies. The dressing should be somewhat warm; it is easier to spread. Add shredded cheese and tomatoes, if wanted. Top with bacon bits. Chill for at least 1 hour or so.

title: lettuce salad
directions: Put one layer of chopped lettuce, one layer peas and one layer onions.
Slice eggs and put on top of onions.

title: katie's krazy skewers
directions: Will need 6 to 8 wooden skewers.

title: apple punch
directions: In large mixing bowl or pitcher (3-quart).
Blend spices with apple juice.
Add remaining ingredients; chill.
Mix before serving with Sweet*10.
Makes 6 (1-cup) servings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken for 15 minutes. Bake almonds and sesame seeds 10-15 minutes at 350°, or until brown. Marinate chicken in dressing overnight or half day. Mix chicken (with dressing) with lettuce, onions, almonds and sesame seeds. Serve. Great with warm bread!

title: magic salad
directions: Mix
water and Jell-O.
Let set until it starts to jell. Then add all other ingredients; mix well.
Let jell until firm.

title: hash brown potato casserole
