directions: Place thawed potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together hash browns, soup, cheese, sour cream, onion and salt. Pour over potatoes.
Top with cornflakes (crushed) and drizzle with melted butter over all.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: joyce's mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Pour half into hot, greased 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle half of cheese.
Add remaining mixture; top with remaining cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes in a 450° oven.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large mixing bowl, beat eggs on high speed about 1/2 minute.
Add pumpkin, evaporated milk, brown sugar, granulated sugar, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg, salt and vanilla.
Beat on low until blended, about 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Bake 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 45 minutes or until knife inserted into center of pie comes out clean.
Serve with whipped cream topping.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix in order given, folding Cool Whip in last. Pour in a glass serving dish.
Refrigerate.

title: pinch me cake
directions: Melt butter.
Mix together the white sugar, brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Roll dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Dip in melted butter and roll in sugar mixture.
Drop in angel food cake pan and let rise until pan is 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: peanut butter chip chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add to butter mixture.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In a microwave-safe dish, combine sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla.
Add margarine to center of dish.
Microwave on High until melted.
Stir to blend.
Add nuts.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: she-ba dip
directions: Mix all together.
Let set at least 3 hours before serving. Serve on crackers.

title: sesame cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, flour and salt.
Add almond extract. Take teaspoon size of mixture; roll into ball, then roll in sesame seed.
Make indention in middle of ball and fill with preserves. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: tapioca rice raisin pudding
directions: Soak raisins in enough water to make 1 cup of juice, overnight or a few hours.
Mix all ingredients well, except vanilla.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cook and stir on medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Pudding will thicken as it cools.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Cool 20 minutes or more and stir.
Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 6 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add whole eggs, one at a time.
Beat well; stir in bananas.
Sift flour, then add soda in a mixing bowl.
Add this to preceding mixture; stir alternately with milk and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Put in a floured loaf pan.

title: baked chicken and broccoli
directions: Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry and soup.
Stir in chicken. Layer broccoli in the bottom of an 8 x 10 or 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Cover with the chicken mixture, then sprinkle with the cheese and finally with the bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until bubbly around the edges.
Serves 6.

title: chicken cream cheese enchiladas
directions: Chop and saute onions in margarine over moderate heat (about 20 minutes).
Remove pan from heat and add cooked chicken, pimentos and cubed cream cheese.
Mix and add salt and pepper to taste.
Put over heat just to warm mixture up; stir.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: In large bowl combine meat, orange juice, vinegar, garlic, cumin and salt.
Marinate 10 minutes.
In skillet heat oil; add onion, pepper and chicken mixture.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, until chicken is cooked.
Serve on flour tortillas with diced tomatoes, shredded lettuce and salsa.
Makes 4.

title: butterscotch treats
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and peanut butter over low heat, stirring constantly, until completely melted and smooth.
Add peanuts and noodles; mix until well coated.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper and let sit for 2 hours.
Serve.
Makes approximately 4 to 5 dozen.

title: spiced tea
directions: Use 3 tablespoons per cup with hot water or can be used as iced tea also.

title: sour cream horseradish sauce
directions: Mix all thoroughly.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: apple bars for a crowd
directions: For pastry, combine first four ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Place egg yolks in measuring cup and stir in enough cold water to make a scant 1 cup.
Sprinkle over dough.
Roll out half to line a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Place half the apples on pan, spreading evenly.

title: juicy ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape into oblong loaf in ungreased 9-inch baking pan or dish.
Bake uncovered 1 hour.
Pour drippings from pan before serving.

title: no fail pie crust(makes 4 crusts)
directions: Mix the flour, salt and shortening.
Beat together the water, egg and vinegar.
Add liquid to first mixture.
Chill.
May be frozen or kept in refrigerator for several days.

title: "gorp"
directions: Put all ingredients in a large plastic bowl with lid.
Shake to mix and serve.
A good high energy snack.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Combine Ritz crackers (crushed), margarine and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix milk with pudding, then add ice cream (softened).
Spread over crust.
Let settle.
Then spread the Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with Heath bars.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut thin slice from stem end of each pepper; remove all seeds and membranes.
Cook peppers in the boiling salted water 5 minutes; drain.
In medium skillet, cook and stir ground beef and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in salt, garlic, powder, rice and 1 cup of the tomato sauce; heat thoroughly.
Lightly stuff each pepper with 1/2 cup of meat mixture.
Stand peppers upright in ungreased baking dish.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over peppers.
Cover; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Soften cream cheese and add milk to make spreading consistency. Pat in 9-inch glass pie plate.
Spread crabmeat over cheese and dribble chili sauce over top.
Serve with crackers.

title: elegant spuds
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: millionaire cake
directions: Bake at 300° to 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pizza bubbles
directions: Brown hamburger with onions if desired.
Add spaghetti sauce to hamburger and mix.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan that has been lightly greased.
Cut biscuits into 4 pieces or smaller and place over meat mixture.
Sprinkle with diced onions, green peppers or mushrooms as desired.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 400° until biscuits are brown.

title: tita biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients together with a spoon.
Grease and flour your hands so dough will not stick as you work it into biscuits.
Put on a greased cookie sheet.
Cook at 375° to 400° until done. Makes approximately 6 large (cat head) biscuits.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Cut off each end of squash; boil whole until tender.
After cooled, cut squash lengthwise, scoop out inside and save.
Saute onion in butter until tender; mix together with all remaining ingredients, except squash shells.
Put mixture back into squash shells.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli chowder
directions: Cook broccoli in one-half of the chicken broth until tender. Chop up broccoli.
Add remaining chicken broth, milk, ham, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring several times.
Add remaining ingredients and broccoli.
Heat to serving temperature.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: tortilla roll ups
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in mixer and spread on tortillas. Divide cream cheese mixture on to each tortilla.
Spread and roll up.
Refrigerate before cutting to firm.
Cut in 1/2-inch size. Dip in salsa or picante sauce.

title: lazy man's lasagna
directions: Bring noodles and water to a boil.
Add Crisco and salt. Cook, stirring occasionally, about 8 to 10 minutes or until all done.
Drain in a colander; rinse.
Place in a greased casserole.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Melt shortening with salt and sugar.
Add onions, green pepper and mushrooms.
Brown lightly, add meat and brown until crumbly. Add to cooked spaghetti.
Add soup and tomatoes.
Mix gently and bake in buttered dish 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serve with cheese.
(If some is left over, I add small can of tomato sauce when reheating.)

title: beer bread
directions: Mix flour and sugar. Add beer. Mix well. Put dough into a greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour melted butter over bread. Return to oven and bake additional 15 minutes. Cool 5 minutes before removing from loaf pan.

title: chicken sauerkraut casserole
directions: Spray pan with Pam. Place chicken breasts on greased pan. Sprinkle cheese over chicken. Spread sauerkraut over cheese. Pour salad dressing over sauerkraut. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells and drain.
Cook spinach according to package directions.
Stir Ricotta, Mozzarella, salt and pepper into spinach.
Stuff shells with about 1 heaping tablespoonful of this mixture.
Cover single layer of shells in 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish with sauce.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover dish part of the cooking time.

title: mexican luncheon
directions: Brown sausage, onions and pepper; add tomatoes, sour cream, milk, macaroni and seasonings.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix cooked squash, cheese, soup, onion, and eggs; salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Mix melted butter and cracker crumbs together; place on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: no fat chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, set aside.
In a large bowl beat egg whites, brown sugar, yogurt and vanilla until well blended.
Add flour mixture and beat until evenly moistened.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° until cake springs back when lightly pressed in the center.
Cool in pan 15 minutes then invert onto serving plate and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Can be kept in an airtight container 1 or 2 days, but is very moist and should not be decorated with powdered sugar until just before serving.
Serves 8.
One serving has 220 calories and less than 1 gram of fat.

title: leftover turkey soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine first 6 ingredients; simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove bones and cut off meat, return meat to the broth.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, covered, 30 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese delight
directions: Boil macaroni in kettle of water with olive oil until tender. Drain water and rinse macaroni.
Return to stove with 4 cups of water.
Add cheese, grated or sliced, in the kettle with tomato soup and stewed tomatoes.
Let simmer until cheese is melted. Bake in oven 45 minutes at 325°.
Serves 6.

title: mincemeat-cranberry glaze(glaze for ham)
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Spoon over ham surface during the last 30 minutes of baking.
Makes enough glaze for a 4 pound half ham.
Double for whole ham.

title: coach collins' favorite macaroni
directions: Melt Velveeta; add milk.
Toss pasta and serve.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix and freeze.
Slice and serve as needed.

title: oatmeal butterscotch bars
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
In a large mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugars until smooth.
Beat in the eggs until mixture is light.
Add the vanilla extract, rolled oats and butterscotch chips. Turn into a lightly greased 15 1/4 x 10 1/2-inch baking pan. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until center of the bars feel firm.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with milk chocolate chips.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes until chips melt. Spread melted chips over the bars. Cut into 2-inch squares.
Serve warm or cool.
Yields 35 (2-inch) bars.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together except flour.
After mixing well, add flour.
May be dropped from teaspoon onto cookie sheet or may use cookie cutters to make cut-outs.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: curried shrimp, rice and vegetables
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add leek and cook, stirring 1 to 2 minutes, until soft.
Stir in rice, garlic and curry powder.
Cook, stirring 3 minutes.
Stir in water and cream.
Heat to boiling over high heat, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove cover and stir in vegetables, breaking them up.
Increase heat to medium. Cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes, or until rice is tender.
Stir in lime juice, salt, pepper and shrimp.
Cover and cook 5 to 10 minutes longer or until shrimp are pink and loosely curled and vegetables are hot.
Serve topped with coconut and cashews.

title: chicken delight soup
directions: Saute chicken in butter with garlic.
Remove garlic and set chicken aside.
Add mushroom and onion and cook.
Stir in milk, soup, mustard and sherry.
Add cooked chicken and simmer for ten minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: jill's challah *
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and stir.
Add 2 cups flour, oil and eggs.
Start adding additional flour.
Recipe will use approximately 6 cups.
Keep adding and kneading until dough is no longer sticky.
Put into an oiled bowl.
Cover and leave in a warm spot
until doubled in quantity (about 1 hour).
Remove from bowl. Punch and divide into sections for braiding.
Braid into one large or 2 small Challahs.
Allow to double in bulk.
Brush with egg yolks, thinned with one tablespoon of water and bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Put cheese in bowl, add egg and mix well.
Add flour and salt. Knead until smooth and hands come clean.
May have to add a little extra flour.
Drop by teaspoonful in boiling water.
Cook until they come to top or until tender (about 10 minutes).
Drain.
Fry onions in butter and pour over cheese balls and serve.

title: sensational beef stroganoff
directions: Slice beef across grain into very thin strips.
In skillet over high heat in 1 tablespoon of butter, cook half of the beef and half of the onion until beef is no longer pink and onion is tender; set aside.
Repeat with remaining butter, beef and onion. Return meat mixture to skillet.
Stir in soup and paprika.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to very low.
Stir in sour cream; gently heat through.
Serve over noodles.

title: lasagna
directions: Simmer tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, oregano, pepper and onion salt. Saute onion and garlic in oil, add ground meat and cook until done; drain.

title: gone all evening stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish.
Bake at 275° for 5 hours or cook in a crock-pot.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix together monterey jack cheese, grated cheese and cream cheese.
Set aside.
Brown ground beef and drain excess fat.
Add chopped onion, garlic, black olives, green chilies, chili powders, tomato paste and water; simmer until done.
In a 9 x 13 inch baking dish, put layer of Doritos, meat sauce, cheese mixture.
Repeat until done.
Just like you would for regular lasagna.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: creamy corn pudding
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Whisk together eggs, whipping cream and butter until smooth; stir in corn and chiles.
Pour mixture into a lightly greased 9-inch by 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until deep golden and set. Let pudding stand for 5 minutes.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Drain juice off fruit and keep; add enough water (if needed) to make 1 cup.
Combine pineapple, oranges and cherries.
Set aside.
Mix pudding with juice and cook until thickens.
While hot, pour over fruit and chill.
Before serving, add sliced bananas.

title: lemon or chocolate dessert
directions: Whip and layer on top, then layer of Cool Whip, chopped nuts or Oreo cookies sprinkled on top.
Refrigerate.

title: white chicken chili
directions: In Dutch oven or large saucepan, combine undrained corn, beans, undrained chile peppers, water, onion, lemon juice, lemon pepper seasoning, cumin and garlic.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Stir in chicken and heat through.
Ladle into bowls and top with crushed tortilla chips and shredded cheese.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Place 1/2 cup chopped pecans on bottom of pan.
Separate the Rhodes dinner rolls and place on top of pecans.
Mix 1/2 cup brown sugar and butterscotch pudding; spread on top of rolls.
Melt 1/2 stick butter; drizzle on top. Mix 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Set out all day or all night for rolls to rise.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn upside down on large plate.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg yolks, one at a time and beat well.
Dissolve the soda in the cream and add cream and flour alternately.
Fold in well beaten egg whites.
Preheat oven to 300° and bake in tube pan about 2 hours.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Lay chicken on top of rice.
Blend in blender onion, margarine, soups and milk.
Pour over chicken; sprinkle 1 envelope of dry onion soup mix over top.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Don't peek until the 1 1/2 hours is up. Bake in 13 x 9 x 1 1/2-inch casserole.

title: the six week muffin(old family recipe)
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add eggs to buttermilk and melted shortening. Combine with dry mixture.
Store in refrigerator. When ready for muffins, pour enough batter to fill muffin tins. Bake at 350° to 400° for 15 minutes.
Will keep 6 weeks in refrigerator.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen muffins.

title: fudgy oatmeal bars
directions: Mix brown sugar, 1 cup butter, eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla in large bowl.
Stir in flour, soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Stir in oats.
Reserve 1/3 of the oatmeal mixture.
Press remaining oatmeal mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat chocolate morsels, milk and 2 tablespoons butter in 2-quart saucepan over low heat.
Stir constantly until chocolate morsels are melted.
Remove from heat. Stir in nuts and salt.
Spread over oatmeal mixture in pan.
Drop reserved oatmeal mixture by rounded teaspoonfuls onto chocolate mixture.
Bake until golden brown at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cut into bars while warm.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in a bowl and then spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan coated with Pam. Place chicken on top and then sprinkle with the dry soup mix. Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: wash day dinner
directions: In large flat pan, cover bottom with butter.
Line the bottom of the pan with thick onion slices.
Then add potato slices.
Sift 2 Tbsp. flour over this.
Then pour the can of tomato juice over that.
Add enough boiling water to cover.
Place a layer of sausage on top.
If sausage gets too brown turn over.
Bake at 350 until vegetables are tender.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries, apples and oranges.
Sprinkle sugar over fruit.
Pour pineapple over and mix well.
This may be frozen and may be made ahead of time.

title: veggie pie
directions: *For example, zucchini, tomato, carrots, red/green peppers, cooked potatoes and onions can be used.

title: picante chicken and rice
directions: Saute garlic and onion in small amount of oil.
Add broth, picante and rice.
Cut breasts in half or smaller.
Lay on top of mixture.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Turn off heat and let set 5 minutes.

title: frosted creams(cake)
directions: Boil raisins and water 5 to 10 minutes to soften.
Drain raisins, saving 1 cup water.
Add soda to water and set aside. Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, water and vanilla.
Add the remaining dry ingredients to the wet.
Add raisins.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool and frost with Struedel Topping.

title: bean dip
directions: Use a round Pyrex dish.
Spread cream cheese on bottom of dish.
Layer beans.
Layer chili.
Layer cheese.
Cook at 350° until it bubbles.
Serve with tortilla chips. Must be served hot.

title: frozen salad
directions: Cream
together
sugar, mayonnaise and cream cheese and add all other ingredients.
Freeze and slice.

title: pat's texas "hot hash" cornbread
directions: Combine mix, milk, eggs and corn in bowl; mix and set aside. Saute beef; drain and set aside.
Pour 1/2 of mix in hot greased 10 1/2-inch skillet.
Sprinkle evenly with beef; top with onion, then cheese.
Add peppers evenly on top.
Pour remaining 1/2 mix over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: stir-fried beef and tomatoes
directions: Cut beef into 2-inch strips.
Put beef, 1 teaspoon oil, 1 teaspoon cornstarch, salt and white pepper in a bowl.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: corny squares
directions: Mix sugar and corn syrup in a saucepan.
Boil for 1 minute; remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, stirring until smooth.
Add vanilla and blend.
Pour over cornflakes; mix well until coated. Spread into a greased pan.
Cut into squares when cooled.

title: fried green tomatoes or eggplant
directions: Thin slice tomatoes or eggplant into a bowl of water.
Put seasoned flour into a bag, add a few slices of tomato or eggplant at a time and shake until well coated.
Put each slice into the hot grease and fry until golden brown.

title: stayaway stew
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish that has a tight lid. Place in oven at 275°. Cook at least 5 hours. Longer cooking will not affect stew.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill and serve on salad greens, if desired.

title: spiced cranberry orange mold
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl for 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in cranberry sauce, cold water, lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves.
Refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours or until thickened.
Stir in orange.
Spoon into a 5 cup mold. Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm.
Unmold.
Garnish, if desired.

title: oriental peppered steak
directions: Select a nonstick skillet large enough to hold all four steaks.
Heat oil in skillet approximately to 310° to 350° and sprinkle with garlic powder.
Carefully place steaks into hot oil and top with pepper rings.
Turn steaks occasionally to insure they cook evenly.
Remove steaks from skillet; drain oil from pepper rings.
Return steaks immediately to skillet and place on burner set at medium heat.
Pour soy sauce over steaks and peppers.
Turn steaks frequently until most of the soy sauce has been absorbed into the steaks and they are caramel colored.
Place on a meat platter and top with pepper rings.

title: indiana-style corn dogs
directions: In bowl, mix corn meal, flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, milk, egg and mustard.
Pour mixture into tall glass.
Skewer hot dogs with wooden skewer; dip in mixture.
Deep fry at 375° until golden brown (about 2 minutes).
Drain on paper towels.
Yields 10 to 16 corn dogs.

title: simple sauces
directions: Blend ingredients. Chill at least 1 hour before serving. Yields 1/3 cup.

title: pea salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite size pieces.
Layer lettuce, onions, celery and peas.
Cover with mayonnaise.
Cover with cheese and bacon bits.
Cover dish with aluminum foil; refrigerate overnight. Use a 10-inch square dish (2-quart).

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo in skillet until clear.
Layer cooked, deboned chicken and uncooked spaghetti over vegetables. Mix soup, broth, salt and pepper.
Top with layers of mushrooms and Parmesan cheese.
Bring to boil and reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together	and bake until set in a 350° oven, approximately 30 to 35 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Arrange cucumbers in bowl; top with cracked ice and sprinkle with salt.
Repeat layers with remaining vegetables.
Let stand 4 hours.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Cook rice.
Add these and remaining ingredients together in a large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pot roast of venison
directions: Trim very carefully and remove all surplus fibers, skin and fat from venison.
Lard with salt pork.
Slice onions, carrots and celery and place in Dutch oven with equal parts of red wine and water.
Add bay leaves, lemon peel, peppercorns, thyme, rosemary, parsley and salt.
Bring to boil and let simmer for 30 minutes. Add the larded venison and cover.
Simmer for 2 hours.
Remove meat, strain the sauce and place venison in roasting pan.
Pour the strained liquid over the roast, adding sour cream and cook slowly until done.
Do not forget to soak the meat first.

title: meat and potato dish
directions: Mix together bouillon soup, tomato soup, worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Place browned hamburger in bottom of a 13x9 baking pan.
Add in layers potatoes, onions, green peppers.
Add soup mixture.
Pour on top of layered ingredients.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: homemade fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, chocolate, syrup and salt in a Dutch oven. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved. continue to cook, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches soft ball stage (240°). Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla (do not stir). Cool to lukewarm (110°). Add pecans; beat with a wooden spoon 2 to 3 minutes or until mixture is thick and begins to lose its gloss. Pour into a buttered 8 inch square pan. Mark warm fudge in 1 1/3 inch squares. Cool and cut.

title: corn dogs
directions: In medium bowl, combine biscuit mix, corn meal and sugar. Beat in egg and milk until smooth.
Allow batter to stand at least 30 minutes.
Dip wieners in batter.
Fry in hot oil until brown.

title: cold tortellini-vegetable kabobs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in saucepan and slowly stir in the water and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Cook just 30 seconds, whisking with wire whisk.
Let cool.
Cut hearts in quarters. Alternate tortellini, tomatoes and hearts on 24 (6-inch) skewers. Place in a large baking dish and pour marinade over, turning to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for 5 hours, turning a
few times. Drain and place on platter.

title: oreo cookie delight
directions: Crumble Oreos in blender; mix well with melted margarine (save 1/2 cup of Oreos for topping). Press remaining cookie mixture in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: rice with onions and walnuts
directions: Boil water and add broth.
Stir in rice, reduce heat to low, cover and cook 20 minutes.
Melt butter in small skillet.
Add the onions and nuts and saute until brown.
When rice is done, add onion-nut mixture and mix well.

title: coconut blizzard
directions: Using half of ingredients at a time, combine in blender or processor until smooth and creamy.
Serve in chilled daiquiri-type glasses.
Makes 12 servings.

title: crab imperial
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put into greased casserole dish. Cover with more stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: brown sugar nuts
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add brown sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roast 30 to 40 minutes.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix ingredients with crumbled corn bread.
Serve.

title: ice cream sundae(low-fat)
directions: Put ice cream in bowl and slice banana on top.
Pour on chocolate syrup and put Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle crushed granola bits on top.
Add cherry.

title: cinnamon-caramel rolls
directions: Combine biscuit mix and milk, stirring with a fork, until blended.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead for 4 or 5 minutes. Roll dough to a 15 x 9-inch rectangle; spread with 2 tablespoons softened butter.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add apples and mix well.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Fold in nuts and flavoring.
Blend.
Bake in a greased Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Cook chicken. Set aside. Mix rest of ingredients in a saucepan. Simmer 20 minutes. Add chicken to sauce. Simmer another 30 to 45 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together well. Form into a loaf.
Place in a deep baking dish.
Bake for 45 minutes, pouring off excess grease at 15 minute intervals.

title: chocolate cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, combine cream cheese and sugar; beat well.
Blend in cocoa, scraping sides of bowl and beaters frequently.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend well. Blend in whipping cream.
Pour into crust.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes (center will be soft but will set upon cooling).
Cool to room temperature.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Top with pie filling.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Put wedges, peel side down, in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and brush over potatoes.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Brush occasionally with juices.

title: chili mac
directions: Brown ground round and onion.
Drain excess fat.
Place in Dutch oven or large pot.
Add remaining ingredients, breaking up tomatoes.
Bring to boil.
Reduce to simmer.
Cover and cook until pasta is tender.

title: daddy's truffle
directions: Cut pound cake into squares.
Set aside.
Make instant pudding, set aside.
Cut strawberries and bananas into slices.
In a large bowl, layer ingredients in the following order using 1/2 of each to make sure you have enough to layer twice:
pound cake, pudding, pineapple, oranges, strawberries, bananas and blueberries.
Repeat for second layer.
Top with Cool Whip, garnish with blueberries.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream together both cheeses.
Add remaining ingredients and 1/2 dried beef.
Mix together.
Form into a ball.
Garnish with remaining dried beef.

title: russian salad
directions: Dissolve marshmallows, cream cheese and Jell-O with 1 cup hot water. Then add other ingredients and congeal.

title: vanilla butternut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Grease a 9x13x2 inch baking pan. In large bowl, beat the eggs slightly with a fork. Then add each ingredient in the order listed, mixing well after each addition. Pour the batter into the prepared pan. Bake for about 45 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. This batter will rise and look like a cake but it falls as it cools and becomes a chewy bar cookie.

title: carrot patties
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook slowly on both sides in oiled skillet on top of stove.
Small and flat patties will cook more quickly.
(Any vegetable that family likes can be used in a patty.)

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice
tomatoes
inch
thick and roll in cornmeal. Fry in bacon drippings and sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: fiesta corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill several hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt margarine and add graham cracker crumbs.
Spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: stuffed chicken on the grill
directions: Butter inside of chicken.
Sprinkle sage in afterwards.
Cut up carrots, celery and onion.
Put inside of chicken.
Cover chicken with foil.
Put on grill for about an hour.
(Foil the rack on grill and spray some Pam on it before putting the chicken on it.)

title: versatile rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add salt and sugar and cool mixture to 85°. Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine milk and yeast mixtures and mix until smooth.
Gradually add flour and mix after each addition. Knead well; let rise covered until double in bulk.
Shape dough as you wish.
Permit rolls to rise in covered pans until doubled. Bake for about 40 minutes at 275°.
Makes 5 dozen rolls.

title: sour cream lemon pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter and sour cream in saucepan and cook over medium heat until thick.
Stir in butter, then cool.
Stir in sour cream, then pour into 9-inch cooked pie shell.
Cover with 1 cup heavy whipped cream.
Garnish with lemon twists.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cajun style fish
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lay fish fillets in shallow baking dish, skin side down.
Sprinkle with all of spices.
In small pan, heat butter, soy sauce, lemon juice and 1/2 teaspoon Redfish Magic until melted; keep warm.
Baste fish fillets with mixture at beginning and during cooking; save some sauce for later.
Bake fish uncovered 15 to 20 minutes (depending on thickness) until it flakes easily with fork.
Remove from oven.
Place on platter. Reheat sauce and pour over fish and serve.

title: slow-cooker chili soup
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat until hot. Add beef and onions; cook and stir until beef is browned.

In slow cooker, combine browned beef and onions and all remaining ingredients, except beans; mix well. Cook on high setting for 1 hour. Reduce heat to low; cook 4 to 5 hours or until beef and vegetables are tender. Stir in beans; cook an additional 30 to 45 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Yields 7 (1 1/3 cup) servings.

title: one bowl chocolate fudge(microwave)
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in large microwavable bowl on High 2 or 3 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring halfway through heating time.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir in vanilla and walnuts.

title: strawberry pineapple salad
directions: Add boiling water to gelatin.
Add 2 cups cold liquid (juice from fruits and water), lemon juice and fruit.
Put 1/2 mixture in mold and chill until it begins to set.
Add sour cream to other half and put on top.
Chill.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in frozen potatoes.
Mix soup, onions, sour cream and cheese.
Pour over potatoes.
Mix 1 stick melted margarine and crushed cornflakes and put on top, if desired.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix first five ingredients.
Add flour and soda, then candy.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Mix together 1 pkg. of cheese, 3/4 c. dry Bisquick and all of the sausage.
Cut jalapenos in half.
Stuff a half pepper with the Bisquick/sausage/cheese mixture.
Stuff the other half pepper with just cheese.
Pinch together tightly.
Prepare the other 3/4 c. Bisquick according to directions and roll out 1/8 inch thick.
Wrap each jalapeno in dough and roll in your hands to form an egg, removing any extra dough.
Roll in coating mix, dip in beaten egg and roll in coating mix again.
Bake at 325° 20-25 minutes.

title: pear `n' apple cobbler
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the cornstarch, 1/4 tsp. of cinnamon and orange juice until smooth. Gently stir in pie filling and pears.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 1-2 minutes or until thickened.
Keep warm.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Brown your hamburger with onion in a frying pan.
Pour off excess fat.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Peel eggplant and cook until soft in salt water.
Mash up the eggplant and fold it in the hamburger mixture.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Pour into greased casserole dish and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric skillet.
I like to use a 5-quart Dutch oven.
Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour (about 250° electric skillet) or until tender.

title: cranberry ketchup
directions: Combine cranberries, red wine vinegar and water in a large saucepan.
Tie allspice, cloves and cinnamon together in a piece of cheesecloth; add to pan.
Bring to a boil, the reduce heat to medium and cook until cranberries pop.
Remove spice bag and press cranberries with a spoon through a strainer.
Discard skins. Return pulp to saucepan.
Add sugar; boil until thick, about 10 minutes.
Ladle into clean, hot pint jars.
Wipe rims clean with a damp cloth; apply new lids and ring bands.
Process in a simmering water bath for 10 minutes to seal.
Remove from water bath; cool. Check seals, label and store in a cool, dark, dry place.
Makes 2 pints.

title: russian tea
directions: Dissolve sugar in 1 quart boiling water.
Add cinnamon and cloves; boil 5 minutes.
Add lemon, orange and pineapple juice after boiling.
Makes 2 quarts of tea.
Pour together.
Serve hot. Makes 1 gallon.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Take about 2 tablespoons mixture; put into cabbage leaf.
Roll.
Place into roaster pan and pour sauce over rolls.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked steak
directions: Cut steak in serving size pieces.
Dip steak in oil; roll in crumbs.
Place in a foil lined baking dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 8 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar, baking powder and flour.
Add eggs and beat well. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yield: 2 pies.

title: mock sour cream
directions: In a blender or small food processor, combine all the ingredients.
Blend into a smooth consistency.
Refrigerate in a screwtop jar for daily use.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: sloppy joes(non-dairy)
directions: Warm vegetarian burger with onion in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat until celery and peppers are tender, about 12 minutes.
Serve on toasted whole wheat buns.

title: pretzel rolls
directions: Place water in electric mixer bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, salt, butter, 1/2 beaten egg and 1 1/2 cups flour.
Beat at medium speed until smooth.
Work in as much of the remaining flour as is necessary to make a stiff dough. Cover bowl with aluminum foil; refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: all-bran muffins
directions: Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until lightly browned. Serve warm.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: In a greased 9 x 13 pan, layer hash browns. Mix rest of ingredients, except corn flakes and 1/4 cup margarine. Layer on top of hash browns. Mix crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted margarine. Sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.

title: quick oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugars.
Add egg, vanilla and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Sift flour with soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix with sugar. Make a hole in center of flour mixture.
Add Wesson oil.
Do not stir.
Add eggs, vanilla and grated apples.
Mix well.
Add pecans and raisins (optional).
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: peggy's favorite easy bake breakfast rolls
directions: Butter a 10-inch Bundt pan.
Put rolls around bottom of pan. Sprinkle top with pudding mix and nuts.
Sprinkle with cinnamon to your taste.
Melt butter and brown sugar; drizzle over the top of the rolls.
Cover with a towel and let raise overnight.
In the morning, bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chess cake
directions: Beat cake mix, oleo and egg until thick.
Spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix powdered sugar, eggs and cream cheese until smooth and spread on top of first mixture.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Grind meat
together
twice.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Make into
balls a little bigger than a walnut.
Fill electric skillet full
of
water
and
add
3 or 4 bay leaves, broken into pieces.
Bring to boil.
Drop in meatballs, simmer for 1 full hour, covered.
Boil off excess liquid.
These can be prepared two or
three days ahead and reheated (the flavor improves).

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pour into vanilla wafer pie crust.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and Ranch dressing together; roll in pecans.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice and steam carrots until just crunchy. Blend soup, oil, vinegar, sugar, sauce and spices. In a large bowl, tumble onion and pepper with carrots while dribbling over sauce. Store in large jar in fridge. Ready in 3 days. Lasts a long time.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and cream cheese together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour 1 cup at a time.
Add vanilla and 1 cup of pecans.
Grease and flour pan.
Spread 1/2 cup nuts in bottom of pan.
Pour in batter and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: dillie's dip pudding
directions: Put milk into 2-quart saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add egg until well blended.
Pour mixture into heated milk.
Stir continuously until boiling and thickened. Remove from fire and add vanilla and nutmeg. Stir. Serve hot or cold over pound cake or Jiffy yellow or white cake.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Add remaining ingredients on top of melted oleo.
Bake at 350°.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: lemon ginger chicken salad
directions: Mix together the mayo, sour cream, sugar, salt and ginger. Add chicken, grapes and celery.
Toss to coat.
Cover and chill 2 hours. Serve in cantaloupe halves.
Sprinkle with toasted almond slivers or serve on croissant with spread.

title: no-bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk, oleo and vanilla in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil; let it boil for 10 minutes or until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add oats.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: melon ambrosia
directions: In a large bowl, combine honeydew melon balls, cantaloupe balls and watermelon cubes.
Combine sugar, water, lemon juice and lime juice mixture over fruit in bowl; toss lightly.
Cover; chill 4 to 6 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: love cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth; add gradually the flour, milk and vanilla to butter and sugar mixture.
Beat until smooth. Fold in egg whites.
Pour into layer pans.
Bake in moderate oven 30 to 35 minutes.

title: almond-butter pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix in flour.
Add vanilla and almond extract; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan or small loaf pans. Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Stir all ingredients together; put in an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut frankfurters into 1-inch slices. Pare potatoes and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Parboil 5 minutes. Drain.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Pare sweet potatoes.
Cut in halves lengthwise.
Place in baking dish.
Add sugar, syrup, butter and water.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.
Cover.
Bake in oven until tender and a thick syrup is formed.

title: polenta with sausage sauce
directions: Remove and discard casings from sausage.
Crumble sausages into a 10 to 12-inch frying pan.
Stir often over high heat until brown and crumbly, 5 to 7 minutes.
Discard fat.
Add onion and stir until lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Add wine, 1 cup water, tomato paste, oregano and thyme.
Simmer until reduces to 3 cups, about 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Meanwhile, in a 3 to 4-quart pan, mix polenta, 4 1/2 cups water and milk.
Bring to boil on high heat, stirring.
Reduce heat to low; stir often until polenta is thick and creamy (about 20 minutes).
Spoon polenta into bowls.
Cover with sauce.
Add salt, pepper and cheese to taste.

title: italian chicken
directions: In medium saucepan combine tomato sauce, onion, mushrooms, green peppers and spices. Bring to a boil and simmer 15 minutes. Remove from heat. Place chicken in baking dish cover with sauce, and cover with foil. Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes until the chicken is done. Uncover and sprinkle with parmesan and grated cheese. Bake until cheese melts and is slightly browned. Serve over small pkg. of spaghetti noodles.

title: chicken sauce piquante
directions: In a paper or plastic bag, place flour and 1 Tbsp. of seasoning mix.
Shake well to blend.
Sprinkle 1 Tbsp. of seasoning mix over chicken pieces.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture until well coated.
Fry until brown and crispy.
Watch your heat so that drippings do not burn.
Drain chicken pieces well.
Pour hot oil from skillet into a glass measuring cup, leaving as much sediment as possible in the pan.

title: crock-pot italian beef
directions: Place roast in crock-pot.
Mix remaining ingredients in small saucepan and bring to boil.
Pour over roast.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Remove roast from crock-pot and shred meat.
Put back in crock-pot until ready to serve.
Makes 6 to 8 sandwiches.

title: turnip greens with hog jowl
directions: Wash greens in several waters, trimming off excess stems. Cook hog jowl in water to cover, about two hours.
Add greens and salt, making sure there's enough water to allow the greens to cook for one hour.
Most of the water should be cooked away when the hour is up.

title: spinach bacon salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix spinach, onion, radishes, and 1/2 cup mushrooms.
In a skillet, fry bacon until crisp and remove from skillet.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper to skillet.
Stir ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Pour bacon and dressing mixture over salad and toss.
Garnish with remaining mushrooms and eggs.

title: french onion soup
directions: *Can also substitute 1/2 water and milk or stock and wine mix.

title: chili con carne
directions: Cook and stir onions, garlic and meat in hot oil until meat loses red color.
Stir in undrained beans, tomato sauce and remaining ingredients.
Simmer over low heat, stirring occasionally, until chili is desired thickness, about 45 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Let cool.
Then top with following mixture.
Mix in large bowl the pineapple, pie filling and Cool Whip.
Mix about 1 minute, until Cool Whip is melted. Spread on cake and chill.

title: no peek chicken bake
directions: Mix rice, mushroom soup and 3/4 soup can of water.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place chicken pieces on top of rice; sprinkle dry soup mix over chicken.
Cover with aluminum foil; bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Layer potato, onion and bell pepper in dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix soup and milk, heat and pour over mixture.
Cook in oven at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Place margarine, broccoli, onion, cheese, eggs and cornbread mix in mixing bowl; mix thoroughly.
Bake at 350° in well-greased iron skillet sprinkled with cornmeal for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: lentil and brown rice soup
directions: In a heavy kettle, combine the stock, 3 cups water, the lentils, the rice, the tomatoes, the reserved juice, the carrots, the onion, the celery, the garlic, the basil, the oregano, the thyme and the bay leaf.
Bring the liquid to a boil and simmer the mixture, covered, stirring occasionally for 45 to 55 minutes or until the lentils and rice are tender.
Stir in the parsley, the vinegar and salt and pepper and discard the bay leaf.
The soup will be thick and will thicken as it stands.
Thin the soup, if desired, with additional hot chicken stock or water.
Makes about 14 cups.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: christmas popcorn treats
directions: Line baking sheet with waxed paper.
Pour popcorn into large bowl.
Combine sugar and corn syrup in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly; boil 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and green food coloring. Stir until peanut butter is completely melted.
Pour over popcorn; stir to coat well.

title: crusty cheese balls(appetizer)
directions: Combine cheese, dry bread crumbs, egg yolk and seasonings. Fold in stiffly beaten egg white.
Shape into balls about 3/4-inch in diameter.
Roll in fine bread crumbs.
Fry in hot deep fat (375°) until brown.
Makes about 24 balls.

title: doctored baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in slow oven at 300° for 2 hours.
Chunks of ham may be added.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Blend sour cream and cream cheese with mixer until smooth. Add other ingredients, mixing well with large spoon.
Chill thoroughly, preferably overnight.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and marshmallows in boiling water.
Add cream cheese (mashed).
Add other ingredients and chill.

title: icebox potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat well.
Keep in refrigerator 7 to 10 days.
Warm up as desired, or make salads, etc.

title: brown sugar cutout cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar, butter, oil, vanilla and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add 2 cups flour. Stir well.
Add water and 2 more cups flour with soda and cream of tartar.
Stir well.
Add the last 2 cups of flour, one at a time. Make stiff enough to roll.
Chill overnight. Roll thin and cut out with your favorite cutters.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 8 minutes, or until lightly brown.

title: romaine and artichoke salad
directions: In a salad bowl, combine lettuces, onion, artichoke hearts and pimento.
Toss to mix.
In a measuring cup, combine, oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and garlic.
Pour over lettuce mixture and toss to coat all ingredients well.
Add cheese and toss again. Serve immediately.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in 2-quart microwavable casserole dish. Cover tightly and microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes or until hot.

title: mom scholl's richer roll dough
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar and cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water, 5 minutes. Add a little sugar to yeast when dissolving. Combine lukewarm milk and dissolved yeast.
Add 3 cups flour and beat well. Add eggs and salt which have been beaten lightly. Add melted Crisco.
When it is well blended, add most of the remaining flour, reserving some for kneading.
When thoroughly mixed and stiff, let rest for 10 minutes.
After resting, knead until smooth and elastic. Return to oiled bowl to rise until doubled. Punch down.
Knead and let rise again.
Shape into loaves, rolls, etc., and let rise.
Put in preheated 400° oven about 15 minutes.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Combine butter, milk, egg and sugar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches a rolling boil.
Cool until warm and add coconut, nuts and crumbs.
Spread this mixture over crackers in the pan.
Cover with whole graham crackers.
Frost with following frosting.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Mix all together and blend well by hand; do not beat a lot. Bake in loaf pan 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Cool, slice and serve.

title: easy chili con carne
directions: Fry out beef.
Drain off any grease.
Add onion and brown lightly.
Add beans, soup and chili powder.
Simmer 20 minutes. Use low heat.
Serve with saltine crackers.
Nice for a cold day.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Brown the chicken in butter.
Remove chicken and add wine to the pan.
To the butter and wine, add apples, celery, onion, parsley, salt and paprika.
Cook until tender.
Stir in flour and stock.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze some water from the spinach.
Blend with mayonnaise and sour cream.
Stir in onions and vegetable soup.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: plantation pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, corn syrup, butter and vanilla gently until combined.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Pour into unbaked 8-inch pie shell.
May garnish with pecan halves.
Bake in preheated 375° oven until set about 30 minutes.
May drizzle melted chocolate over cooled pie between pecans.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs lightly in mixer.
Add remaining ingredients except pecans.
Blend until just combined. Pour mixture into pie shell and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake 40 minutes or until filling is puffy and the crust is golden brown.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Place wafers in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine gelatin and boiling water and lemon juice, peel and sugar.
Place in refrigerator until it starts to set.
Whip evaporated milk until thick and fold into gelatin mixture.
Pour over crushed wafers. Sprinkle a few crumbs on top.
Let chill.
Yields approximately 14 pieces.

title: keebler crunchers
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Break graham crackers into individual pieces.
Spread in single layer over entire lined cookie sheet.
In a saucepan, melt butter and margarine.
Add sugar and bring to a boil, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes or until thickened and golden brown (will be very bubbly).
Pour evenly over crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake approximately 8 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.
Cool and break apart.

title: cheating heart of tomato soup
directions: Stir water into soup, make as creamy as possible.
Then add tomatoes and rosemary.
Bring almost to a boil and reduce heat, simmer until ready to serve.

title: confetti macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and cool.
In large bowl, mix macaroni with remaining ingredients. Cover and refrigerate until well chilled.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: "primavera salad"(spring)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in refrigerator for 1/2 hour and enjoy it.

title: mac and cheese casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on package. Cut sausage or brats in bite size pieces and brown or stir-fry.
Thin soup with 1/2 cup of milk.
Mix all ingredients and spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Cover with buttered cracker crumbs and bake at 250° until heated or crumbs are golden brown.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix all
ingredients together in large bowl.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: grandma's sugar cookie recipe
directions: Mix together sugar, shortening eggs, sour milk.
Add the rest of the ingredients a little at a time.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Kneed until it loses its stickiness.
Roll out and cut with with cutter.
Bake 350°
for 8 minutes.
Ice with fondant.

title: lemon-butter cups
directions: Prepare pie crust mix according to directions on package; roll out dough, half at a time, to 1/8-inch thickness on lightly floured pastry cloth.
Cut out circles about 3 1/2 inches across; fit into small tart or muffin pan cups; flute edges.
Prick pastry with fork.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for about 10 minutes or until golden brown; cool.
Just before serving, fill each cup with about 1 tablespoon Lemon Butter.
Makes 3 dozen tarts.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Combine and mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over batter.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in 375° oven or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Serve warm.

title: lemon ginger chicken and pasta
directions: Squeeze the lemons into a Ziploc bag.
Remove the pits.
Add the soy sauce and grated ginger.
Add the chicken pieces to the bag.
Squeeze as much air out of the bag as possible and close. Refrigerate for 24 hours, turning the bag a few times so that all pieces are equally well marinated.
About 45 minutes before the meal, drain the chicken pieces and place them in one layer in a shallow roasting pan.
Throw out the marinade as the baking chicken will draw plenty of pan juices.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, basting with the pan juices occasionally.
Drain and reserve the juices and then raise the heat to 400° and bake for another 10 minutes to brown and crisp up the skin.

title: low-fat banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with skim milk.
Layer pudding, cake and bananas and top with Cool Whip.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll into small balls.
Bake for 15 minutes on each side.
Good hot or cold.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Mix ingredients together, let simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Split buns, spread mixture on each half.
Bake at 400 degrees until mixture is browned.
Makes about 12 burgers depending on how much you put on the half.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown onion and hamburger.
Add drained beans and soup.
Put in shallow baking dish and top with mashed potatoes to which cream and butter have been added.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry pies
directions: In a medium boiler, combine sugar, salt and jello.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1 1/2 cups of hot water.
Pour in boiler with dry ingredients and cook over medium heat until sugar and jello are dissolved (stir constantly).
Drain strawberries and place in bottom of pie crusts.
Pour liquid mixture into crusts.
Chill. Top with whipped cream or Dream Whip.

title: roger's mexican dip
directions: Cook and stir ground beef until brown; drain. Stir in beans, tomato sauce, seasoning mix, onion, mustard and chili powder. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Spread in ungreased 9-inch pie plate. Spread sour cream over ground beef mixture, sprinkle with shredded lettuce and cheese. Serve with corn chips.

title: easy party punch
directions: Chill each ingredient.
Mix together in a large punch bowl. Add crushed ice and serve.

title: tropical ice salad
directions: In muffin pans, chop 2 cherries in each compartment.
Mix all other ingredients, together and divide evenly among muffin pans. Freeze.
Serve on a lettuce leaf with sliced fruit. Makes 20 frozen fruit cups.

title: beef stew
directions: In a 5 quart
Dutch
oven,
heat oil.
Saute onions and garlic.
Add beef; brown
on all sides.
Stir in salt, pepper, chili powder and
reserved	tomato	juice.	Bring
to
a boil. Reduce to low heat;
cover and cook 1 hour.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and
cook
minutes or until cabbage is done.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken tortillas
directions: Mix chicken, onion, sour cream and 1 can of mushroom soup. Place mixture in tortillas and roll up.
Place in baking dish; bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Pour remaining can of mushroom soup over tortillas.
Add salsa and grated cheese.
Bake another 20 minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: lo-cal chocolate-nut brownies
directions: Melt the unsweetened chocolate and butter in a saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Add sweetener, vanilla and the beaten eggs.
Stir until well blended.
Add sifted cake flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix until blended.
Stir in chopped walnuts.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Level batter in pan.
Bake in a slow 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Makes 32 brownies at 55 calories each.

title: easy fruit punch
directions: Mix all in 1 gallon jug.
Fill the jug to the top with water. Stir well.
Refrigerate.
Will keep a long time.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: In top of double boiler, melt oleo and marshmallows.
In a large bowl, put other ingredients and pour melted mixture over them.
Mix well!
Mold or shape into 2 rolls or loaves.
Wrap in wax paper and store in refrigerator. Best when stored several days in refrigerator.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine the shredded cheese, chicken soup, sour cream, chopped onion, 1/4 cup melted butter, salt and pepper; mix well.
Fold in thawed hash brown potatoes.
Pour mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Crush corn flakes and 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Sprinkle over the potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown and potatoes are tender.

title: pumpkin crisp
directions: Whisk together first 2 ingredients.
Then mix next 4 ingredients in with first 2.
Mix well.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle yellow cake mix over pumpkin mixture, then 1 1/2 cup nuts.
Melt margarine; drizzle over nuts and cake mix.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken barbecue for sandwiches
directions: Simmer hens until tender; cool in broth.
Remove meat, skin and bones.
Cut or tear chicken into small pieces.
This can be done a day ahead before preparing barbecue.

title: pink party punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; stir well.
Add ginger ale at last minute.
Makes 32 (4 ounce) punch cup servings.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream together first 5 ingredients.
Mix flour, soda and salt together and blend with creamed mixture.
Fold in cornflakes and oats.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes a dishpan full. Can be frozen.

title: rhubarb brownies
directions: Mix sugar and rhubarb and set aside.
In large bowl, cream shortening, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, cinnamon, salt and baking soda. Add to first mixture and mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs. Sift together flour, soda and salt. Add bananas alternately with sifted dry ingredients to butter mixture. Mix in vanilla and nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 400°.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla until totally mixed.
Blend in soda and salt.
Add peanut butter, flour and milk.
Mix chocolate bits in by hand.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Wash cauliflower; break into small pieces and place in large saucepan.
Add onions, celery and water.
Simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove vegetables from cooking water with slotted spoon.
Save cooking water.
Place vegetables and butter in food processor and process until smooth.
In large saucepan, melt butter and stir in flour and seasoning.
Cook 1 minute.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease and flour two 9 inch round pans or spray with non-stick cooking spray. (If you are using a non-stick pan you will not need to do this.)

title: irish bread #3
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and cut in margarine until crumbly.
Add buttermilk, raisins and caraway seed.
Mix until well blended.
Place mixture into well-greased 9-inch round cake pan. Brush top with 2 tablespoons of melted margarine.
Sprinkle with 4 teaspoons of sugar and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Cut an "X" on top with a sharp knife.

title: imperial chicken
directions: Dip chicken in butter or oleo.
Roll in crumbs.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan for approximately 1 hour at 350° to 375°.

title: fresh broccoli and mushroom salad
directions: Make dressing according to package.
Pour over vegetables and let set overnight.

title: todd's lazy man cobbler
directions: Melt butter; add fruit.
Then mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: ziti
directions: Brown sausage and ground meat until brown; drain. Simmer 1/2 hour with sauce. In casserole layer the following: 1/3 sauce and meat mixture, 1/3 ziti noodles, 1/3 mushrooms, 1/3 Mozzarella cheese and 1/3 Parmesan cheese. Repeat until all ingredients are used. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Saute onions, parsley and garlic in butter.
Add shrimp.
Cook until pink (about 3 minutes).
Add salt, pepper, lemon juice and dry vermouth.
Heat 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles

title: cream cheese topped pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Beat eggs in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Add sugar and continue beating until thick.
Stir in flour, pineapple, pecans, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake until knife inserted into center comes out clean, about 40 to 45 minutes.
Let cool in pan on rack.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Boil chicken until fully cooked; debone.
In separate pan, combine soups, onion, bell pepper and water; bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
In casserole dish, alternate 1 layer of chicken and 1 layer of tortillas until all the chicken is used. Pour the soup over the top of the chicken and tortillas.
Cover with cheese; put in oven at 350° until cheese is melted.
Serve hot.

title: blueberry citrus cake
directions: In large bowl, combine cake mix, orange juice, water, oil and eggs.
Beat with electric mixer on low speed for 30 seconds. Increase speed to medium; beat for 2 minutes.
With a wooden spoon, gently fold in blueberries, orange peel and lemon peel. Pour into 2 greased and floured 8 or 9 inch round pans.

title: frozen oreo dessert
directions: Crumble enough cookies to make a crust for a 13 x 9-inch pan. Melt the stick of margarine and mix in crumbs.
Form crust in bottom of pan.

title: caramel apple pie
directions: Combine tapioca, salt, cinnamon, orange juice, orange rind and apples.
Fill unbaked pie shell with 1/2 apple mixture and sprinkle with 1/2 of the caramel chips.
Add remaining apples, then remaining chips; dot with butter.
Put on top crust (make slits in top crust for air to escape).
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hamburger help mate
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Cook noodles.
Add soups and Cheez Whiz to noodles.
Mix in hamburger and onion.
Add green pepper and garlic salt, if you want.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
No need to cover.

title: toquitos
directions: In a skillet, heat oil until warm.
Place a tortilla in oil until soft (do not fry them until they are crisp).
Shake off excess oil.
Lay tortillas flat.
Put a tablespoon of meat on tortilla; roll tightly.
Place on baking sheet.
Make as many as you want.
Bake at 500° until crunchy.
Serve with salsa, sour cream or guacamole.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Roll Basic Dough on lightly floured surface to a 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Brush with 1/4 cup melted butter; sprinkle with mixture of 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Roll lengthwise as for jelly roll; seal edge.
Cut roll in 1-inch slices.

title: corn and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in a small skillet over low heat; add onion and green pepper and saute until tender.
Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 c. Cheddar and Monterey Jack
cheese mixture.
Spoon into a lightly greased casserole and top with the Cheddar/Monterey Jack cheese.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: lentil soup
directions: In a soup kettle, brown first four ingredients in oil.
Add next six ingredients and cook until it simmers or is heated through.
Add chili powder and red pepper to taste.
Cook about 1 1/2 hours and add water to prevent it being too thick.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugars. Add egg and pumpkin.
Sift together all dry ingredients. Beat in alternating with sour milk. Add nuts, if desired.
Bake in two 8-inch greased cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool. Frost with Fluffy White Icing.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: As soon as sweet potato is grated (food processor works), mix with milk to prevent darkening.
Add other ingredients and pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°. Stir at 15 minute intervals while baking.

title: jello instant pie
directions: Mix instant pie mix (your choice of flavor) and milk until thickened, then fold in sour cream and 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Put into the pie crust; let set in refrigerator.
Put Cool Whip on top of pie just before serving.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Crumble corned beef in bottom of well-greased 8 x 12-inch pan. Pat dressing over corned beef.
Spread sauerkraut over top.
Then cover top with Swiss cheese.

title: bonbons
directions: Cream butter, milk and powdered sugar well.
Add coconut and walnuts; roll mixture into small bite size balls and chill.
Melt wax and chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Place toothpicks in the chilled balls and dip in the chocolate; chill and re-dip. Chill and remove toothpicks.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix equal parts of breadcrumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Add parsley to taste.
Dip chicken pieces in melted butter and roll in crumb-cheese mixture.
Spray pan with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° for approximate cooking time: boneless 30 minutes, with bone 45 minutes.

title: summer sausage
directions: Combine and mix well.
Shape in 2 rolls.
Wrap in foil.
Tie ends.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Don't remove foil; place in pan. Cover with water.
Bring to boil and boil 1 hour.
Punch holes in foil to drain over rack.
Re-wrap and refrigerate.

title: vegetables in-a-huddle
directions: Cut celery and carrot slices diagonally.
Pour dressing over combined vegetables.
Toss.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for 4 hours or overnight.

title: broccoli delight
directions: Prepare a pie crust in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until flaky, not done.

title: delicious dip
directions: Mix together with a wire whisk and chill at least 4 hours. Serve with vegetables or chips.

title: potato topper
directions: Mix yogurt, horseradish, onion and chives together. Serve heated with roast beef or chilled for baked potatoes.

title: crunchy punch
directions: Dissolve sugar and gelatin in boiling water.
Add additional water and mix.
Add rest of ingredients except 7-Up.
Freeze overnight or longer.
At time of serving, remove from freezer 1 hour prior to serving (if not too hot) and add ginger ale, 7-Up, etc., to make as many servings as you need.
Mixture can be refrozen.
Serves up to 50 punch servings.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Add tomato sauce and mix well. Mold.

title: applesauce meatballs
directions: Mix well and make into medium balls.
Pour 1 can Hunt's tomato paste over top.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: german apple pancake
directions: In blender, mix eggs, flour, milk and salt.
Blend until smooth.
Let batter stand 1 hour.
Sprinkle juice of 1/2 lemon over apple slices.
In a 12-inch skillet (that can go in oven), heat 2 tablespoons butter.
When bubbly, pour in batter.
Cover with apple slices and bake in 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter; sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mixture over apples.
Return to oven for 2 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Arrange apples in buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with bourbon, then with 1 tablespoon sugar and the cinnamon.
Pour butter into a bowl.
Add 3/4 cup sugar, flour and egg and stir until smooth.
Spread batter over apples; sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar.

title: creamed crabmeat with artichoke hearts
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in 1 tablespoon butter in a heavy saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until tender. Drain.
Press mushroom mixture, crabmeat and artichoke hearts between paper towels to remove excess moisture; set aside.
Melt 1/2 cup butter in a saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add whipping cream; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in white wine and remaining ingredients.

title: crunchy milk chocolate fudge
directions: In top of a double boiler over hot water, melt chocolate pieces and peanut butter.
Remove from heat.
Stir in condensed milk; mix well.
Spread fudge in a lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Turn fudge out and cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds of candy.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt butter and add sugar, cocoa and milk.
Let boil for a couple of minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Can either dip out and make cookies or spread all the mixture into a pan and dip out when desired.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: In large saucepan, brown meat lightly; drain off excess fat. Add onion, garlic, tomato paste, water, parsley, basil, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, about 30 minutes; stir occasionally.

title: oyster stew
directions: Melt butter in frying pan over low heat.
Add oysters until they curl.
In a separate pan, combine milk and half and half. Scald it and combine with oyster mix after they curl.
Garnish with paprika and serve with oyster crackers.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together well with a fork.
Make into cakes.
Fry on both sides until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel to absorb the grease.
Serves 4.

title: creamy chicken
directions: Place chicken breast in a pan.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Pour cream of chicken soup over chicken and bake another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: grandma's cake
directions: Grease pan.
Layer pineapple and cherry pie filling.
Prepare yellow cake mix as directed on box.
Pour cake mix over pineapple and cherries; add walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; spread coconut over top and dot with oleo.
Return to oven for 1/2 hour.

title: easter lilies
directions: Combine eggs, mayonnaise, onion, salt and pepper.
Add vinegar and mash to smooth paste.
Spread on bread.
Fasten two opposite corners of bread together with toothpicks forming lily shape. Decorate with carrot stick for center of lily and pickle slices for leaves.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan pies
directions: Mix syrup, sugar, flour & salt.
Stir and add melted oleo and vanilla.

Mix well and add eggs. Mix well & add chopped pecans. Mix and pour in unbaked pie shells and decorate with pecan halves. Preheat oven to 350 degrees and bake for 20 minutes, then lower the temperature to 325 degrees and bake until firm in center and light brown in color.
Bake approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and serve.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant.
Cut into small cubes.
Boil in salted water until tender.
Drain and mash.
Fry onion in butter or bacon grease until tender.
Add eggplant, tomatoes, salt, pepper and 1/2 of bread crumbs.
Mix well.
Add eggs and cheese.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle the remaining bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° until eggs are done and crumbs are brown.

title: berry whip frosting
directions: Put all in bowl and mix together with mixer.
Beat for a long time for frosting to remain stiff.

title: pineapple bars
directions: Beat eggs and sugar, add undrained pineapple, flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add nuts and mix well.
Pour into 11 x 17-inch jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle coconut on top and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Spread glaze on top and sprinkle with 1/2 cup chopped nuts.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Make roux by browning oil and flour until it reaches the color of a paper bag.
Add water and chopped onions, garlic, bell pepper and spices, including bay leaves.
Cook until tender.
Then add seafood, green onions and parsley.
Add okra last and turn off the heat.

title: scandinavian rice cream
directions: Prepare several hours before serving.

title: gail's overnight surprise
directions: Butter a solid angel food cake pan or Bundt pan.
Place nuts in bottom of pan, covering completely.
Place the frozen dough balls on top.
Sprinkle the pudding mix on top of dough balls.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, cheese, sour cream, soup, butter, salt and pepper.
Put in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix butter and crushed corn flakes and spread on potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: irish soda bread(award winner for the laoh feis)
directions: Cut shortening into flour with pastry blender or fingers until mixture has consistency of coarse corn meal.
Add, stirring quickly, the egg, buttermilk and raisins.
Turn dough onto a well floured board.
Knead dough lightly and shape into an 8-inch circle and place in greased pan.
With a sharp, lightly floured knife, cut a cross into the top of the dough.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; add remaining ingredients.
(Line casserole with tortillas, broken in pieces.)
Pour in 1/2 meat mixture and then shredded cheese.
Repeat.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: 3 layer noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions for 5 minutes and drain.
Toss with 2 1/2 cups sauce and meat.
Combine remaining ingredients for filling. Turn 1/2 noodle mixture into 3-quart casserole.
Spread cheese filling over noodles.
Cover with remaining noodles.
Top with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar, 1/2 cup butter, eggs, vanilla and milk together and put in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients for topping.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: blueberry crunch(quick and easy)
directions: Place blueberries in 2-quart baking dish.
Combine all other ingredients until crumbly and sprinkle over blueberries.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp with lobster sauce
directions: Have all ingredients measured and ready.
Set wok or skillet over fire and heat for 30 seconds on high.
Add 2 tablespoons of oil and heat for 30 seconds on high.
Add shrimp and stir-fry for about 1 minute or until they turn pink.
Add wine and stir for 30 seconds.
Remove shrimp from wok and set aside.
Add more oil to wok and reheat.
Add beans and garlic to wok and stir-fry for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add soy, salt, sugar, pepper and shrimp.
Add chicken stock and bring to a slow boil.
Add cornstarch mix and stir until it thickens.
Slowly add egg, stirring constantly, while adding. Remove from heat; stir in scallions and serve at once over rice.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, nutmeg and raisins in a bowl. Add apples, coating them well. Put the mixture into the pie shell. Make the Crumb Topping.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients together.
When you take from fire, add a generous lump of butter and vanilla.
Let cool and serve warm or cold as you prefer.

title: jam spice cake
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Sift flour
and other dry ingredients together 3 times.
Cream sugar and butter; add eggs and beat well.
Mix jam, nuts, coconut, raisins and vanilla.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place in two 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream the butter and sugar together. Add eggs, milk, vanilla, salt and potatoes.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: royal hawaiian snacks
directions: Trim crust from sliced bread and add butter to each slice. Spread mustard over top.
Cut each slice in 4 squares and arrange on baking sheet.
Cut ham and cheese into squares and place on top of bread.
Then top with a pineapple chunk and secure with a toothpick.
Bake until cheese melts about 8 to 10 minutes in 450° oven.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Combine dry ingredients.
Mix together and beat well.
If desired, add 1/2 cup nuts and 1/2 cup coconut.
Bake at 350° approximately 25 minutes in oblong pan.

title: microwave party mints
directions: Combine butter and milk in glass bowl.
Microwave on high for 45 to 60 seconds or until butter is melted.
Add frosting mix. Microwave on high until frosting is blended, stirring frequently. Stir in extract and food coloring.
Drop by teaspoonfulls onto waxed paper; cool.
Chill until firm.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: cherry cheese pie
