directions: Beat softened cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in milk until smooth.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours.
Top with desired amount of pie filling.

title: honey mustard dip
directions: In a small bowl, stir together vinegar and dry mustard. Add honey, green onions, Dijon-style mustard, thyme and oregano; mix well. Great dip for chicken nuggets or chicken fingers.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Cook sausage. Drain. Keep drippings. Saut celery and onion in sausage drippings and drain. Combine all ingredients. Blend well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: polenta
directions: Combine cornmeal, cold water and salt.
Stir into boiling water.
Stir constantly over low heat for 15 minutes.
Add 2 tablespoons butter and stir.
Stir until thickens.
Spread on polenta board or on individual plates.
Sprinkle each serving with melted butter (optional) and Parmesan cheese.
Spread on sauce and more cheese.
Grab your fork, mark off your area and enjoy.

title: beer hall pie
directions: You will need 2 pie plates.

title: fruit salad with apricot dressing
directions: In a microwave safe bowl, stir sugar, cornstarch, and apricot nectar until smooth.
Microwave uncovered 6-10 minutes until slightly thickened.
Stir in vanilla.
Refrigerate.
In a large bowl combine fruit.
Drizzle with dressing.
Gently toss to coat fruit.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook bag of egg noodles as directed.
Put noodles in a big casserole bowl and add soups, tuna fish and grated cheese.
Stir. Add milk until desired texture. Top with crushed potato chips. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cube salt bacon very tiny.
Put peeled, sliced potatoes in water.
Chop 2 onions fine.
Cook over medium fire until meat is done.
Salt to taste.
Usually has enough in bacon.
Mash with potato masher.
Add can cream to taste.
Thicken with a little cornstarch.
Slice eggs over top of each soup bowl.
This is a hearty soup served with cornbread.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well in large container. Use 1/4 cup mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cook onion in a skillet with hamburger.
Drain.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread hamburger.
Place frozen Tater Tots on top of hamburger.
Pour chestnuts on Tater Tots.
Mix soup with 2/3 can water.
Pour over Tater Tots.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of both kinds of cheese.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: purple cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir well and add mayo.
Toss just enough to mix.
Chill.

title: spinach snacks(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll into balls or spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Bake at
325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: saucy fruit salad
directions: Drain fruits and reserve 1 cup of the juice.
Combine fruit, pudding (dry), Tang powder and reserved juice.
Chill thoroughly. For eye-appeal, serve in clear glass bowl.

title: country squares
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Add flour and mix well.
Pour half the batter into a 13 x 9-inch rectangular ungreased pan.
Spread pie filling and then pour rest of batter on top, spreading evenly.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Cool and cut in same pan.

title: super nachos
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onions; drain on paper towels. Spread beans on bottom of baking dish and cover with hamburger mix. Spread on chiles.
Cover with cheese and top with picante sauce. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When done, mound guacamole in center with sour cream around.
Garnish with black olives.
Serve with corn chips.

title: shoe peg corn
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers and oleo.
Rub casserole dish with oleo.
Pour mixture into casserole dish; smooth over top.
Put the crushed crackers on top.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven, or until bubbly and brown.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer the first seven ingredients.
Prepare dressing.
Mix the mayonnaise, sugar and Ranch dressing.
Seal and let set for 12 hours.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Mix just before serving.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Gradually beat in one egg at a time. Add flour gradually.
Add lemon extract and 7-Up.
Pour into a well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours at 325°.
Allow to cool in pan.

title: banana cake(diabetic)
directions: Cream shortening, eggs and sugar.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: easy strawberry cream pie
directions: In blender or food processor, combine juice concentrate, cream cheese and pudding mix; process until smooth.
Transfer to large bowl; fold in whipped topping and strawberries.
Transfer to pie crust; spread evenly.
Cover and refrigerate until firm, at least 2 hours.
tags: frozen orange strawberry banana juice concentrate

title: rich chocolate peanut butter cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and 1/2 tsp. salt.
Add milk, water, oil, eggs and 2 tsp. vanilla;
blend until moistened.
Beat for 2 minutes, batter will be thin.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 inch round cake pans.
Sprinkle 1/3 cup morsels over each cake.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 - 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool in pans on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove cakes to wire racks and cool completely.

title: peanut butter turtle cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease two baking sheets.
In a small bowl, stir together flour and baking soda. Set aside.

title: carrots and potatoes
directions: In saucepan, bring 2 inches of water to boiling.
Add carrots and potato; cover and simmer about 25 minutes or until very tender.
Drain.
Beat or mash until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and reheat if necessary.
Serves 4.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and butter on low until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder. Add to batter at 1/2 cup at a time.
Alternate with milk.
Add flavoring and coconut.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 315° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Moist and delicious.

title: panama canal dessert
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and chopped nuts. Press with hands into glass 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.

title: weight watcher's lazy day lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, green pepper and onion.
Add salt, pepper, sugar and Italian spice to taste.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and water.
Bring to boil.
Let simmer 15 minutes.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer meat sauce and noodles (uncooked).
Add remaining sauce.
Top with 8 ounces part-skim Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chicken sundae
directions: Wrap each chicken breast in strips of bacon and dried beef, securing with toothpicks.
Place chicken in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
In a bowl, mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 200° for 3 hours (slow cooking makes very moist and tender).
Great served with brown rice.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Cut skinless chicken breasts in half, if not already cut. Wash and drain.
Mix cheese and mayo.
Spread over chicken and put on a baking sheet or shallow baking pan.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potato and onion bake
directions: Take baking potatoes and slice them 1/2 to 3/4 inch thick; do not peel. Peel and slice onions 1/4 to 1/2 inch thick.
Place on heavy foil a slice of potato and a slice of onions alternately until together, then sprinkle with garlic, salt and pepper.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: corn and sausage chowder
directions: Shape sausage into a large patty and brown 5 minutes on each side.
Drain off fat and break into pieces.
Put sausage into a kettle.
Return 2 tablespoons of fat to the pan and saute the onions.
Stir in potatoes, salt, pepper, basil and water.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in corn and corn liquid and evaporated milk.
Cover and heat almost to boiling.
Serve with French bread.

title: candied sweets(great for thanksgiving)
directions: Mash potatoes.
Put in butter, pineapple, cinnamon and 1 cup marshmallows; stir together.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 300°, then put 1 cup marshmallows on top for the remaining 15 minutes.
Should be golden brown.
I usually double for Thanksgiving.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Let cook 6 hours on low.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Spread in large casserole dish (butter dish lightly).

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat 30 seconds.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Test with toothpick.

title: italian meat balls
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Heat 3 tablespoons of olive or salad oil in skillet.
With wet hands, make into 16 meat balls. Brown slowly in oil, turning over with a rubber spatula to keep round and not break apart.
Let meat balls get a little crispy on outside.

title: chicken rice soup
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in Dutch oven.
Bring to boil. Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until chicken is tender. Strain; reserve broth.
Remove and discard onion, celery, parsley and bay leaf.
Remove and discard skin from chicken.
Bone chicken and finely chop meat; set aside.

title: quick fried apple pies
directions: Roll canned biscuits out on floured surface one at a time. Spoon sugared apples on dough.
Fold and seal edges with fork.
Oil a 9 x 13 x 3-inch pan, coat both sides of pies in pan so oil will be even for browning.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Check both sides to ensure even browning.

title: sugar-free striped pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Peel, core and de-seed apples.
Cut into slices.
Wash apple slices and put into a large bowl.
Set aside.

title: orange kiss me cake
directions: Reserve 1/3 cup juice from the orange.
Grind together the orange, raisins and walnuts.
Set both aside.
Sift together the next 4 ingredients.
Add shortening and 3/4 cup milk.
Beat for two minutes at low speed, then 2 minutes at medium.
Add eggs and 1/4 cup milk; beat 2
more minutes.
By hand fold in the orange-raisin-walnut mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt or angel-food pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Unmold after 10 minutes; punch holes in cake and drizzle with reserved orange juice.
Mix the remaining sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Sprinkle on top.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs well.
Add oil, vanilla and sugar.
Sift and mix together 2 3/4 cups flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to egg mixture.
Mix additional 1/4 cup flour, apples, nuts and coconut.
Fold into cake batter.
Pour into a fluted tube pan and bake for 60 to 70 minutes or until tester comes out clean.

title: pure fruit cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 large cookie sheets.
Mash bananas until smooth.
You need 1 1/2 cups.
Stir in oil, vanilla and salt.
Add oats, oat bran, mixed fruits and nuts.
Stir well to combine.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Pour sugar and syrup into a large saucepan, stirring well over medium heat until it starts to boil. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and stir until smooth. Add corn flakes and stir until well coated. Pour into a buttered 9 x 13 baking dish. Let cool, then cut into squares or roll into balls.

title: texas chili--dr. atkinson
directions: Soak beans overnight in water in a Dutch oven; cook until tender.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Cut beef chuck steak into 1-inch strips.
Heat half of the butter with oil in a large skillet.
Pat beef strips dry and divide into batches; cook until well done. Transfer to a large pot.
Add ground beef to skillet.
Cook over medium-high heat until lightly browned.
Combine with strips. Throw away fat.
Add remaining butter to pan.
Stir in onions and cook 3 minutes.
Add garlic and cook 2 minutes.
Transfer with meat to a large, ovenproof pot.
Stir chili powder into meat mixture. Add remaining ingredients except beans.
Mix well; heat to boil. Cover and transfer to oven.
Bake until strips are tender, approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Combine meat and beans.
Return to oven.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Add beef broth if necessary.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together melted
shortening, sugars, egg and water. Sift dry ingredients together.
Set
aside.
Add uncooked oats and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: sweet potato custard
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together sweet potato and banana.
Add milk and blend well.
Add brown sugar, egg yolks and salt.
Mix. Spray 1-quart casserole with Pam.
Put sweet potato mixture in casserole.

title: secret vegetable casserole
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter until tender (save portion of butter for topping).
Cook vegetables according to package directions.
Drain well and mix with celery, onion, water chestnuts, cheese and mayonnaise.
Put in buttered casserole dish and top with crumbled Ritz crackers, mixed with remaining butter. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until casserole is hot and bubbly and cheese has melted.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Beat in eggs; add peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Flatten and crisscross with wet fork.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Put milk and butter in double boiler and heat.
Add egg yolks, cornstarch, sugar and salt which have been beaten together.
Boil together until thick and then add vanilla.
Cool.
Add coconut and put into baked pie crust.
Cover with the beaten whites (meringue) or Cool Whip.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Drain.
Add chopped peppers and onion to macaroni, then add salad dressing. Sprinkle with celery seed, if desired.

title: stuffed chicken cutlets
directions: Cook stuffing as directed on box.
Filet chicken breast. Place cooked stuffing over filleted chicken breast; roll and place in baking pan.
Place a small piece of butter or margarine on each rolled chicken breast.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and parsley.
Add about 1/4 to 1/2 cup of water in pan and cover pan with foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Mix soup with water as directed on can and pour over chicken, cooking chicken uncovered for 15 minutes longer.

title: butter crunch
directions: Put all ingredients, except for chocolate chips, in cast-iron frying pan.
Cook on medium, stirring constantly, until brittle stage.
Candy will turn thick and amber in color.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet; let stand 4 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Let melt; spread over candy.
Let cure 24 hours.

title: mom's coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix
as directed on package in 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool 15 minutes, then poke holes in cake with fork.

title: diabetic dutch apple pie
directions: Combine apples, orange juice, cornstarch, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, nutmeg and fructose.
Blend together well and pour into an uncooked 9-inch pie crust.
Combine the flour, margarine and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon to make a crumbly topping and sprinkle over the pie.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 8 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar with oleo.
Add eggs; stir in bananas and lemon juice.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to banana mixture and stir in nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all together and form into balls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 70 balls.
"These are great served at large family get togethers for breakfast or brunch."

title: beefy mexican lasagna
directions: In large skillet, brown beef and drain.
Add canned tomatoes and taco seasoning; simmer uncovered, 5 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 can French fried onions.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and grated peel.
Beat together until well blended.
Sift flour and baking powder together with spices. Add to liquid mixture.
Stir in zucchini and nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pans. Remove and wrap each individually.
Can be frozen.

title: brownie
directions: Mix oil, cocoa and sugar.
Add eggs; beat until smooth.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and nuts.
Mix until just moistened. Spread batter into a greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate covered cherry cake
directions: Mix by hand; cherries go to bottom. Bake a little longer than instructed on box.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar or add whipped topping.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix eggs separately in small bowl.
In a pan mix flour and sugar; add eggs and gradually add milk.
Mix all together until thick like pudding.
Add vanilla.
Set aside until just about cool.
Take a large bowl and line bottom and side with waters. Add 1 1/2 bananas on top; add half of cooled pudding.
Add more wafers on top and more banana, then rest of pudding.
Top off with crushed wafers on top.

title: papaya kiwi fruit salad with orange dressing
directions: Peel and remove seeds from the papaya. Slice lengthwise into thin slices. Peel kiwi fruit and cut lengthwise into thin slices. Arrange papaya and kiwi fruit on 4 salad plates. Combine orange juice concentrate and honey in a small bowl. Stir in sour cream. Spoon dressing over salads; sprinkle with peels. Serves 4.

title: nutted broccoli with poppy seed
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion; cook until clear.
Remove from heat. Stir in sour cream, then remaining ingredients, except nuts and broccoli.
Keep sauce warm.
Arrange cooked broccoli on heated platter.
Pour sauce across the middle; sprinkle with nuts.

title: italian round steak
directions: Rub oil on steak.
Coat all pieces with bread crumbs and place in baking dish.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Roll crackers into crumbs and cut in fruit, nuts and marshmallows.
Put in bowl and pour Eagle Brand milk over all mixture.
Mix well.
Pack together in a roll and wrap in foil. Very good.

title: best broccoli casserole
directions: Bring salt and water to a boil.
Add rice and cover and remove from heat.
Let stand for about 5 minutes.
Melt butter in skillet.
Saute onion and celery until tender.

title: country french potato pie
directions: In blender or food processor, blend cottage cheese until smooth. Add mashed potatoes, eggs, salt, pepper, cayenne pepper and mix well. Gently stir in green onions (use a lot of the green part) and pour into pie shells. Top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 425° for 50 minutes. Check the crust after 35 minutes. You may have to cover with foil if too brown. Allow to cool slightly before slicing. Slices will not hold shape if too hot. Makes 2 pies.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, soda, salt and nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add pecans, apples and dates.
Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: hazel dubberly's broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into small flowerets.
Core and dice apples.
Add raisins and nuts.
Mix well the mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar; pour into broccoli and apple mixture.
Let set overnight.

title: poppy seed coffee cake
directions: Combine and set aside poppy seed and buttermilk.
Add almond extract.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk and beat.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk mixture.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Pour half of the batter into a greased tube or Bundt pan. Sprinkle half of the sugar and cinnamon on batter.
Add remaining batter and cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Cut through the batter with a knife for a marble effect.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mom's homemade soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook on low heat until carrots and potatoes are done.

title: dreamy apricot salad
directions: Combine apricot gelatin, sugar and water in small saucepan and bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar and gelatin.
Remove from heat and stir in apricots and undrained pineapple.
Set aside to cool.
Combine milk and cream cheese and beat until smooth. Stir in gelatin mixture and fold in nuts.
Pour into a large or two medium Pyrex dishes.
Chill overnight.
Top with Cool Whip or Dream Whip and additional chopped nuts.
Serves 20 to 24.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
Combine brown sugar, Karo, salt and margarine in a large pot.
Heat on medium, stirring occasionally, until it reaches a full boil.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from burner and add baking soda.
Stir until all foamy.
Pour immediately over popped popcorn, coating well.
Bake in large shallow pan for 50 to 60 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Cool. Store in an airtight container.

title: mexican chicken and rice
directions: Saute the onion and green pepper in the oil.
Combine all of the above and put in buttered, covered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until heated through.
May top with additional cheese.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Mix and bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook and cool potatoes and eggs.
Mix well and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients by mixer.
Mix all others by hand.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon; place in plastic bag.
Cube biscuits in four.
Shake a few biscuits at a time in sugar mixture until well coated.
Place in Bundt pan (spray pan with Pam).
When about halfway through, sprinkle some of the sugar on biscuits in pan; dribble with half of melted butter.
Continue until all biscuits are coated; cover with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove bread from pan while still hot.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa and salt; add to milk in a double boiler.
Stir and cook until thick.
Add beaten egg yolks, butter and vanilla; cook 5 minutes, stirring.
Cool and pour into a baked pastry shell.
Top with meringue of the egg whites and 2 tablespoons sugar.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix salad, pour dressing on and let set several hours or overnight.

title: i can't believe this is carrots
directions: Melt margarine over medium heat. Add carrots, syrup, salt and pepper. Cook about 5 minutes, then dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup water.
Stir in with carrots. Cook another 5 minutes.
Ready to serve.
Best carrots you've ever eaten.
One can makes about 3 servings.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown ground beef; add cheese and melt. Add rest of ingredients.
Make open-faced on half of a hamburger bun; broil until done (watch closely).

title: navy bean soup
directions: Clean and wash
beans;
add
to
the
gallon
of water. Bring to a boil and
cook
for
1 hour over a low fire.
After beans have cooked 1 hour, add chopped onions, celery, carrots, ketchup, salt, pepper and sugar.
Continue to boil under a low fire until beans are well done.
Add the small can of tomatoes and with a wire whip stir well.

title: salmon ball erma
directions: Mix all together; chill several hours and mold into 1 large or 2 small balls.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: baked squash
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased baking dish. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Serves 4.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Mix in separate bowl remaining ingredients.
Make a well in the center of dry ingredients and pour strawberry mixture into it.
Stir until all is moistened.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken salad casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water, adding desired seasonings.
Reserve 2 cups of the broth.
When cool enough to handle, cut chicken in large bite size pieces.
Place chicken in large buttered baking dish.
Combine soups and milk; pour over chicken.
Melt butter in reserved broth and add stuffing mix, blending lightly.
Spread on top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: snapper vera cruz
directions: Cut vegetables into long strips.
Saute in olive oil only until wilted; add picante sauce and saute one more minute.	Set aside.
Dust filets in flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Saute filets in olive oil over high heat.
When golden brown turn and reduce heat.
Top with vegetable mixture and sauce. Simmer, covered 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: beef and broccoli casserole
directions: In small bowl, stir together cornstarch, broth, soy sauce and brown sugar until smooth; set aside.
In 10-inch skillet over medium high heat in 1 tablespoon oil, stir-fry beef until browned. Remove; set aside and repeat with other half of beef.
Reduce heat to medium.
In same skillet using 1 tablespoon oil, stir-fry broccoli with garlic powder and ginger until tender-crisp.
Add reserved cornstarch mixture and cook until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Return beef to skillet and heat through. Stir occasionally.
Serve over hot rice.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook veggies and drain.
Mix in onion, celery, mayonnaise and cheese. Pour in greased baking dish.
Stir butter into crushed saltines.
Top veggies with saltines.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broiled peach halves with raspberry puree
directions: Place raspberries, sugar and lemon juice in an electric blender and puree until smooth.
Strain puree; discard seeds. Cover and chill.
Place peach halves, cut side up, in an 8 x 8-inch cake pan or small shallow baking dish.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle evenly over each peach half.
Sprinkle peaches evenly with rum; dot with margarine.
Broil peaches until hot and bubbly, approximately 10 minutes.
Place peach halves on individual dessert plates; top with chilled raspberry puree. Serve immediately.

title: crab dip
directions: Melt first 5 ingredients in pan over low heat until soft.
Add crabmeat. Serve hot or cold.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Combine all ingredients; pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle crumbled cheese crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: kugel noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Add eggs and mix.
Add butter and salt; mix.
Add cottage cheese and sour cream; mix.
Add sugar, cinnamon and raisins/pineapple; mix.
Bake in 8 or 9-inch Pyrex dish at 350° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: peanut butter creams
directions: Combine all ingredients except chocolate chips; mix until blended.
Remove from bowl and knead on board until smooth. Spread and pat into a 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips over low heat.
Spread over peanut butter mixture.
Cool until chocolate is firm.
Cut into squares.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together powdered sugar, peanut butter and cream cheese. Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: poke cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan as directed on box. While cake is baking, prepare cherry Jell-O with boiling water and cold water.
Let Jell-O stand at room temperature while cake is cooking.
When cake is done, remove from oven and poke holes into it with a fork.
Pour cherry jelly mixture over top and refrigerate.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, pudding, margarine, egg and 1/2 cup milk.
Pour into 9-inch pie plate or square pan.
Make a raised edge with batter.
Place sliced peaches over batter; sprinkle with 1 teaspoon of sugar and 1/8 teaspoon of nutmeg.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, and eggs.
Add corn flakes, oatmeal, and flour to which soda, baking powder, and salt have been added. Stir in coconut, pecans, and vanilla.
Drop in small amounts on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° until brown.

title: old fashioned molasses pie
directions: Soften butter and blend in other ingredients, adding molasses and milk last.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in a very slow 300° oven until set in the center or test by inserting a knife into center. If knife comes out clean, pie is done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together corns, eggs and muffin mix.
Saute onion and peppers in margarine.
Add to corn mixture.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Dollop sour cream over top.
Add Cheddar cheese over top.
Cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix
all well, except broccoli and cornbread.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: gardener's delight
directions: Cut each green pepper in half.
Remove seeds and membranes. Heat the butter.
Briefly saute onions and zucchini.
Stir in tomato, thyme and black pepper.
Spoon mixture into pepper halves. Place in baking dish.
Pour 1/4 cup water into dish.
Cover. Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes until the peppers are barely tender.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Mix soup, cheese, onion, macaroni and dried beef.
Fold in eggs and put into a 1 1/2 quart greased casserole.
Refrigerate 3 to 4
hours
or
overnight, covered.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick garlic toast
directions: Spread butter on one side of each slice of bread. Cut each slice in half. place plain side down on baking sheet. Sprinkle with garlic salt and parmesan cheese. Broil 4 inches from heat for 1-2 minutes or until lightly browned. You may also put this in the oven at 350 degrees. You must then butter both sides. Put one side in for approx. 8 minutes and the other for 5 minutes.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Combine milk and sugar in saucepan; heat to boiling.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into buttered 8 or 9-inch square pan.

title: championship bean dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Transfer to slow cooker, cook until heated through, stirring once or twice. Can also be heated in a heavy saucepan over low heat stirring often.

title: vidalia cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except onions (batter will be thin). Stir in onions, mixing well.
Pour into well-greased iron skillet and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: anna banana bread
directions: Mix together well.
Pour into lightly greased loaf pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: carrot cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Add and beat well the next 3 ingredients.
Add and blend the remaining ingredients.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) layer cake pans that are greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes in pan; turn out on rack and cool thoroughly.

title: veal parmigiana(microwave)
directions: In 4-cup measure, combine oil and onion.
Microwave on High 1 to 2 minutes or until onion is tender. Stir in tomato sauce and basil.
Microwave on High 3 to 5 minutes, or until sauce is hot and somewhat thickened. Dip veal pieces in egg. Dredge in crumbs. Place in a 12 x 8-inch dish. Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High 3 1/2 to 5 minutes or until veal is fork-tender.
Pour sauce over veal. Sprinkle with Mozzarella and top with Parmesan. Microwave, uncovered, at 50% (Medium) for 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: strawberry cheesecake pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Fold in whipped cream and pour into crumb crust.
Chill several hours.
Clean strawberries and place in a ring on top of chilled pie.
Brush strawberries with melted jelly.

title: baked beans
directions: Add 1 teaspoon Tabasco sauce to regular catsup to make it hot.

title: dill cucumber
directions: Up to one week before serving, slice cucumbers very thinly. In saucepan, combine white vinegar, granulated sugar, water, salt and dill.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over cucumber slices in 1-quart jar.
Cover tightly.
Makes 1 quart.
(I slice onions thinly and put in jar.)

title: delight salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Chill overnight or for several hours before serving.
Serves 20.

title: santa's boot cookies
directions: Roll dough to 1/4-inch thickness on floured wax paper placed on cookie sheet.
Cut dough with a 2 1/2-inch boot-shaped cookie cutter and freeze dough for 10 minutes.
Remove dough from freezer and transfer dough shapes to ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake according to package direction.
Cool on wire racks.
Then color 3/4 of white frosting with red food coloring and frost bottom of Santa's boot.
Use remainder of white frosting to make "fur" at top of boot.

title: hot turkey salad
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in a large bowl; toss. Combine mayo, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce. Add to turkey mixture.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole coated with cooking spray.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle evenly over turkey mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yields 4 servings (about 261 calories per serving).

title: salad dressing
directions: Blend ingredients in blender.
Refrigerate unused portion.

title: sister grandma's cherry salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in cherry pie filling and place in 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan and chill until partially set.
Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup boiling water. Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise together.
Gradually add lemon jello, whipped cream and pineapple.
Pour on cherry mixture and top with mini marshmallows and nuts.
Chill.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour; add eggs, margarine, and milk; mix well. Fold in vanilla and lemon flavoring. Pour into chilled pie shell and bake at 425° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake for 35 minutes without opening the door. Check to see if center is solid when a knife is inserted.

title: fluffy peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft & fluffy. Beat in peanut butter & sugar. Add milk slowly blending thoroughly into mixture. Fold in cool whip. Pour into prepared crusts. Sprinkle with chopped peanuts & freeze until firm. Serve partially frozen.

title: squash casserole parmesan
directions: Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Mixture will become set.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in water until well done.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until thick.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Slice bananas into a large bowl.
Beat until mashed, then blend all remaining ingredients.
Beat with mixer for 2 minutes. Pour into a well greased and floured 10-inch tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 70 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Finish cooling on rack.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Mix well.
Cook fast until it will break in cold water, then pour very slowly over 4 beaten egg whites.
Beat until thick enough to stand in peaks when dropped on wax paper or dish.

title: sliced ham with raisin sauce
directions: Measure cornstarch, salt, mustard and sugar into small saucepan.
Gradually stir in syrup, vinegar and water.
Add raisins and margarine.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture boils.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour over ham slices in shallow baking dish.
Bake in a 325° oven for about 1/2 hour.

title: all meat chicken pie
directions: Bone and chop chicken; place in bottom of deep dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup and chicken broth together.
Mix flour, butter and milk together.
Pour cream of chicken and broth over chicken.
Pour flour mixture on top of chicken mixture.
Cook at 350° for minutes or until dough is brown.

title: seafood quiche
directions: Lightly grease quiche dish or pie plate.
Lay seafood, then Muenster cheese over the bottom.
With wire whisk, mix well the eggs, light cream and milk, Bisquick and mustard and pour over all. Add crisp bacon.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: If desired, slice pineapple and orange pieces in half.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add a little pineapple juice if dry. chill for 2 hours.
Yields 10 servings.

title: shrimp gumbo with rice
directions: Add all ingredients except shrimp into a large skillet.
Cook until tender.
Deshell and devein raw shrimp.
Add to mixture and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Reserve half of the nuts; mix other ingredients together and form in a ball.
Roll in reserved nuts.
Wrap in plastic wrap or foil and refrigerate or chill overnight.

title: pear relish
directions: Easiest way is to wash pears, removing seeds and any dark spots.
Wash and seed bell peppers.
Peel and wash onions (jalapenos too, if used).
Grind all ingredients in a food chopper. Then mix all other ingredients in large pot.
Cook slowly for one hour or until thickened.
Pour into jars and seal.
Very good on pork or any other meats.

title: gourmet chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 13 x 15-inch greased pan.
Top with cheese and mushrooms.
Mix wine with soup; pour over chicken.
Mix dressing as package directs; spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May be prepared a day ahead, but allow extra baking time.

title: pineapple whip
directions: Prepare Jell-O mix with boiling water and pineapple juice. Set partially in fridge, then stir in 1 cup crushed pineapple. Return to fridge for short time.
Then stir in sweetened whipped cream.
(Do not make whipped cream too stiff.)
Return to fridge to set completely.
Before serving, trim with whipped cream and any other decoration desired.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and eggs.
Dice onion, celery, potatoes and eggs.
Combine sugar, yellow mustard, water, eggs, vinegar, flour and salt in medium saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Add butter and Miracle Whip.
Stir well.
Pour over other ingredients.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: For the breading, mix together meal, flour, buttermilk, eggs, celery and onion.

title: dot's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and peanut butter, then eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° on greased cookie sheets.

title: fondant frosting
directions: Combine ingredients and blend well.
Dip cooled baked cookies into frosting.
Set on rack or waxed paper until frosting sets. While still soft, frosting may be sprinkled with coconut, colored sugar, crushed peppermint or chopped nuts.
Good on brownies, butter cookies, nut cookies, molasses cookies, etc.
Makes frosting for 3 dozen.

title: broccoli rice casserole("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Cook onion and celery in oil.
Add frozen broccoli and cover. Steam over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pecans
directions: Stir, heat in 200° oven for 1 hour.

title: polynesian pie
directions: Beat together lemon juice, Eagle Brand milk and cream cheese, then fold in crushed pineapple, bananas and pecans.
Pour into two graham cracker crusts.
Chill 2 hours.

title: broccoli rabe cooked in oil
directions: Trim the greens and separate the tough stalk from the tips. Bring a saucepan of salted water to boil and add the stalks.
When they are almost tender, add the tips and cook another minute or two.
Drain.

title: layered fruit-cheddar salad
directions: Combine cream cheese and honey, mixing until well blended. Stir in sour cream.
Chill.
Combine cheese with lettuce; layer lettuce mixture, peaches, berries, grapes and cream cheese mixture in a large bowl.
Chill several hours.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: marinated broccoli salad
directions: Mix vinegar, water, oil, sugar, dill and garlic; pour over broccoli.
Cover and chill at least 12 hours.
Before serving, toss broccoli with olives and pimentos.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cover pizza pan or jelly roll pan with 1/4-inch slices of cookie dough.
Press slices together to cover all of pan.
Bake according to directions on package.

title: sloppy joes 2
directions: Melt shortening in skillet.
Add beef, onion, salt, pepper and flour.
Cook until meat loses its color, stirring occasionally. Drain off excess fat.
Stir in water, Worcestershire and catsup. Simmer, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes.
Serve in hot buns.

title: cream cheese clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients good.
Serve with Fritos.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread these ingredients in the pan in order listed.
Do not stir anything together.
Pour butter, melted, on top of other ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 60 minutes.

title: mom's pie crust
directions: Measure flour and salt into bowl.
Cut in shortening thoroughly with fork.
Sprinkle in water, 1 tablespoon at a time, mixing until all flour is moistened and dough almost cleans side of bowl. (One or two teaspoons more water can be added, if needed.)

title: blueberry bran muffins(makes 1 dozen)
directions: In medium bowl, combine bran, milk, margarine and egg; let stand for 5 minutes.
In small bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, baking powder and baking soda; stir in bran mixture just until blended.
(Batter will be slightly lumpy.)
Stir in blueberries. Spoon batter into 12 paper-lined or greased 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 22 minutes or until done.
Serve warm.

title: spinach salad and sesame seed dressing
directions: Rinse and prepare salad fixings.
Mix salad dressing and toss. Delicious!!

title: green beans with blue cheese
directions: Combine water and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and add beans.
Cover and cook 6 to 8 minutes; drain.
Toss beans with 1 tablespoon of butter, Blue cheese and pepper.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1-quart casserole dish and set aside.
